COPY public.destinations (id, name, slug, description, short_description, hero_image, gallery, highlights, best_time_to_visit, duration, difficulty, region, featured, published, created_at, updated_at, created_by, attractions) FROM stdin;
2b49568e-fffe-461b-8386-1bd25fc485e2	SIWA OASIS	siwa-oasis-egypt	Escape to a timeless oasis where ancient Berber culture thrives among palm groves and crystal springs. Float in salt lakes, explore crumbling fortresses, and witness sunsets over endless sand dunes in Egypt's most remote and enchanting destination, untouched by modern chaos.\n	Egypt's Hidden Desert Paradise	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/af52b26b-e4ec-4e83-9b28-d6e7809ff97b.jpg	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/eb2af2a7-b54d-421c-8595-d2e726ad564c.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/957ba652-62b4-4982-b4f8-9703795674b7.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/7e8d4459-0b7a-42f7-b848-15b837322809.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/dd90511f-0a94-46b0-940d-6e91709d2ee6.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/98dc523f-b9c5-4a7e-9848-b90906873b80.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/40f90eb2-c6fa-43b1-b7e2-789aecd39a82.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/6f3dc158-6576-4603-97b7-2deaf4c3ecf2.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/fa147e3d-3adc-4559-8571-6314a40ebb74.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/d2b06630-42e9-449b-9737-46cc6f130619.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b1653a8b-ce98-4b38-83a4-be0e94f79d94.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/45fe9576-cce8-4e88-a202-08e24eb7b091.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/3d190a01-5b2a-4a84-80af-cdce07c8a06b.jpg}	{"Shali Fortress","Temple of the Oracle (Aghurmi)","Mountain of the Dead (Gebel al-Mawta)","Cleopatra's Spring (Ein Guba)","Siwa Salt Lakes","Great Sand Sea","Fatnas Island (Fantasy Island)","Siwa House Museum","Hot & Cold Springs","Siwa Souq (Local Market)","Date Palm & Olive Groves"," Traditional Siwan Villages"}	October to April for comfortable temperatures; avoid summer's extreme heat (can exceed 45°C)	2-3 days (4-5 days for desert adventures and full immersion)	Moderate	Western Desert	t	t	2026-01-27 18:02:38.592541	2026-02-14 02:16:43.355	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	[{"id": "3b58b330-f59a-41b6-944b-744860ef5fa8", "name": "Shali Fortress", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/eb2af2a7-b54d-421c-8595-d2e726ad564c.jpg", "description": " The ancient mud-salt fortress rises hauntingly from Siwa's center, its crumbling kershef walls dissolved by rare rainstorms. Climb through labyrinthine passages to panoramic sunset views over palm groves and desert. This 13th-century citadel, once housing thousands, now stands as atmospheric ruins whispering Siwa's isolated history."}, {"id": "08504bb2-902d-4e94-a43f-01f37f237703", "name": "Temple of the Oracle (Aghurmi)", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/957ba652-62b4-4982-b4f8-9703795674b7.jpg", "description": " Alexander the Great journeyed here in 331 BC seeking divine confirmation as pharaoh from the god Amun. This ancient temple atop a rocky outcrop still evokes mystical power. Walk where the legendary conqueror walked, explore crumbling chambers, and gaze across endless palms from this sacred site."}, {"id": "dcea92ca-19e7-43b9-8fb0-7d24d98a8e5e", "name": "Mountain of the Dead (Gebel al-Mawta)", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/7e8d4459-0b7a-42f7-b848-15b837322809.jpg", "description": " Hundreds of rock-cut tombs honeycomb this hillside necropolis overlooking Siwa. Four beautifully painted tombs from Ptolemaic and Roman periods remain accessible, featuring vivid scenes of the afterlife journey. The clifftop views at sunset, with palm groves stretching to desert horizons, are breathtaking and haunting."}, {"id": "18df1874-fd0b-408e-8358-14c2a92c2ede", "name": "Cleopatra's Spring (Ein Guba)", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/dd90511f-0a94-46b0-940d-6e91709d2ee6.jpg", "description": " Legend claims Cleopatra bathed in this circular stone pool fed by natural springs. Today, locals and travelers swim in the crystal-clear water bubbling up from underground. Surrounded by palm trees with views of Shali Fortress, it's the perfect refreshing escape from desert heat and Siwa's most iconic swimming spot."}, {"id": "4d4dccba-a74b-4658-b00e-43606c58d091", "name": "Siwa Salt Lakes", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/98dc523f-b9c5-4a7e-9848-b90906873b80.jpg", "description": "Float effortlessly in hypersaline lakes where salt concentration rivals the Dead Sea. These surreal turquoise pools scattered across the desert offer therapeutic mud baths and impossibly buoyant swimming. Sunset transforms the landscape into shimmering gold and purple a photographer's dream and unforgettable natural spa experience."}, {"id": "3f616eef-d9da-4436-afa4-6696062fcbab", "name": "Great Sand Sea", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/40f90eb2-c6fa-43b1-b7e2-789aecd39a82.jpg", "description": " Endless golden dunes stretch westward toward Libya in this pristine desert wilderness. Adventure seekers camp under Milky Way skies, sandboard down towering dunes, and 4x4 through dramatic landscapes unchanged for millennia. This is Egypt's true Sahara remote, majestic, and humbling in its vast silence."}, {"id": "9ad6a0c4-69a5-492d-8ca2-ddbe2d57c64a", "name": "Fatnas Island (Fantasy Island)", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/6f3dc158-6576-4603-97b7-2deaf4c3ecf2.jpg", "description": " This tiny palm-covered island in Birket Siwa lake offers the most romantic sunset spot in the oasis. Walk across the causeway to traditional reed cafes serving mint tea while watching the sun set over water and palms. Local musicians sometimes perform, creating magical evenings of Siwan culture."}, {"id": "dd7e06ae-ad86-4439-8ed3-75492354e234", "name": "Siwa House Museum", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/fa147e3d-3adc-4559-8571-6314a40ebb74.jpg", "description": " This restored traditional kershef house reveals authentic Siwan daily life through original furnishings, wedding costumes, and household items. The mud-salt architecture, cool interior courtyards, and displays of distinctive silver jewelry and embroidered dresses showcase the unique Berber culture that thrives only here in Egypt's remotest corner."}, {"id": "b65432bc-4b23-47e7-9d0e-20938512baeb", "name": "Hot & Cold Springs", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/d2b06630-42e9-449b-9737-46cc6f130619.jpg", "description": " Natural springs bubble throughout Siwa, from hot therapeutic pools to refreshingly cold swimming spots. Bir Wahed in the desert combines hot springs and golden dunes for the ultimate experience. These natural baths, used for centuries by Siwans, offer relaxation, healing properties, and connection to the oasis's life-giving water sources."}, {"id": "5fba79b4-0d8f-4f1c-9ca1-5605eefaad96", "name": "Siwa Souq (Local Market)", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b1653a8b-ce98-4b38-83a4-be0e94f79d94.jpg", "description": "The traditional market pulses with authentic Berber culture handwoven baskets from date palms, Siwa's famous dates and olive oil, embroidered textiles, and distinctive silver jewelry. Unlike tourist bazaars elsewhere, this souq serves locals, offering genuine glimpses into Siwan self-sufficiency and craftsmanship unchanged for generations."}, {"id": "26827718-c10d-4ab2-b8d1-3f065b7fa6b2", "name": "Date Palm & Olive Groves", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/45fe9576-cce8-4e88-a202-08e24eb7b091.jpg", "description": "Over 300,000 date palms and 70,000 olive trees create Siwa's green heart, sustained by natural springs. Wander shaded paths through these agricultural forests where Siwans have cultivated legendary Siwa dates and pressed olive oil for millennia. The contrast between lush groves and surrounding desert creates surreal, peaceful beauty."}, {"id": "152470fb-fd51-4b2f-8db7-11df2940764e", "name": " Traditional Siwan Villages", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/3d190a01-5b2a-4a84-80af-cdce07c8a06b.jpg", "description": " Beyond the main town, small villages maintain the most traditional Berber lifestyles in Egypt. Women wear distinctive silver jewelry and embroidered garments, speaking the Siwi language. Respectful visitors can witness authentic ceremonies, traditional architecture, and customs preserved through centuries of isolation a living window into vanishing cultures."}]
668d9b8f-e994-4c9f-a84e-606cc2e6379d	ALEXANDRIA	alexandria-egypt	Feel the sea spray on your face in Egypt's most cosmopolitan city, where Alexander the Great's dream still echoes through Greco-Roman ruins. Stroll along the Corniche, dive into literary history, and taste the Mediterranean fusion that makes Alexandria unlike anywhere else in Egypt.\n	Where Mediterranean Breezes Meet Ancient Legends	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/695a8d6e-c479-47af-85e6-e3ef76158240.jpg	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/259bfbb7-ad96-4528-95c8-7180cb592211.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/fd7a4db6-f46b-477e-988d-8b5e3eb24002.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b7b85015-34dd-4349-9e10-434aa2d69c33.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/47b60e40-dda2-41a7-9fd8-2815650026a4.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/41f1ab90-1abd-460c-b5d1-9935b99fdf5f.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/948c3b2d-d09e-45f7-97a0-ddcdf33a81db.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/93df519d-090c-40c5-8185-f3632c6be30c.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f206dbd8-f592-452f-ac09-56c8a0570e8d.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/39262389-47cf-4bad-bc86-b81bce081c33.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b1a3a1c8-700c-4463-a0a2-f6920d513887.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/2a9875e0-6704-4174-8056-ebe1dda8e6f8.jpg}	{"Bibliotheca Alexandrina (Library of Alexandria)","Citadel of Qaitbay","Catacombs of Kom El Shoqafa","Pompey's Pillar","Alexandria National Museum","Roman Amphitheatre (Kom el-Dikka)","Morsi Abu El-Abbas Mosque","Royal Jewelry Museum","Ras El-Tin Palace","St. Mark's Coptic Orthodox Cathedral","St. Catherine Cathedral"}	March to November for Mediterranean climate; spring and fall offer perfect weather without summer crowds	2-3 days (4 days for relaxed exploration)	Easy	Lower Egypt	t	t	2026-01-25 13:41:25.406687	2026-02-14 02:15:53.134	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	[{"id": "9ffa2eb8-0185-4e98-a279-eb9d3132468b", "name": "Bibliotheca Alexandrina (Library of Alexandria)", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/259bfbb7-ad96-4528-95c8-7180cb592211.jpg", "description": " The legendary ancient library reborn as a stunning modern architectural marvel. This disc-shaped glass and steel wonder houses millions of books, manuscript museums, and planetarium shows. Stand where scholars once gathered, now reimagined for the 21st century, keeping Alexandria's intellectual flame alive."}, {"id": "75893942-be8c-41ba-b29e-b8f3fcd4264c", "name": "Citadel of Qaitbay", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/fd7a4db6-f46b-477e-988d-8b5e3eb24002.jpg", "description": " Built on the exact spot where the Pharos Lighthouse—one of the Seven Wonders once stood, this 15th-century fortress guards Alexandria's harbor. Walk through medieval chambers, explore ancient foundations below, and gaze across turquoise Mediterranean waters from walls where Mamluk soldiers once watched for Ottoman fleets."}, {"id": "75bc0e97-592a-4d10-81c6-3ff0b8b34ece", "name": "Catacombs of Kom El Shoqafa", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b7b85015-34dd-4349-9e10-434aa2d69c33.jpg", "description": "Descend into Egypt's largest Roman burial site, a mysterious underground necropolis blending Egyptian, Greek, and Roman styles. Three levels of tombs carved into bedrock feature haunting statues, intricate reliefs, and the eerie Caracalla Hall. This archaeological wonder lay hidden beneath the city for centuries."}, {"id": "72c467a8-6d81-4a56-a30d-ed24671935d8", "name": "Pompey's Pillar", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/47b60e40-dda2-41a7-9fd8-2815650026a4.jpg", "description": " This massive 27-meter red granite column rises dramatically from Roman ruins, Alexandria's tallest ancient monument. Erected in 297 AD to honor Emperor Diocletian, it stands among sphinx statues and temple remnants. Climb the surrounding hill for panoramic city views and imagine the grand Serapeum temple complex."}, {"id": "45ba0c62-cbcb-4b3d-8840-0d250990e29e", "name": "Alexandria National Museum", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/41f1ab90-1abd-460c-b5d1-9935b99fdf5f.jpg", "description": " Journey through 5,000 years of Alexandrian history in this beautifully restored Italian-style palace. From pharaonic artifacts to Greco-Roman treasures and Islamic-era masterpieces, each floor reveals another civilization layer. Underwater archaeology exhibits showcase sunken palace treasures from Cleopatra's submerged ancient city, recently discovered in the harbor."}, {"id": "38f88c74-af88-4c7b-bd16-12339b551eea", "name": "Roman Amphitheatre (Kom el-Dikka)", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/948c3b2d-d09e-45f7-97a0-ddcdf33a81db.jpg", "description": " Egypt's only Roman amphitheater emerges from the city center, its marble terraces still intact after 2,000 years. This 13-tiered semicircle once hosted performances and philosophical debates. Wander through adjacent Roman baths and villa mosaics, imagining when Alexandria was the empire's intellectual capital and entertainment hub."}, {"id": "9f50f154-f2e6-4576-885a-b3518717438f", "name": "Morsi Abu El-Abbas Mosque", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/93df519d-090c-40c5-8185-f3632c6be30c.jpg", "description": "Alexandria's most beautiful mosque rises in cream and ochre splendor above the Corniche. Built over the tomb of a 13th-century Sufi saint, its Andalusian-style architecture features soaring minarets and ornate interiors. The surrounding plaza buzzes with local life—fishermen, families, and the authentic Alexandria beyond tourist trails."}, {"id": "304b6167-86b7-4274-b461-5cefe4d97678", "name": "Royal Jewelry Museum", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f206dbd8-f592-452f-ac09-56c8a0570e8d.jpg", "description": "Step into a glittering palace showcasing Egyptian royalty's extraordinary treasures. King Farouk's diamond-encrusted chess set, Princess Fawzia's wedding jewels, and Muhammad Ali dynasty heirlooms fill ornate rooms adorned with stained glass and ceiling frescoes. This decadent glimpse into vanished luxury reveals Egypt's last monarchs' extravagant lifestyle."}, {"id": "775fb7c3-605f-4e6e-aa1b-b0859151b3fd", "name": "Ras El-Tin Palace", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/39262389-47cf-4bad-bc86-b81bce081c33.jpg", "description": "Egypt's oldest royal palace stretches majestically along the western harbor, where King Farouk signed his abdication before sailing into exile. Though primarily closed to public, its Ottoman and European architecture tells stories of power and Mediterranean grandeur. The surrounding gardens and coastal views embody Alexandria's regal past meeting sea."}, {"id": "50584dde-d72f-427d-8790-7b93f1484f6b", "name": "St. Mark's Coptic Orthodox Cathedral", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b1a3a1c8-700c-4463-a0a2-f6920d513887.jpg", "description": "Christianity's oldest cathedral in Africa stands where St. Mark the Apostle allegedly founded the Egyptian Church in 60 AD. Beneath the altar lies the saint's returned relics, while beautiful Coptic artwork and ancient icons adorn the sanctuary. This spiritual pilgrimage site anchors Alexandria's enduring Christian heritage."}, {"id": "c3848137-8d72-444c-9382-f577d3fd0f14", "name": "St. Catherine Cathedral", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/2a9875e0-6704-4174-8056-ebe1dda8e6f8.jpg", "description": " Alexandria's stunning Catholic cathedral showcases neo-Byzantine architecture with soaring domes and intricate mosaics. Built in 1847 for Italian and European communities, it reflects the city's cosmopolitan golden age. The peaceful interior, adorned with religious art and stained glass, offers sanctuary from bustling streets while celebrating Alexandria's multicultural soul."}]
040910bc-68fe-48aa-867f-016921b32428	LUXOR	luxor-egypt	\nWalk where pharaohs walked through the ancient city of Thebes, where every sunset illuminates temples older than time itself. Cross the Nile to the Valley of the Kings, stand between colossal statues, and witness one-third of the world's antiquities concentrated in one breathtaking destination.	 The World's Greatest Open-Air Museum	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/cd3b646e-b837-4c0d-bb9a-7cd32762c42a.jpg	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/d69e81ef-355e-4838-b8ef-af8a1a1a87af.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/6da3785f-91aa-4ff2-908b-8dede79bd0ea.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/c2af3eb6-4235-4b03-87ba-cd0c7a12238c.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/ad2443f3-23f6-4d29-b7d3-69c10d00850e.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/14a82eef-61b2-4112-9cd8-b66cdcbb506f.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/08d703a6-851a-40dd-a3df-0677b1eff808.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/d51736cc-d303-420f-a892-ff6a2a6a72ab.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/03fcc26c-3cfd-4345-87f8-3d8997e32515.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/ec8b69c7-8e31-48f9-b31b-156e9150e3c9.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/20fae0e6-d5eb-4a8b-8c84-563e7199773d.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/42a085ea-618d-4749-bfb4-fcf41d78bfc6.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/d33085d2-0df3-46dc-af3c-0b8028c4bd60.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b841eb12-02f3-4104-b2c2-dbf35ab89def.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/bca8edde-6207-4710-8af3-2f703944fc55.jpg}	{"Karnak Temple Complex","Luxor Temple","Luxor Museum","Mummification Museum","Avenue of Sphinxes","Valley of the Kings","Valley of the Queens (Tomb of Nefertari)","Temple of Hatshepsut (Deir el-Bahari)","Colossi of Memnon","Medinet Habu (Mortuary Temple of Ramesses III)","Ramesseum (Mortuary Temple of Ramesses II)","Tombs of the Nobles","Deir el-Medina (Workers' Village)","Temple of Seti I"}	October to April - mild temperatures, ideal for temple exploration without extreme heat	3-4 days (5-7 days for comprehensive exploration)	Easy	Upper Egypt	t	t	2026-01-25 15:05:21.359715	2026-02-14 02:16:05.661	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	[{"id": "96f64731-85b2-4549-a029-afa2cb7233b7", "name": "Karnak Temple Complex", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/d69e81ef-355e-4838-b8ef-af8a1a1a87af.jpg", "description": "Walk through humanity's largest religious complex, where 134 towering columns create a petrified forest of stone. Built over 2,000 years by successive pharaohs, this sprawling masterpiece features the sacred lake, towering obelisks, and hieroglyphs covering every surface. Evening sound and light shows bring ancient rituals magically alive."}, {"id": "00e52a2a-d8e5-4bd4-b3d3-a340a8a26435", "name": "Luxor Temple", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/6da3785f-91aa-4ff2-908b-8dede79bd0ea.jpg", "description": " Rising magnificently along the Nile Corniche, this temple glows golden under nighttime floodlights. Built by Amenhotep III and Ramesses II, it features the dramatic Avenue of Sphinxes, towering statues, and a mosque built atop ancient ruins. Walk where pharaohs celebrated the Opet Festival for 3,400 years."}, {"id": "10620ec0-9e0e-4fe2-8988-744b726d02a1", "name": "Luxor Museum", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/c2af3eb6-4235-4b03-87ba-cd0c7a12238c.jpg", "description": "This world-class museum showcases Thebes' finest treasures in stunning modern displays. Exquisitely preserved statues, jewelry, and artifacts—including finds from Tutankhamun's tomb are beautifully presented with context. The mummy exhibit and cache of royal statues discovered at Luxor Temple make this essential viewing for understanding ancient Egypt."}, {"id": "77dfeb77-62d0-4a02-b956-85befcfc017f", "name": "Mummification Museum", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/ad2443f3-23f6-4d29-b7d3-69c10d00850e.jpg", "description": " Uncover the sacred art and gruesome details of ancient Egyptian mummification. Actual mummified animals, preservation tools, and Canopic jars reveal the 70-day process of preparing bodies for eternity. This small but fascinating museum demystifies death rituals that obsessed a civilization for millennia, making mummies more understandable."}, {"id": "44929161-9612-47e3-8c9e-abccec468654", "name": "Avenue of Sphinxes", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/14a82eef-61b2-4112-9cd8-b66cdcbb506f.jpg", "description": " Walk the recently restored 2.7-kilometer ceremonial road lined with over 1,000 sphinx statues connecting Karnak to Luxor Temple. Once traversed by pharaohs during sacred processions, this ancient highway lay buried for centuries. Today's dramatic illumination transforms evening strolls into magical journeys through time alongside stone guardians."}, {"id": "124713aa-67db-4ea4-a6c3-99c54bc33b42", "name": "Valley of the Kings", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/08d703a6-851a-40dd-a3df-0677b1eff808.jpg", "description": "Descend into the legendary necropolis where 63 pharaonic tombs tunnel into limestone cliffs, including Tutankhamun's treasure-filled resting place. Vibrant hieroglyphs and painted ceilings depicting the journey to the afterlife still glow after 3,000 years. Each tomb reveals ancient Egypt's obsession with death, resurrection, and eternal glory."}, {"id": "9b455a34-5b22-4732-8850-f334bdbb3b2d", "name": "Valley of the Queens (Tomb of Nefertari)", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/d51736cc-d303-420f-a892-ff6a2a6a72ab.jpg", "description": "Queen Nefertari's tomb is ancient Egypt's most beautifully painted burial chamber an underground Sistine Chapel of the pharaonic world. Brilliant colors depicting the queen's journey through the afterlife remain breathtakingly vivid. Limited daily access and additional fees preserve this fragile masterpiece for future generations to witness."}, {"id": "2114139b-81b3-46f4-9047-6f5cb671d9ea", "name": "Temple of Hatshepsut (Deir el-Bahari)", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/03fcc26c-3cfd-4345-87f8-3d8997e32515.jpg", "description": " Egypt's most powerful female pharaoh's mortuary temple rises in three dramatic terraces against towering cliffs. Its unique modern-looking architecture, built 3,500 years ago, features colonnaded halls and stunning reliefs depicting Hatshepsut's divine birth and trading expeditions. The desert setting at sunrise creates unforgettable photographic moments."}, {"id": "c9918b7e-3af5-4d77-af1a-b14eb8464b15", "name": "Colossi of Memnon", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/ec8b69c7-8e31-48f9-b31b-156e9150e3c9.jpg", "description": "Two massive seated statues of Amenhotep III each weighing 720 tons—rise 18 meters from the Theban plain. Once guardians of a vanished mortuary temple larger than Karnak, they've stood here for 3,400 years. Ancient Greeks believed they sang at dawn; today they remain Luxor's most iconic roadside sentinels."}, {"id": "d9b07ff9-f5a3-465d-9c23-fbdb8bbdf502", "name": "Medinet Habu (Mortuary Temple of Ramesses III)", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/20fae0e6-d5eb-4a8b-8c84-563e7199773d.jpg", "description": " This fortress-like temple complex is Luxor's best-preserved monument, with towering walls depicting naval battles and vivid original colors still visible. Ramesses III's last great pharaonic temple features elaborate carvings, a sacred lake, and palace ruins. Far less crowded than other sites, it offers intimate encounters with antiquity."}, {"id": "22fad458-cf3c-4b21-a277-33b93bb05615", "name": "Ramesseum (Mortuary Temple of Ramesses II)", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/42a085ea-618d-4749-bfb4-fcf41d78bfc6.jpg", "description": " The fallen colossus of Ramesses II—inspiration for Shelley's \\"Ozymandias\\"—lies shattered among temple ruins that once rivaled Karnak. Massive pylons, headless statues, and columns covered in hieroglyphs reveal this pharaoh's megalomaniacal ambitions. The atmospheric ruins whisper of empires that crumble despite rulers' eternal dreams."}, {"id": "111864a5-d4f2-4bdb-8bbc-27c62982e744", "name": "Tombs of the Nobles", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/d33085d2-0df3-46dc-af3c-0b8028c4bd60.jpg", "description": "While pharaohs get the fame, nobles' tombs reveal vivid daily life in ancient Egypt. These smaller, intimately decorated burial chambers showcase hunting scenes, banquets, farming, and family life painted in brilliant detail. Less crowded than royal tombs, they offer authentic glimpses into how ancient Egyptians actually lived and loved."}, {"id": "92b84c13-2fe7-452a-9299-2a9a92918555", "name": "Deir el-Medina (Workers' Village)", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b841eb12-02f3-4104-b2c2-dbf35ab89def.jpg", "description": "Explore the remarkably preserved village where artisans who built the Valley of the Kings lived for generations. Small houses, workers' tombs with stunning paintings, and a temple to Hathor reveal daily life 3,000 years ago. This archaeological treasure humanizes ancient Egypt beyond pharaonic grandeur—showing the real people behind monuments."}, {"id": "87de477d-67f1-4975-bca6-fbb93dc83362", "name": "Temple of Seti I", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/bca8edde-6207-4710-8af3-2f703944fc55.jpg", "description": " This beautifully preserved temple in Qurna showcases some of Luxor's finest relief work and original colors. Built by Seti I and completed by his son Ramesses II, it features seven sanctuaries dedicated to different gods. The astronomical ceiling and delicate carvings make this lesser-visited gem worth the journey beyond main tourist routes."}]
3d32e78c-4f31-4341-a28a-1b71428bdfea	MARSA ALAM	marsa-alam-egypt	Swim alongside sea turtles and dugongs in pristine bays where nature reigns supreme. Dive legendary reefs untouched by crowds, venture into ancient emerald mines, and discover the Red Sea's last frontier—where luxury meets wilderness in perfect harmony.	Egypt's Untouched Marine Paradise	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/21be915c-4641-4097-ac72-d59676285109.jpg	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/bf30f017-84b2-4c29-ad98-297ec3b4d06f.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b5131299-bbc5-4394-8b18-f93c0aff7ea7.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/5efb2d41-fd9d-4920-8f85-3f69bd4082bb.webp,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/4e57f6e4-387b-48f4-b74b-2656078cdb6b.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/00d19e42-cf6d-4b9d-9c54-f7c4ab124fed.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/21be915c-4641-4097-ac72-d59676285109.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/7a7bd9aa-da13-4ce1-a344-b8e37ec695bc.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/2bca8272-76f8-4346-820a-ac9cd2a4eac0.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f68ad1db-41c1-4452-b674-bf4ca8a307b8.jpg}	{"Marsa Mubarak Bay","Abu Dabbab Bay","Sharm El Luli Beach","Elphinstone Reef","Dolphin House (Sha'ab Samadai)","Port Ghalib Marina","Wadi El Gemal National Park","Emerald Mines (Wadi Sikait)","Hamata Islands"}	Year-round; spring and fall offer ideal temperatures for diving and excursions	4-6 days (7+ days for diving expeditions and desert exploration)	Easy	Red Sea	t	t	2026-01-27 19:36:33.033793	2026-02-14 02:18:13.356	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	[{"id": "d32d8849-9aad-4626-8b79-48f9f2344d6d", "name": "Marsa Mubarak Bay", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/bf30f017-84b2-4c29-ad98-297ec3b4d06f.jpg", "description": "This protected bay hosts one of the Red Sea's healthiest seagrass meadows, attracting resident sea turtles who munch vegetation just meters from shore. Dugongs rare marine mammals occasionally appear in these calm waters. The easy snorkeling, guaranteed turtle encounters, and pristine conditions make this bay legendary among nature lovers."}, {"id": "63bdceaf-1b9a-4681-81a7-f587aa21f228", "name": "Abu Dabbab Bay", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b5131299-bbc5-4394-8b18-f93c0aff7ea7.jpg", "description": "Swim daily alongside gentle green sea turtles grazing on seagrass in this sheltered bay renowned for reliable wildlife encounters. The resident dugong occasionally surfaces, creating magical moments for lucky snorkelers. Pristine coral reefs, shallow warm waters, and guaranteed marine life make Abu Dabbab essential for underwater enthusiasts seeking accessible natural wonders."}, {"id": "d01b5fe8-48db-4d6c-b502-8ef0a33efd30", "name": "Sharm El Luli Beach", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/5efb2d41-fd9d-4920-8f85-3f69bd4082bb.webp", "description": "Arguably Egypt's most beautiful beach  a crescent of powder-white sand meeting impossibly turquoise waters in complete isolation. Protected coral reefs offshore explode with colorful marine life, while the pristine shore remains beautifully undeveloped. The stunning natural beauty, crystal-clear visibility, and tranquil atmosphere create paradise found at Red Sea's southern edge."}, {"id": "4ee35862-03f0-4c7e-8596-030f8387ac22", "name": "Elphinstone Reef", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/4e57f6e4-387b-48f4-b74b-2656078cdb6b.jpg", "description": "This legendary offshore pinnacle ranks among the world's most thrilling drift dives. Vertical walls plunge 200 meters into the abyss while oceanic whitetip sharks, hammerheads, and manta rays cruise the blue. Powerful currents sweep past pristine hard and soft corals creating underwater cathedral beauty. For experienced divers, this is bucket-list diving."}, {"id": "0931c102-af0f-4d34-8a93-ee2aabd012a1", "name": "Dolphin House (Sha'ab Samadai)", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/00d19e42-cf6d-4b9d-9c54-f7c4ab124fed.jpg", "description": "This horseshoe-shaped reef shelters spinner dolphins who rest in the protected lagoon after nighttime hunting. Snorkel respectfully alongside these playful creatures in designated zones, witnessing acrobatic spins and curious interactions. The reef itself dazzles with vibrant corals. Strict conservation rules ensure sustainable wildlife encounters in this marine sanctuary."}, {"id": "f129bca3-5728-41a9-a4bc-0e3e45561e17", "name": "Port Ghalib Marina", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/21be915c-4641-4097-ac72-d59676285109.jpg", "description": "Marsa Alam's sophisticated waterfront hub features luxury yachts, international restaurants, boutique shopping, and evening entertainment along beautifully landscaped promenades. The marina blends modern elegance with Red Sea relaxation cafes, bars, water sports centers, and cultural shows create cosmopolitan atmosphere. It's Marsa Alam's social heart where travelers gather after desert and diving adventures."}, {"id": "225250f5-a2aa-4da2-9dee-708f9ff21b64", "name": "Wadi El Gemal National Park", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/7a7bd9aa-da13-4ce1-a344-b8e37ec695bc.jpg", "description": "This vast protected area encompasses 7,000 square kilometers of desert mountains, pristine coastline, mangrove forests, and coral reefs. Ancient Roman ruins, Bedouin settlements, diverse wildlife from gazelles to migratory birds, and untouched beaches create wilderness adventure. Desert safaris reveal stunning landscapes and cultural heritage beyond the beaches."}, {"id": "01933eb7-833a-4a10-8143-3825c7f61188", "name": "Emerald Mines (Wadi Sikait)", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/2bca8272-76f8-4346-820a-ac9cd2a4eac0.jpg", "description": "Trek into desert mountains to explore ancient Roman emerald mines dating to Cleopatra's era. Abandoned mining settlements, temple ruins dedicated to mining gods, and old extraction tunnels reveal where precious gems were sourced for Roman emperors. The challenging desert journey rewards with archaeological wonders and historical intrigue few tourists ever witness."}, {"id": "12182303-8dce-4057-bfa8-42e52722c1c1", "name": "Hamata Islands", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f68ad1db-41c1-4452-b674-bf4ca8a307b8.jpg", "description": "This remote archipelago south of Marsa Alam features pristine uninhabited islands surrounded by virgin coral reefs. Turquoise lagoons, deserted white-sand beaches, and exceptional snorkeling in untouched waters create ultimate desert island fantasies. Day trips reveal the Red Sea's most pristine marine ecosystems, far from any development, where nature remains gloriously wild."}]
ae858398-cc75-4fff-a655-6a3c0c077020	SHARM EL SHEIKH	sharm-el-sheikh-egypt	Descend into the Red Sea's most legendary dive sites, where shipwrecks rest beside technicolor reefs. Scale sacred Mount Sinai at dawn, unwind in world-class resorts, and discover why this Sinai Peninsula jewel captivates divers, adventurers, and sun-seekers from across the globe.	Where Desert Mountains Meet Coral Gardens	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/7cfd0095-da59-430e-9a0d-34dfb5a00c32.jpg	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/9e02d97f-0cea-466a-91a8-fa580c1750b1.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b4f735f1-9ac3-427f-b13d-450c71799d28.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/c4d7e73a-dc4f-4a39-b24d-6e4890c0830a.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/5b7c038d-6cf8-4ab3-a907-a334f0f34202.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b4b2b5c7-ee77-4a4e-8a49-aa052f5918a5.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/7cfd0095-da59-430e-9a0d-34dfb5a00c32.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/461f9299-0646-458a-a41b-bd389ab1e7c0.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/19072d90-2003-41d3-99d3-5639b6128733.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b9da75ad-8256-4ede-a0e6-ea303d141380.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/58be1d05-33a7-40ea-8a8b-74ae4bd05575.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/6c2cbf84-a812-426a-bb74-738f0accc7fe.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/c3f63079-2a0c-4429-9114-41b0cf0b9e25.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b51d833a-c018-4615-a349-22d703c3581f.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b6706554-c1fb-40ea-bd9e-f00b134f03ef.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/da3696aa-b4ee-4f54-88be-589a7a335b97.jpg}	{"Ras Mohammed National Park","Naama Bay","Tiran Island","SS Thistlegorm Wreck","Blue Hole","Colored Canyon","Mount Sinai","St. Catherine's Monastery","Al-Mustafa Mosque","El Sahaba Mosque","Coptic Orthodox Church","Sharm El Sheikh Old Market","Soho Square","Shark's Bay","Nabq Bay"}	Year-round; spring and fall offer ideal temperatures for diving and desert excursions	4-6 days (7+ days for diving certification and Sinai exploration)	Easy	Red Sea	t	t	2026-01-27 19:11:56.269138	2026-02-14 02:17:52.333	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	[{"id": "eace36af-a286-4c74-8e15-55e77d1a2af0", "name": "Ras Mohammed National Park", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/9e02d97f-0cea-466a-91a8-fa580c1750b1.jpg", "description": "Egypt's first national park protects the Red Sea's most biodiverse marine ecosystem. Vertical coral walls plunge into the abyss, massive schools of fish swirl through blue infinity, and sea turtles glide past pristine reefs. This underwater Eden defines world-class diving a bucket-list destination for serious divers globally."}, {"id": "a3a002ca-388f-4889-80ff-ecc8bea2ff00", "name": "Naama Bay", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b4f735f1-9ac3-427f-b13d-450c71799d28.jpg", "description": "Sharm's beating heart pulses along this crescent bay lined with hotels, restaurants, and nightlife. The palm-fringed promenade transforms evenings into vibrant scenes of dining, shopping, and entertainment. Accessible house reefs make beach resorts snorkeling-ready, while the cosmopolitan atmosphere creates Sharm's signature blend of relaxation and excitement."}, {"id": "d859cfca-ea9a-4888-a46f-16c26aa8d0ea", "name": "Tiran Island", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/c4d7e73a-dc4f-4a39-b24d-6e4890c0830a.jpg", "description": "Four legendary dive sites in the Straits of Tiran Jackson, Woodhouse, Thomas, and Gordon reefs offer world-class wall diving. Powerful currents sweep nutrients past vertical coral gardens teeming with sharks, rays, and massive schools of fish. Jacques Cousteau declared these waters among Earth's most beautiful, and divers worldwide agree."}, {"id": "f49d93fe-90d0-4e36-8487-a870aabdd6a1", "name": "SS Thistlegorm Wreck", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/5b7c038d-6cf8-4ab3-a907-a334f0f34202.jpg", "description": "The world's most famous wreck dive lies 30 meters down a British WWII supply ship torpedoed in 1941. Explore cargo holds filled with motorcycles, trucks, rifles, and boots frozen in time. Schools of barracuda patrol the dramatic superstructure. This underwater time capsule delivers diving's ultimate historical adventure."}, {"id": "9b666cf4-f13f-4332-a4ab-3fad447677ab", "name": "Blue Hole", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b4b2b5c7-ee77-4a4e-8a49-aa052f5918a5.jpg", "description": "The Sinai's most notorious dive site a 130-meter vertical underwater sinkhole in Dahab, north of Sharm. Advanced divers descend into the abyss through \\"The Arch,\\" while snorkelers marvel at the rim's vibrant corals. Its dangerous beauty and technical diving challenges attract thrill-seekers worldwide, earning legendary status among extreme divers."}, {"id": "3ca15b0e-8691-4138-96d3-99d28d1d166d", "name": "Colored Canyon", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/7cfd0095-da59-430e-9a0d-34dfb5a00c32.jpg", "description": "This spectacular geological wonder features towering sandstone walls striped in reds, yellows, purples, and oranges. Wind and water carved narrow passages you squeeze through sideways, creating adventure-filled desert trekking. The three-hour excursion from Sharm through Sinai mountains rewards with otherworldly landscapes unlike anything else in Egypt."}, {"id": "b46745f0-970f-4e47-a3a1-4eade1cd3ede", "name": "Mount Sinai", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/461f9299-0646-458a-a41b-bd389ab1e7c0.jpg", "description": "Climb the biblical mountain where Moses received the Ten Commandments in predawn darkness, arriving at the 2,285-meter summit for sunrise over ancient pilgrimage routes. The spiritual journey whether via 3,750 steps or camel-assisted path culminates in breathtaking panoramas across jagged Sinai peaks. Sacred, challenging, and utterly unforgettable."}, {"id": "0abecba9-8fff-40d1-850b-cb81f8ff961c", "name": "St. Catherine's Monastery", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/19072d90-2003-41d3-99d3-5639b6128733.jpg", "description": "This UNESCO World Heritage monastery, built 1,500 years ago at Mount Sinai's base, houses priceless religious treasures ancient icons, illuminated manuscripts, and the alleged Burning Bush. Greek Orthodox monks still maintain this fortress-like sanctuary, one of Christianity's oldest continuously operating monasteries. History, spirituality, and architecture converge magnificently."}, {"id": "60e0c495-6b28-401b-a51a-d1efba9052d6", "name": "Al-Mustafa Mosque", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b9da75ad-8256-4ede-a0e6-ea303d141380.jpg", "description": "Sharm's stunning modern mosque rises with soaring minarets and elegant Ottoman-inspired architecture. Its pristine white facade, ornate interiors, and beautiful courtyards create peaceful sanctuary. Evening illumination transforms it into a glowing landmark visible across the city. Respectful visitors can admire its architectural beauty and spiritual significance."}, {"id": "d88d3683-a566-4bd6-84f1-875fed2e42d8", "name": "El Sahaba Mosque", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/58be1d05-33a7-40ea-8a8b-74ae4bd05575.jpg", "description": "This beautiful mosque in the Old Market area features distinctive twin minarets and traditional Islamic architecture. Built with intricate geometric patterns and calligraphy, it serves Sharm's Muslim community while welcoming respectful tourists. The surrounding area offers authentic Egyptian atmosphere away from resort zones, showcasing local religious and cultural life."}, {"id": "27cb7ad6-8e3c-4ccf-932a-b40c6dd3bd35", "name": "Coptic Orthodox Church", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/6c2cbf84-a812-426a-bb74-738f0accc7fe.jpg", "description": "Sharm's beautiful Coptic church showcases traditional Christian Egyptian architecture with colorful icons and religious artwork. The Heavenly Cathedral serves the city's Christian community, featuring distinctive domes and peaceful sanctuaries. Visitors can admire its exterior beauty and architectural significance, representing Egypt's ancient Christian heritage in this modern resort destination."}, {"id": "bace03fb-5c3d-4617-b9e3-f5071ccfd76e", "name": "Sharm El Sheikh Old Market", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/c3f63079-2a0c-4429-9114-41b0cf0b9e25.jpg", "description": "Step into authentic Egyptian market chaos spice aromas, colorful textiles, handcrafted souvenirs, and aromatic perfumes fill labyrinthine alleys. Haggle with friendly vendors, discover traditional cafes serving shisha and mint tea, and experience local life beyond resort bubbles. This vibrant souq delivers genuine Egyptian atmosphere and cultural immersion."}, {"id": "e19d93c2-632d-4651-a26c-5cdde17f5c0a", "name": "Soho Square", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b51d833a-c018-4615-a349-22d703c3581f.jpg", "description": "Sharm's entertainment hub features open-air restaurants, cafes, ice rink, bowling, cinema, and nightly shows in European plaza-style setting. Illuminated fountains, diverse dining from international to Egyptian cuisine, and family-friendly activities create cosmopolitan atmosphere. The amphitheater hosts concerts and cultural performances, making evenings memorable beyond beach days."}, {"id": "16b5ffd9-4d45-47ee-9589-432b875c4105", "name": "Shark's Bay", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b6706554-c1fb-40ea-bd9e-f00b134f03ef.jpg", "description": "This protected bay north of Naama features some of Sharm's most accessible and spectacular snorkeling directly from shore. The house reef drops dramatically just meters from beach, revealing colorful corals and tropical fish. Calmer waters, fewer crowds, and excellent visibility make it perfect for families and beginner snorkelers seeking underwater magic."}, {"id": "c25cf338-91e1-4197-9be0-f7ebc36d802e", "name": "Nabq Bay", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/da3696aa-b4ee-4f54-88be-589a7a335b97.jpg", "description": "Sharm's newest resort area features pristine beaches backed by protected mangrove forests the northernmost mangroves in the world. Luxury resorts line golden sands, while the shallow bay offers gentle swimming and excellent kitesurfing conditions. This quieter alternative to Naama Bay delivers upscale seclusion with natural beauty and world-class resorts."}]
873e4eb8-6438-449a-b63c-e74a0e4722ea	EL GOUNA	el-gouna-egypt	Drift through lagoon-lined canals in Egypt's most sophisticated resort town, where European elegance meets Red Sea beauty. Kitesurf turquoise waters, dine at world-class marinas, and discover why this eco-conscious paradise attracts discerning travelers seeking luxury without the crowds.	The Red Sea's Venetian Dream	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/6467dbf1-fef6-4b2f-b7ab-221fe958e007.jpg	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/746e4b44-bead-4ccb-b8c8-18e5b1426bdf.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/aa750f7a-83f2-4a0a-8908-e55a5b129d2e.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/64ba05c4-a7b9-4a05-b8a5-256a5971425c.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/189848a5-51a8-4003-b136-33174b4108aa.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/d7aa6aa4-598b-4293-8b5a-13abee77c614.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/53ad9426-a532-450f-a62f-1e299298bbdb.jpg}	{"Abu Tig Marina","Downtown El Gouna","Mangroovy Beach","Zeytuna Beach","El Gouna Golf Club","El Gouna Aquarium"}	Year-round; spring and fall offer ideal temperatures for outdoor activities	3-5 days (7+ days for full relaxation and water sports)	Easy	Red Sea	t	t	2026-01-27 19:21:42.020716	2026-02-14 02:18:02.295	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	[{"id": "ff9c5c12-32ac-4e4f-8f8f-f1711dfb0c27", "name": "Abu Tig Marina", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/746e4b44-bead-4ccb-b8c8-18e5b1426bdf.jpg", "description": "El Gouna's beating heart features luxury yachts bobbing in turquoise waters, surrounded by waterfront restaurants, chic cafes, and boutique shops. Evening transforms the marina into magical ambiance twinkling lights, live music, and Mediterranean atmosphere. Dine on fresh seafood while watching sunset paint the Red Sea golden."}, {"id": "04b9fc21-3e8a-4a3f-9542-00246fcdc4c5", "name": "Downtown El Gouna", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/aa750f7a-83f2-4a0a-8908-e55a5b129d2e.jpg", "description": "This pedestrian-friendly center showcases colorful Nubian-inspired architecture, art galleries, designer boutiques, and vibrant cafes. Wander car-free streets connecting lagoons via bridges, discover local artisan workshops, and experience El Gouna's cosmopolitan energy. The Friday market brings authentic Egyptian culture to this European-style town."}, {"id": "bb17c0e0-1a74-440e-9acc-4253d8b4f094", "name": "Mangroovy Beach", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/64ba05c4-a7b9-4a05-b8a5-256a5971425c.jpg", "description": "The Red Sea's premier kitesurfing destination offers consistent winds, shallow lagoons, and world-class conditions for beginners to professionals. This dedicated water sports beach features kitesurfing schools, equipment rentals, beachfront cafes, and vibrant atmosphere. Even non-kiters enjoy watching colorful kites dance across turquoise waters while lounging on pristine sands."}, {"id": "d0483719-bf5e-446e-a8f1-756e9c7d1441", "name": "Zeytuna Beach", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/189848a5-51a8-4003-b136-33174b4108aa.jpg", "description": "El Gouna's most beautiful public beach stretches along pristine white sands meeting crystal-clear turquoise waters. Palm-shaded loungers, beach clubs serving cocktails and fresh seafood, and calm swimming conditions create perfect relaxation. The stunning house reef just offshore offers excellent snorkeling, revealing colorful corals teeming with tropical fish."}, {"id": "ee286070-0f23-4ef7-8c4b-77031fd18414", "name": "El Gouna Golf Club", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/d7aa6aa4-598b-4293-8b5a-13abee77c614.jpg", "description": "This championship 18-hole course designed by legends Karl Litten and Gene Bates offers dramatic Red Sea views and desert mountain backdrops. Lush fairways contrast beautifully with surrounding arid landscapes, while strategic water hazards and challenging holes test golfers of all levels. Sunset rounds deliver unforgettable experiences combining sport and scenery."}, {"id": "1123980f-cf58-4e7c-ba49-d001eb31a68f", "name": "El Gouna Aquarium", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/53ad9426-a532-450f-a62f-1e299298bbdb.jpg", "description": "This unique Red Sea aquarium showcases local marine biodiversity in beautifully designed exhibits. Witness colorful reef fish, graceful rays, small sharks, and delicate corals native to surrounding waters. Educational displays explain Red Sea ecosystems and conservation efforts. Perfect for families and anyone wanting to understand the underwater world before snorkeling or diving."}]
6035fb03-cea0-4fd8-9d26-a56cb19579c5	CAIRO	cairo-egypt	Step into the soul of Africa's largest metropolis, where the legendary Pyramids stand eternal against a vibrant urban skyline. Lose yourself in chaotic souks, marvel at pharaonic treasures, and feel the pulse of a city that has captivated travelers for millennia.	Where Ancient Wonders Meet Modern Heartbeat	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/5bca76ca-51cc-4132-96fe-42bb1e11fd94.jpg	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/679bfff0-ea9a-45a3-9aa7-8baf79a60187.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/e7f7d38d-1463-4b02-a748-7b1d936efb5d.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/0b532122-2ddd-4da6-bfca-7862cdf396fb.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/59edd1b2-960a-4b82-87f4-afb346f24a83.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/d1769dfd-bfea-495b-89f0-ed33513b09ba.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/45ffd1f0-8883-4eb6-b048-595ef77dc9fc.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/59ddb2ce-84f3-46b7-8df5-c1553bfd20dc.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/60214a7f-b065-474d-abc9-206cc05f7cfe.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f67f393b-80fc-443a-b9a8-47bc119b20c9.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/444376f8-20ba-461b-967d-0f7dc9d06b64.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/cbe3325b-6bfd-4f25-bed9-5392744a6b97.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f22f70d2-f718-46df-b39b-f11e18e4e27d.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/987675f3-ae75-441f-9a57-59b0c2211c6a.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/517049f7-dcaf-4705-966b-61a4306544cc.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/63d59160-7cb4-49fb-a615-e0da277cbbfa.jpg}	{"Giza Pyramids Complex","The Sphinx","Saqqara Step Pyramid",Dahshur,Memphis,"National Museum of Egyptian Civilization","The Egyptian Museum","Grand Egyptian Museum (GEM)","Citadel of Saladin","Mosque of Muhammad Ali","Al-Azhar Mosque","Khan el-Khalili Bazaar","Al-Muizz Street","Coptic Cairo","Cairo Tower"}	October to April - pleasant weather for sightseeing; avoid summer heat (June-August)	4-5 days (7-10 days for comprehensive exploration)	Moderate	Lower Egypt	t	t	2026-01-24 14:38:07.453465	2026-02-14 02:15:22.124	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	[{"id": "5ff1d222-1085-4c85-a893-79056b5a26ba", "name": "Giza Pyramids Complex", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/679bfff0-ea9a-45a3-9aa7-8baf79a60187.jpg", "description": "Stand before humanity's greatest mystery—three colossal tombs built 4,500 years ago that continue to baffle scientists. Walk where pharaohs were laid to rest, touch limestone blocks older than history itself, and witness the last surviving Wonder of the Ancient World that has captivated civilizations for millennia."}, {"id": "1f2007f7-3aa4-407f-bb94-af3abb619111", "name": "The Sphinx", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/e7f7d38d-1463-4b02-a748-7b1d936efb5d.jpg", "description": "For 4,500 years, this enigmatic limestone guardian has watched over the Giza Plateau, its weathered face holding mysteries scholars still debate. Stand before the iconic lion's body and pharaoh's head, and feel the weight of millennia in the gaze of Egypt's most mystifying monument."}, {"id": "72779448-497f-43ad-a905-a93f8aec9811", "name": "Saqqara Step Pyramid", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/0b532122-2ddd-4da6-bfca-7862cdf396fb.jpg", "description": "Witness where pyramid architecture was born. Djoser's revolutionary Step Pyramid, Egypt's oldest stone monument, rises from the desert sands surrounded by nobles' tombs adorned with vivid scenes of ancient life. Walk through 4,700-year-old corridors where hieroglyphs still whisper stories of pharaohs and gods."}, {"id": "58d52e41-2d04-4b64-bd1a-a6c8bf0e9267", "name": "Dahshur", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/59edd1b2-960a-4b82-87f4-afb346f24a83.jpg", "description": "Discover pyramid evolution at this tranquil archaeological wonder. Marvel at the unique Bent Pyramid, where ancient architects changed angles mid-construction, and venture inside the Red Pyramid's mysterious chambers—something rarely possible at Giza. Here, you'll walk through pharaonic burial chambers in near solitude, touching ancient history."}, {"id": "0541f934-fece-400e-931a-fb3c8ae7874d", "name": "Memphis", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/d1769dfd-bfea-495b-89f0-ed33513b09ba.jpg", "description": "Walk through the ruins of Egypt's legendary first capital, where pharaohs ruled for over a thousand years. A magnificent 33-foot statue of Ramses II lies in eternal repose, surrounded by sphinxes and ancient temples. This open-air museum brings you face-to-face with the power that built an empire."}, {"id": "5c8faf33-282a-4f85-95fe-7e8dfc5b41f9", "name": "National Museum of Egyptian Civilization", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/45ffd1f0-8883-4eb6-b048-595ef77dc9fc.jpg", "description": "Journey through 50,000 years of heritage in this stunning lakeside museum. The Royal Mummies Hall is unforgettable come face-to-face with Egypt's greatest pharaohs, from Ramses II to Hatshepsut, preserved in remarkable detail. Their stories of power, love, and legacy come alive in state-of-the-art displays."}, {"id": "81fbf545-83d0-409d-8d89-a84351a22b5b", "name": "The Egyptian Museum", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/59ddb2ce-84f3-46b7-8df5-c1553bfd20dc.jpg", "description": "Step into treasure overload 160,000 artifacts spanning 5,000 years fill this iconic pink palace in Tahrir Square. Gaze upon Tutankhamun's golden death mask, stand before royal mummies, and wander halls crammed with jewelry, sarcophagi, and statues. Every corner reveals pharaonic wonders that museums worldwide envy."}, {"id": "285623a8-6c43-438a-baa1-8ab5e68a5e7e", "name": "Grand Egyptian Museum (GEM)", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/60214a7f-b065-474d-abc9-206cc05f7cfe.jpg", "description": "The world's largest archaeological museum dedicated to one civilization opens a new chapter in Egyptology. King Tut's complete 5,000-piece collection displayed together for the first time, colossal statues of Ramses II greeting you at the entrance, and cutting-edge technology bringing ancient Egypt breathtakingly to life."}, {"id": "a38f3674-321d-414a-a6bc-de79eb56aa4a", "name": "Citadel of Saladin", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f67f393b-80fc-443a-b9a8-47bc119b20c9.jpg", "description": "Saladin's mighty fortress crowns Cairo's skyline, built to defend against Crusader armies 800 years ago. Wander through stone courtyards where Ottoman sultans ruled, marvel at the glowing Alabaster Mosque, and witness panoramic views from ramparts that have watched empires rise and fall through the centuries."}, {"id": "4b41f7d3-c641-4c7b-84af-293b1cb69c34", "name": "Mosque of Muhammad Ali", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/444376f8-20ba-461b-967d-0f7dc9d06b64.jpg", "description": " The Alabaster Mosque gleams like a crown atop the Citadel, its Ottoman domes and soaring minarets visible across Cairo. Step inside to discover walls clad in luminous alabaster, intricate Islamic calligraphy, and massive chandeliers illuminating prayer halls. This architectural masterpiece blends Turkish elegance with Egyptian grandeur."}, {"id": "33f0075c-21b4-4b8f-ba0e-94b7d927833a", "name": "Al-Azhar Mosque", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/cbe3325b-6bfd-4f25-bed9-5392744a6b97.jpg", "description": " For over a millennium, Al-Azhar has been Islam's intellectual heart, where scholars from across the world have studied. Wander through peaceful courtyards adorned with ancient minarets, witness students debating theology as they have for centuries, and feel the spiritual gravity of one of history's oldest continuously operating universities."}, {"id": "e1292dd9-5d45-4519-b008-7654d64acdf6", "name": "Khan el-Khalili Bazaar", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f22f70d2-f718-46df-b39b-f11e18e4e27d.jpg", "description": "Step into Cairo's legendary medieval maze, alive with commerce for over 600 years. Watch master craftsmen hammer copper, inhale exotic spices wafting through narrow alleys, and haggle for handmade treasures in souks where sultans once shopped. Sip mint tea in historic cafes where traders' stories echo through time."}, {"id": "d0586330-dcd2-40ff-a6bf-f955850b47da", "name": "Al-Muizz Street", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/987675f3-ae75-441f-9a57-59b0c2211c6a.jpg", "description": "Walk through the Islamic world's best-preserved medieval street, a living museum spanning a thousand years. Magnificent mosques, ornate fountains, and historic mansions line this pedestrian thoroughfare where Fatimid caliphs once paraded. As sunset gilds the minarets, you'll understand why this street is Cairo's architectural soul."}, {"id": "94cf1bcd-8cdc-4f04-8af7-64d12ec509eb", "name": "Coptic Cairo", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/517049f7-dcaf-4705-966b-61a4306544cc.jpg", "description": " Enter the ancient Christian heart of Egypt, where sacred churches rise from Roman fortress ruins. The Hanging Church seems to float above the old Babylon gate, while narrow lanes lead to monasteries and the cave where the Holy Family allegedly sheltered. Centuries of Coptic devotion emanate from every ancient stone."}, {"id": "6fdf1b82-651e-4335-8b5c-244553d03f04", "name": "Cairo Tower", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/63d59160-7cb4-49fb-a615-e0da277cbbfa.jpg", "description": "Soar 187 meters above the Nile in this iconic lotus-shaped tower, Cairo's mid-century modern masterpiece. From the observation deck, watch the sprawling megacity stretch to the pyramids on the horizon. Time your visit for sunset, then dine in the revolving restaurant as millions of lights twinkle below."}]
1df89a9e-2773-4163-8899-640f1c31532d	ASWAN	aswan-egypt	Experience the magic of Egypt's sunniest city, where golden desert meets the eternal Nile. Sail on traditional feluccas, explore ancient temples, and immerse yourself in authentic Nubian culture and hospitality that has welcomed travelers for millennia.\n	Gateway to Nubian Heritage	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/a1789443-f53c-4855-95bf-ef4ee2274642.jpg	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/a38ad710-27e9-4e01-ba42-fd29f286ac60.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/ae1b67c8-203f-4f53-bcb8-724d210dedcd.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b6c9ead5-231c-4903-a245-9aae0523f36d.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/bf973d95-0da6-486a-9ef1-d119a4890420.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/e02829a8-4360-450a-825f-f5415e8b015d.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/3bccd294-bce6-42c9-ac2d-40d3192ab157.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/8f62655d-bc25-490f-96f6-5845a7cfb67e.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/9bf81a66-13da-48b0-bd5c-900744dd0890.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/5d38d651-a33f-4ac4-93a7-e907154e0663.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/341a6e96-fd4f-49e5-a046-b715c0a1fd8d.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/2b56a6b1-9612-4757-ba4d-c69bed884a21.jpg}	{"Philae Temple (Temple of Isis on Agilkia Island)","Abu Simbel Temples (Great Temple & Temple of Hathor)","Unfinished Obelisk","Elephantine Island (Temple of Khnum, Aswan Museum, Nilometer)","Nubian Museum","St. Simeon's Monastery","Tombs of the Nobles (Qubbet El-Hawa)","Temple of Kom Ombo","Edfu Temple (Temple of Horus)","Kalabsha Temple","Aga Khan Mausoleum"}	October to April for ideal weather; year-round destination with warm, dry climate	2-3 days (4-5 days including Abu Simbel and extended Nubian experiences)	Easy	Upper Egypt	t	t	2026-01-25 16:01:39.613886	2026-02-14 02:17:10.336	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	[{"id": "07085b25-a562-45bd-ab03-43fabe895db4", "name": "Philae Temple (Temple of Isis on Agilkia Island)", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/a38ad710-27e9-4e01-ba42-fd29f286ac60.jpg", "description": " This enchanting island sanctuary dedicated to the goddess Isis was rescued stone-by-stone from rising Nile waters and relocated to Agilkia Island. Intricate hieroglyphs, graceful columns, and evening sound-and-light shows bring ancient worship rituals magically alive on this sacred isle accessible only by boat."}, {"id": "91ef7ad8-3f8f-40a6-9e81-aa9086d076ef", "name": "Abu Simbel Temples (Great Temple & Temple of Hathor)", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/ae1b67c8-203f-4f53-bcb8-724d210dedcd.jpg", "description": " Four colossal 20-meter seated statues of Ramesses II guard this rock-cut wonder carved into a mountainside 280 kilometers south of Aswan. Twice yearly, sunlight penetrates 60 meters deep to illuminate inner sanctuaries. The adjacent Temple of Hathor honors Queen Nefertari in equally breathtaking splendor."}, {"id": "899397f1-08fa-4770-9181-65aca5e2834d", "name": "Unfinished Obelisk", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b6c9ead5-231c-4903-a245-9aae0523f36d.jpg", "description": " Witness ancient quarrying secrets at this massive obelisk still attached to bedrock, abandoned 3,500 years ago when cracks appeared. At 42 meters long and 1,200 tons, it would've been Egypt's largest. Tool marks and splitting techniques reveal how pharaohs carved these monumental monuments from solid granite."}, {"id": "e146a034-fe61-4721-a01c-57193c3e47c2", "name": "Elephantine Island (Temple of Khnum, Aswan Museum, Nilometer)", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/bf973d95-0da6-486a-9ef1-d119a4890420.jpg", "description": " Aswan's largest Nile island cradles 4,000 years of history—ancient temples to the ram-headed god Khnum, a museum showcasing finds from Nubian archaeology, and stepped Nilometers that measured flood levels for millennia. Peaceful Nubian villages make this a perfect afternoon escape from mainland bustle."}, {"id": "e379fdc9-b505-4209-990d-64011603805d", "name": "Nubian Museum", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/e02829a8-4360-450a-825f-f5415e8b015d.jpg", "description": " This stunning architectural gem showcases 7,000 years of Nubian civilization rescued before Lake Nasser's creation. Beautifully displayed artifacts, reconstructed Nubian houses, pottery, jewelry, and statues reveal the rich culture of Egypt's southernmost people. The peaceful gardens feature traditional dwellings and ancient rock carvings relocated from flooded sites."}, {"id": "6c8aa884-c14d-4462-b0e3-c75361f94d4d", "name": "St. Simeon's Monastery", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/3bccd294-bce6-42c9-ac2d-40d3192ab157.jpg", "description": " This haunting 7th-century Coptic monastery fortress rises from desert sands on Aswan's west bank, accessible only by camel or foot. Once home to 300 monks, its massive walls, frescoed church, and monastic cells evoke early Christian desert spirituality. The panoramic Nile views and atmospheric ruins make the journey unforgettable."}, {"id": "6f7fc981-a47e-4bcb-9b64-4bed9ec07095", "name": "Tombs of the Nobles (Qubbet El-Hawa)", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/8f62655d-bc25-490f-96f6-5845a7cfb67e.jpg", "description": " Carved into cliffs on the west bank, these decorated tombs of ancient governors offer spectacular Nile panoramas and intimate glimpses into provincial elite life. Vivid paintings depict hunting, farming, and daily activities 4,000 years ago. The steep climb rewards with breathtaking sunset views over Aswan's islands."}, {"id": "fe627d06-afdc-4355-a487-f8ce7581af62", "name": "Temple of Kom Ombo", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/9bf81a66-13da-48b0-bd5c-900744dd0890.jpg", "description": "This unique double temple dedicated to both crocodile-god Sobek and falcon-god Haroeris rises dramatically above the Nile between Aswan and Luxor. Symmetrical halls, a crocodile museum with mummified specimens, and ancient medical instruments carved on walls make this riverside stop fascinating. Best visited on Nile cruises at sunset."}, {"id": "4074c7b2-78ff-452b-a4dd-bcc05a356a38", "name": "Edfu Temple (Temple of Horus)", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/5d38d651-a33f-4ac4-93a7-e907154e0663.jpg", "description": " Egypt's best-preserved ancient temple stands majestically in Edfu, a Nile town between Aswan and Luxor. Dedicated to falcon-god Horus, its towering pylons, roofed hypostyle hall, and detailed hieroglyphs reveal Ptolemaic-era worship. The temple's remarkable state of preservation offers the most complete ancient Egyptian temple experience possible."}, {"id": "1c6647fa-dd56-4972-88b9-0cf2fb1f3995", "name": "Kalabsha Temple", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/341a6e96-fd4f-49e5-a046-b715c0a1fd8d.jpg", "description": " Rescued from Lake Nasser's waters and relocated near the High Dam, this impressive Nubian temple dedicated to Manduli features beautifully preserved reliefs and columns. Built during Roman times, it blends Egyptian and Greco-Roman architectural styles. The lakeside setting and relative solitude make this rescued monument particularly atmospheric."}, {"id": "2190c4c3-496a-48cf-9e94-09ed5cad2a75", "name": "Aga Khan Mausoleum", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/2b56a6b1-9612-4757-ba4d-c69bed884a21.jpg", "description": "This elegant pink sandstone mausoleum crowns a hilltop on the west bank, where Sultan Sir Muhammad Shah Aga Khan III rests. Built in 1959 in Fatimid Egyptian style, the domed structure overlooks the Nile he loved. Though closed to visitors, its exterior architecture and commanding position create stunning photographic moments."}]
cff5dd4b-b7c1-4a1d-ab6e-97e285288d61	HURGHADA	hurghada-egypt	Dive into a turquoise paradise where vibrant coral reefs meet golden desert shores. Snorkel with dolphins, sail to pristine islands, and surrender to sun-soaked luxury in Egypt's ultimate beach escape, where adventure and relaxation blend beneath endless blue skies.\n		https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/c80e4d44-5828-4248-990a-80f8aff187e4.jpg	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/62f6cc82-eebd-4da7-b8cb-c10857524acc.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/155264d7-7ccf-411e-b4fb-66eba4334a94.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/19978fd9-240a-480d-8854-220a36d73b47.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f29f1199-aeec-41dd-87b7-30af4e56cec2.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/24ce8bab-5835-4d8f-8298-9a63e1b33084.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/10c19cd2-d7c1-4e02-b87c-2ede41610729.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/c2eba6cb-55b7-42dd-8185-d96ac5b16ab8.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/59069bd9-f6bb-4ab7-9421-d9e21d65a98c.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/cc264c37-43be-4944-abf9-28d68bd2a5bc.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/9af4ef78-2f2d-40de-8dec-874a194188a6.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/4995afed-d0fd-4642-8b3c-9049923a1ddc.webp,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f55a8579-9d5a-4a59-8139-824345b51a8e.webp,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/633bb3f4-7dd9-4004-a169-c0bdec64de24.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/113abad6-6400-4c16-8471-28005b5f9c2f.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/fa68bb90-8719-4602-bc1c-eded0ae0a166.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/a3d44b60-71fc-421c-9851-e61f637876a1.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/58e8988a-eeea-4b37-872b-7406ab8fff38.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/c80e4d44-5828-4248-990a-80f8aff187e4.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/fc861c58-ffe6-4ef2-9978-0e5f118d33e3.jpg}	{"Giftun Island (Mahmya Island)","Orange Bay Island","Paradise Island","Hurghada Marina","Hurghada Grand Aquarium","Al-Mina Mosque","Mini Egypt Park","Hurghada Museum","1001 Arabian Nights Show","Sand City","Senzo Mall","El Dahar Bazaar","Makadi Water World","Sindbad Submarine","Dolphin House (Sha'ab El Erg)","Sharm El Naga Bay","Utopia Island","Sahl Hasheesh Bay","Coptic Cathedral of Saint Shenouda"}	Year-round destination; ideal spring and fall	3-5 days (7+ days for diving courses and island hopping)	Easy	Red Sea	t	t	2026-01-27 18:49:20.36266	2026-02-14 02:17:23.762	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	[{"id": "d4a84762-630b-4431-8796-791c7f7ba5ba", "name": "Giftun Island (Mahmya Island)", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/62f6cc82-eebd-4da7-b8cb-c10857524acc.jpg", "description": "This protected national park island boasts Hurghada's most pristine beachespowder-white sand lapped by impossibly turquoise waters. Snorkel vibrant coral gardens teeming with tropical fish, lounge under palm-shade palapas, and lunch at beachfront restaurants. It's Red Sea perfection, accessible by boat from Hurghada's marinas."}, {"id": "6424775a-24ef-453d-9c9b-1c926940293c", "name": "Orange Bay Island", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/155264d7-7ccf-411e-b4fb-66eba4334a94.jpg", "description": "Recently emerged as Hurghada's trendiest island escape, Orange Bay dazzles with brilliant turquoise shallows perfect for Instagram-worthy photos. Pristine sandbars, colorful beach loungers, and protected snorkeling spots make this the ultimate day-trip destination. The journey itself sailing across cobalt waters rivals the destination's beauty."}, {"id": "e1fe6944-98d6-4132-8375-284d8107cac1", "name": "Paradise Island", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/19978fd9-240a-480d-8854-220a36d73b47.jpg", "description": "True to its name, this small island offers untouched coral reefs steps from sandy shores. Snorkel among parrotfish and rays in crystal-clear shallows, then relax on quiet beaches far from resort crowds. The surrounding waters showcase the Red Sea's legendary underwater diversity in shallow, easily accessible depths."}, {"id": "59f95469-7d6b-4bfa-9454-a8b8656f2552", "name": "Hurghada Marina", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f29f1199-aeec-41dd-87b7-30af4e56cec2.jpg", "description": "This modern waterfront promenade buzzes with Mediterranean energy luxury yachts, open-air restaurants, designer boutiques, and lively cafes. Evening transforms the marina into magical ambiance with twinkling lights reflecting on water. It's the perfect spot for sunset cocktails, fresh seafood dinners, and people-watching in cosmopolitan style."}, {"id": "70207ab9-b6ad-41b3-979a-487e9a4dd20b", "name": "Hurghada Grand Aquarium", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/24ce8bab-5835-4d8f-8298-9a63e1b33084.jpg", "description": "Egypt's largest aquarium transports you through marine ecosystems from Red Sea coral reefs to Amazon rainforests. Walk through underwater tunnels surrounded by sharks, rays, and sea turtles, then explore mini-zoo exhibits and rainforest habitats. This world-class attraction offers marine education combined with entertainment for all ages."}, {"id": "ea3976fa-727f-4cfe-8183-0220f0b5d5b6", "name": "Al-Mina Mosque", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/10c19cd2-d7c1-4e02-b87c-2ede41610729.jpg", "description": "Hurghada's stunning modern mosque rises majestically along the marina with twin minarets and elegant architecture. Its pristine white facade, ornate interiors, and peaceful courtyards create spiritual sanctuary. Non-Muslim visitors can admire its beauty from outside, especially when illuminated at night, making it a architectural landmark and photographic highlight."}, {"id": "13a40770-b038-4614-803a-eebc0c6f9dcb", "name": "Mini Egypt Park", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/c2eba6cb-55b7-42dd-8185-d96ac5b16ab8.jpg", "description": "Experience all of Egypt's monuments in miniature at this fascinating open-air museum. Accurate 1:25 scale replicas of pyramids, temples, mosques, and landmarks let you tour Egypt in hours. Evening illumination brings the tiny monuments to life, making it perfect for families and anyone wanting Egypt's highlights condensed."}, {"id": "2ceafd19-fb70-42a4-b62d-2c8b4bed6de8", "name": "Hurghada Museum", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/59069bd9-f6bb-4ab7-9421-d9e21d65a98c.jpg", "description": "Journey through 7,000 years of Egyptian civilization in this beautifully designed museum near the airport. Pharaonic artifacts, mummies, Greco-Roman treasures, and Islamic-era masterpieces are displayed with modern technology and English explanations. It's the perfect introduction to Egyptian history or farewell experience before departing, showcasing culture beyond beaches."}, {"id": "a2c55066-2097-4824-bb6c-d922625676a6", "name": "1001 Arabian Nights Show", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/cc264c37-43be-4944-abf9-28d68bd2a5bc.jpg", "description": "Experience spectacular Arabian entertainment belly dancers, Tanoura performers, folklore shows, and acrobatic acts under starlit skies. This theatrical extravaganza combines traditional Egyptian culture with Las Vegas-style production. Enjoy traditional feast meals while watching magical performances that transport you into legendary tales of desert kingdoms."}, {"id": "7741e33e-4467-42f6-8bdd-0c3b6270c18c", "name": "Sand City", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/9af4ef78-2f2d-40de-8dec-874a194188a6.jpg", "description": "The world's largest sand sculpture park showcases over 40 intricate masterpieces carved from sand pharaohs, mythological scenes, famous landmarks, and fantasy creatures. These massive temporary artworks, created by international artists, demonstrate incredible detail. Evening illumination transforms sculptures into glowing artworks, making this unique attraction memorable for all ages."}, {"id": "a698aaa6-f134-445f-a8d7-96e387c25935", "name": "Senzo Mall", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/4995afed-d0fd-4642-8b3c-9049923a1ddc.webp", "description": " Hurghada's premier shopping and entertainment destination offers international brands, Egyptian souvenirs, restaurants, cinemas, and bowling alleys under air-conditioned comfort. This modern mall provides respite from beach activities, featuring everything from luxury goods to traditional handicrafts. The food court and family entertainment zones make it perfect for leisurely afternoons."}, {"id": "c1ff22e6-b054-4c02-b12a-ac1d7727c4cd", "name": "El Dahar Bazaar", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f55a8579-9d5a-4a59-8139-824345b51a8e.webp", "description": "Step into authentic Egyptian market atmosphere in Hurghada's oldest neighborhood. This traditional souq buzzes with spice aromas, colorful textiles, handcrafted jewelry, and aromatic perfumes. Haggle with friendly vendors, discover Egyptian street food, and experience local life beyond resort bubbles. It's Hurghada's cultural heart, chaotic and wonderful."}, {"id": "6ee23ba0-f57e-44a9-b665-aed868e39302", "name": "Makadi Water World", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/633bb3f4-7dd9-4004-a169-c0bdec64de24.jpg", "description": "Egypt's largest water park delivers family thrills massive slides, wave pools, lazy rivers, and children's splash zones spread across sprawling grounds. Adrenaline junkies conquer kamikaze slides while families relax in tropical-themed pools. All-day passes include beach access, making it the ultimate day of aquatic fun for all ages."}, {"id": "4891aadf-f840-4f26-84b9-5754aa47a01b", "name": "Sindbad Submarine", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/113abad6-6400-4c16-8471-28005b5f9c2f.jpg", "description": "Descend 25 meters beneath Red Sea waves in this tourist submarine for dry underwater exploration. Through panoramic windows, watch coral gardens, schools of colorful fish, and occasional rays glide past. Perfect for non-swimmers or those wanting underwater experience without getting wet, this unique journey reveals Red Sea magic."}, {"id": "3f131c91-0040-4aeb-9b07-5ebe7418130c", "name": "Dolphin House (Sha'ab El Erg)", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/fa68bb90-8719-4602-bc1c-eded0ae0a166.jpg", "description": " Snorkel alongside wild spinner dolphins at their natural reef habitat. These playful creatures often interact with swimmers, creating magical encounters in crystal-clear waters. The reef itself dazzles with vibrant corals and tropical fish. This protected marine area offers one of the Red Sea's most unforgettable wildlife experiences."}, {"id": "ee22e485-5e15-4ced-9d96-b161b233339f", "name": "Sharm El Naga Bay", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/a3d44b60-71fc-421c-9851-e61f637876a1.jpg", "description": "This pristine bay south of Hurghada remains beautifully undeveloped a crescent of golden sand meeting turquoise waters. The house reef explodes with marine life just meters from shore, making it perfect for beginner snorkelers. Quiet beaches, clear waters, and excellent visibility create the ideal escape from busier resort areas."}, {"id": "79ef6427-14b6-487b-ba16-94ddd55c2fd1", "name": "Utopia Island", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/58e8988a-eeea-4b37-872b-7406ab8fff38.jpg", "description": " A small desert island paradise featuring shallow turquoise lagoons perfect for swimming and snorkeling. Colorful coral gardens surround the island, while sandy beaches offer relaxation. The relaxed atmosphere, fresh seafood lunches, and easy snorkeling access make it popular for families and couples seeking tranquil island escapes without crowds."}, {"id": "41dd294f-a0f5-4520-857e-faaea5207696", "name": "Sahl Hasheesh Bay", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/c80e4d44-5828-4248-990a-80f8aff187e4.jpg", "description": "Hurghada's most upscale resort area boasts pristine beaches, luxury hotels, and turquoise bays protected by coral reefs. The 12-kilometer stretch of golden sand remains beautifully preserved, with strict development regulations maintaining natural beauty. World-class diving, championship golf courses, and exclusive marinas create sophisticated elegance for discerning travelers."}, {"id": "937c6d05-e63b-4b6a-b5dc-313456a029e9", "name": "Coptic Cathedral of Saint Shenouda", "image": "https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/fc861c58-ffe6-4ef2-9978-0e5f118d33e3.jpg", "description": "This stunning modern Coptic cathedral showcases beautiful religious architecture with soaring domes and intricate iconography. The peaceful sanctuary features colorful religious artwork and serves Hurghada's Christian community. Visitors can admire its exterior beauty and architectural significance, representing Egypt's diverse religious heritage beyond Islamic monuments."}]
\.
COPY public.faqs (id, question, answer, category, sort_order, is_visible, created_at, updated_at, created_by) FROM stdin;
18c80bd6-53ee-4774-9792-1a23963755e5	What's included in the package price?	All luxury accommodations, private Egyptologist guides, exclusive site access, gourmet dining, private transportation, domestic flights, VIP airport services, entrance fees, and 24/7 concierge support. International flights, visa fees, travel insurance, and gratuities are additional unless specified in custom packages.	Pricing & Payment	1	t	2026-01-22 13:50:37.792497	2026-01-22 13:50:37.792497	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2
da13dfa0-1ab0-43b1-a84c-5d74ec89f86e	What payment methods do you accept?	We accept international wire transfers, major credit cards (Visa, Mastercard, American Express), PayPal, and specialized luxury travel payment platforms. All transactions are secure and processed through encrypted channels. Multi-currency options available for international clients.	Pricing & Payment	2	t	2026-01-22 13:50:55.940744	2026-01-22 13:50:55.940744	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2
38b9d07b-3a03-436c-9016-08f2af1ad9a7	Are there any hidden fees?	Absolutely not. Our pricing is completely transparent with detailed breakdowns. The quoted price includes all specified services. Optional add-ons like helicopter tours, private yacht charters, or extended services are clearly itemized separately. No surprises—just exceptional experiences.	Pricing & Payment	3	t	2026-01-22 13:51:17.569344	2026-01-22 13:51:17.569344	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2
ab56b148-bed3-4a8f-ba52-445ea6774b36	Do you offer customized packages?	Yes, complete customization is our specialty. Every itinerary is tailored to your interests, pace, and preferences. Whether you want archaeological deep-dives, wellness retreats, adventure experiences, or romantic celebrations, our travel designers craft unique journeys that reflect your personal vision.\n	Pricing & Payment	4	t	2026-01-22 13:52:01.256996	2026-01-22 13:52:01.256996	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2
62d09286-3afb-4ff1-bbb0-a0da8dc8bd4c	Visa requirements for US citizens	US citizens need a tourist visa for Egypt, easily obtained as e-Visa online ($25) before travel or on arrival ($25 cash). Valid for 30 days. We provide detailed visa instructions and can arrange VIP visa assistance services for seamless airport processing.\n	Travel Logistics	11	t	2026-01-22 13:53:17.711701	2026-01-22 13:53:17.711701	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2
3c6675f5-7f56-4486-8c42-fbfed94367d5	Best time to visit Egypt	October through April offers perfect weather (65-80°F) for sightseeing. November-February is peak luxury season with comfortable temperatures. March-April brings spring blooms. May-September is hotter but offers fewer crowds and exclusive access. We'll recommend timing based on your preferences.\n	Travel Logistics	12	t	2026-01-22 13:53:36.940236	2026-01-22 13:53:36.940236	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2
b92e001f-520b-4699-9265-6a3a596ce7f4	Is Egypt safe for American tourists?	Yes, Egypt is very safe for American tourists. The government prioritizes tourist security with dedicated tourism police at all major sites. Luxury Egypt provides additional VIP security protocols and 24/7 monitoring for complete peace of mind throughout your journey.	Safety & Security	1	t	2026-01-22 13:45:35.301966	2026-01-22 12:47:38.314	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2
adc6a79b-7cd3-4625-aebe-fa2e1008d48b	What security measures are in place?	We provide pre-screened private drivers, GPS-tracked luxury vehicles, 24/7 operations monitoring, VIP fast-track airport services, and coordination with tourism police. High-profile clients receive discrete executive protection. All partners meet international security standards with emergency medical evacuation capabilities.	Safety & Security	2	t	2026-01-22 13:48:01.966865	2026-01-22 13:48:01.966865	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2
cea5b926-8429-4c67-bc48-9813d8e014f3	Are there any areas to avoid?	Our luxury itineraries focus exclusively on premier destinations: Cairo, Luxor, Aswan, Alexandria, and Red Sea resorts. These areas have excellent security infrastructure. We avoid any regions with travel advisories, ensuring you experience only Egypt's safest and most spectacular locations.	Safety & Security	3	t	2026-01-22 13:48:21.760783	2026-01-22 13:48:21.760783	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2
289d226b-629a-4d62-8a6e-6cf2858a1404	How do I book a luxury tour?	Contact us via phone, email, or our website. We'll schedule a consultation to understand your preferences, then our travel designers create a bespoke itinerary. After your approval and deposit, we handle everything—from permits to reservations—ensuring a seamless experience.	Booking & Reservations	1	t	2026-01-22 13:49:00.73153	2026-01-22 13:49:00.73153	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2
564dc6bc-61eb-4650-892e-022a27a27914	What's your cancellation/refund policy?	We offer flexible cancellation terms based on your departure date. Cancellations 90+ days prior receive full refunds minus deposit. 60-89 days: 50% refund. Under 60 days: case-by-case review. We recommend comprehensive travel insurance for maximum protection and flexibility.	Booking & Reservations	2	t	2026-01-22 13:49:25.777123	2026-01-22 13:49:25.777123	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2
352020b4-e282-465d-bead-f76742acdc10	How far in advance should I book?	We recommend booking 6-12 months in advance for peak season (October-April) to secure ultra-luxury properties and exclusive experiences. Last-minute bookings (30-60 days) are possible but may have limited availability for premier suites and private archaeological access.	Booking & Reservations	3	t	2026-01-22 13:49:43.558277	2026-01-22 13:49:43.558277	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2
7a297c05-5bd5-4e96-be6b-3b2a234cb8b5	What deposit is required?	A 30% deposit secures your booking and reserves all services. The remaining 70% balance is due 60 days before departure. We accept wire transfers, major credit cards, and international payment platforms for your convenience and security.	Booking & Reservations	4	t	2026-01-22 13:50:00.351013	2026-01-22 13:50:00.351013	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2
6bee3a25-af45-404c-91ac-8dcc224a500a	Flight arrangements - do you handle them?	We can arrange international flights through our luxury travel partners or you can book independently. We handle all domestic flights within Egypt (Cairo-Luxor-Aswan) in business class. Our VIP meet-and-greet services ensure seamless connections regardless of your arrival arrangements.\n	Travel Logistics	13	t	2026-01-22 13:54:01.01884	2026-01-22 13:54:01.01884	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2
840699e8-d45c-4805-accd-51b38a3d758b	Airport transfers and private transportation	All ground transportation is private, luxury, and climate-controlled. You'll have dedicated professional drivers and premium vehicles (Mercedes, Cadillac, or similar). VIP airport fast-track services include meet-and-greet, expedited immigration, and porter services. Helicopters and private jets available upon request.\n	Travel Logistics	14	t	2026-01-22 13:54:11.847724	2026-01-22 13:54:11.847724	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2
cf826217-4c30-4934-a3e9-0d0ec0b9a10c	What level of luxury hotels do you use? (5-star names)	We partner with Egypt's finest: Four Seasons Cairo & Sharm El Sheikh, Marriott Mena House, Sofitel Legend Old Cataract Aswan, Hilton Luxor, and ultra-luxury Nile cruises like Sanctuary Sun Boat IV. All properties are internationally acclaimed five-star establishments.\n	Accommodations	15	t	2026-01-22 13:56:06.417893	2026-01-22 13:56:06.417893	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2
7521a023-c464-40a7-892c-2d81e8de597b	Room categories and upgrades	Standard bookings include deluxe rooms or suites. We offer complimentary upgrades when available and can arrange premium suites, royal suites, or private villas. Nile-view rooms, pyramid-view suites, and exclusive accommodations are prioritized for our guests.\n	Accommodations	16	t	2026-01-22 13:56:30.813667	2026-01-22 13:56:30.813667	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2
e629ead5-2c21-4844-bc98-3b31a445ff5a	Special requests (dietary, accessibility, celebrations)	We accommodate all special requests: kosher, vegan, gluten-free, allergy-sensitive menus, accessibility needs, wheelchair access, celebration arrangements (anniversaries, proposals, birthdays), spa treatments, and religious observances. Just inform us during planning—we handle everything discreetly and professionally.	Accommodations	17	t	2026-01-22 13:56:41.523088	2026-01-22 13:56:41.523088	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2
1010d21d-d9b9-408a-b20d-ae6af5c87169	Can I customize my itinerary?	Absolutely. Every Luxury Egypt journey is fully customizable. Choose your destinations, pace, activities, and experiences. Want private Pyramids access at sunrise? Felucca sunset cruises? Hot air ballooning? Cooking classes? We design itineraries around your dreams, not templates.\n	Experiences & Customization	18	t	2026-01-22 13:57:46.523354	2026-01-22 13:57:46.523354	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2
37b47f66-5919-40df-8099-1cbbe7cf815e	Private vs. group tours	All our experiences are exclusively private—never group tours. You'll have dedicated Egyptologist guides, private vehicles, and personalized attention throughout. This ensures flexibility, privacy, and VIP treatment at every location. Your journey moves at your pace.\n	Experiences & Customization	19	t	2026-01-22 13:58:16.229185	2026-01-22 13:58:16.229185	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2
f83f029d-639f-4c15-a69f-6a6fa0c8b086	Exclusive experiences available	Private after-hours Pyramids access, exclusive tomb visits, sunrise hot air ballooning over Luxor, private felucca sailings, Bedouin desert camps, private museum tours, cooking classes with celebrity chefs, spa experiences, and VIP access to archaeological excavations (subject to availability).\n	Experiences & Customization	20	t	2026-01-22 13:58:35.422498	2026-01-22 13:58:35.422498	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2
2a5c9d60-7563-41e4-951a-e520ee515e87	Photography opportunities	Egypt is a photographer's paradise. We arrange optimal timing for iconic shots, provide photography permits, and can arrange professional photographers or videographers to capture your journey. Sunrise/sunset positioning at temples, drone photography (where permitted), and Instagram-worthy moments are built into itineraries.	Experiences & Customization	21	t	2026-01-22 13:59:12.30254	2026-01-22 13:59:12.30254	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2
c5c458e1-6fa0-4df9-ba81-d6279dcdb279	Vaccination requirements	No mandatory vaccinations for Egypt travel from the US. However, CDC recommends routine vaccines (MMR, Tdap) and suggests Hepatitis A and Typhoid for travelers. Consult your physician 4-6 weeks before departure. We provide detailed health preparation guidelines with booking confirmations.\n	Health & Comfort	22	t	2026-01-22 14:00:25.98062	2026-01-22 14:00:25.98062	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2
ef1b5d58-d205-4f85-b643-af8d42d0dbd8	Travel insurance recommendations	We strongly recommend comprehensive travel insurance covering trip cancellation, medical emergencies, evacuation, and lost luggage. We partner with luxury travel insurance providers and can recommend policies. Medical evacuation coverage is particularly important for international travel.\n	Health & Comfort	23	t	2026-01-22 14:00:51.858653	2026-01-22 14:00:51.858653	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2
db3a25c5-7e50-4898-92fb-785e23347d38	Medical facilities available	Egypt's major cities have excellent private hospitals with internationally trained doctors. We maintain relationships with premium medical facilities and English-speaking physicians. Our 24/7 support includes medical coordination. Private air ambulance evacuation services available if needed.\n	Health & Comfort	24	t	2026-01-22 14:01:10.891656	2026-01-22 14:01:10.891656	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2
643ecf42-9c15-46b0-962c-c7e8aff29df0	Dietary accommodations	All dietary needs are fully accommodated: vegetarian, vegan, kosher, halal, gluten-free, allergies, or medical restrictions. Our partner hotels and restaurants provide gourmet cuisine tailored to your requirements. Inform us during planning, and every meal will meet your specifications.	Health & Comfort	25	t	2026-01-22 14:01:22.694062	2026-01-22 14:01:22.694062	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2
0c0a41c2-fc02-4b6e-b94b-2d6a4f3d485a	Languages spoken by guides	All our Egyptologist guides are fluent in English with university degrees in Egyptology or archaeology. Many also speak French, Spanish, German, or Italian. They're not just linguists—they're engaging storytellers who bring ancient Egypt alive with expertise and passion.\n	Communication & Support	26	t	2026-01-22 14:02:18.554508	2026-01-22 14:02:18.554508	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2
3a517349-5a55-4ca5-850d-1f7c4e52e1ae	24/7 support availability	Yes, absolutely. You'll have 24/7 access to our operations team throughout your journey via WhatsApp, phone, or email. Your dedicated travel concierge monitors your itinerary in real-time and can handle any request, change, or emergency instantly.\n	Communication & Support	27	t	2026-01-22 14:02:38.000211	2026-01-22 14:02:38.000211	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2
b90ef055-93ce-4d30-a582-598e69518907	How to contact you during the trip	Before departure, you'll receive emergency contact numbers, WhatsApp support line, and your dedicated concierge's direct number. Our operations center tracks your journey in real-time. Your guide also has direct communication with our team for seamless coordination.	Communication & Support	28	t	2026-01-22 14:02:48.479761	2026-01-22 14:02:48.479761	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2
49afec47-1586-4568-bccb-595b84883881	Dress code recommendations	Egypt is respectful and moderate. Lightweight, modest clothing is ideal: loose pants/skirts covering knees, shoulders covered at religious sites. Bring comfortable walking shoes, sun protection, and layers for air-conditioned interiors. Luxury hotels and restaurants have no restrictions; smart casual is perfect.\n	Cultural Information	29	t	2026-01-22 14:03:18.015066	2026-01-22 14:03:18.015066	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2
cd21e8b3-fa1c-4713-a98d-6a5217c03789	Tipping etiquette	Tipping (baksheesh) is customary in Egypt. We provide detailed tipping guidelines with your travel documents. Generally: guides $50-75/day, drivers $25-35/day, hotel staff $5-10, restaurant 10-15%. We can arrange tip envelopes or include gratuities in packages for convenience.\n	Cultural Information	30	t	2026-01-22 14:03:40.668223	2026-01-22 14:03:40.668223	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2
b798f012-6c6d-4f8d-b1d7-7ebde8515d83	Cultural customs to know	Egyptians are warm and hospitable. Greet with handshakes, remove shoes when entering mosques, ask permission before photographing people, dress modestly at religious sites, and use your right hand for eating/greeting. Public displays of affection are minimal. Friday is the holy day.	Cultural Information	31	t	2026-01-22 14:03:51.620019	2026-01-22 14:03:51.620019	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2
\.
