COPY public.tours (id, title, slug, description, short_description, hero_image, gallery, duration, group_size, difficulty, price, currency, includes, excludes, itinerary, destinations, category, featured, published, created_at, updated_at, created_by, brochure_url) FROM stdin;
ceb41dec-b067-4a65-a840-c7eaf29e6888	Luxor Day Tour to Karnak and Luxor Temples	luxor-karnak-temples-day-tour	Immerse yourself in ancient Egyptian spirituality on this exclusive Luxor day tour to Karnak and Luxor temples. Explore the colossal Karnak Temple complex and the elegant Luxor Temple connected by the Avenue of Sphinxes. This Karnak and Luxor temples tour showcases monumental columns, sacred sanctuaries, and the religious heart of New Kingdom Egypt with expert interpretation.	Explore the magnificent Karnak and Luxor temples on a comprehensive day tour. Discover ancient Egyptian religious architecture with expert guides and witness the spiritual heart of New Kingdom Egypt.	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f38292b8-10d9-4191-8a52-1bc5cbaba932.jpg	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f38292b8-10d9-4191-8a52-1bc5cbaba932.jpg}	4 HOURS	2 - 12 people	Easy	0	USD	{"Air-conditioned vehicle "," Professional Egyptologist guide "," Hotel pickup and drop-off in Luxor "," Entrance fees to Karnak and Luxor temples "," Bottled water "," All taxes and service charges"}	{"Personal expenses "," Gratuities (optional) "}	[{"day": 1, "title": "Day 1 | Karnak & Luxor Temples - Sacred Sanctuaries of Ancient Thebes", "activities": ["Karnak & Luxor Temples - Sacred Sanctuaries of Ancient Thebes"], "description": "Your temple exploration begins with morning pickup from your Luxor hotel. Start at the magnificent Karnak Temple complex, the largest religious building ever constructed, covering over 100 hectares. Enter through the Avenue of Ram-Headed Sphinxes and explore the Great Hypostyle Hall, featuring 134 massive columns reaching 23 meters high, covered with intricate hieroglyphics and colorful reliefs. Wander through numerous chapels, sanctuaries, and courts built by successive pharaohs over 2,000 years, dedicated to the Theban triad of Amun, Mut, and Khonsu. Visit the Sacred Lake where priests performed purification rituals, admire towering obelisks including Queen Hatshepsut's perfectly preserved obelisk, and explore the Festival Hall of Thutmose III. Continue to Luxor Temple, a beautifully preserved sanctuary built primarily by Amenhotep III and Ramses II. Walk the Avenue of Sphinxes connecting both temples. Explore the temple's massive first pylon, Abu Haggag Mosque built atop the ancient structure, colonnade, courts, and inner sanctuaries. Return to your hotel with comprehensive understanding of Luxor's greatest temples."}]	{"Luxor "," Karnak Temple "," Luxor Temple"}	LUXOR	f	t	2026-02-13 23:05:58.244999	2026-02-14 00:51:32.107	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	\N
2d82217d-62a8-4b50-b397-80824042a7d2	3 Days Trip To Cairo From Luxor By Plane	three-days-cairo-trip-luxor-plane	Experience Cairo's treasures in depth on this extensive 3 days trip to Cairo from Luxor by plane. Explore the Pyramids, Egyptian Museum, Saqqara, Memphis, Islamic monuments, and Coptic sites across three enriching days. This comprehensive Cairo tour provides thorough exploration, comfortable accommodations, expert guidance, and immersive encounters with Egypt's ancient, Islamic, and Coptic heritage.	Immerse yourself in Cairo's wonders on a comprehensive 3-day tour from Luxor. Explore pyramids, museums, Islamic sites, and more with expert guides.\n	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f38292b8-10d9-4191-8a52-1bc5cbaba932.jpg	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f38292b8-10d9-4191-8a52-1bc5cbaba932.jpg}	3 Days/ 2 Night 	2 - 12 people	Moderate	0	USD	{"Air-conditioned vehicles "," Professional Egyptologist guides "," Hotel pickup and drop-off in Luxor "," Domestic flights (Luxor-Cairo-Luxor) "," 2 nights accommodation in Cairo (4-star hotel) "," Meals: 2 breakfasts, 3 lunches, 2 dinners "," Entrance fees to all mentioned sites "," Bottled water "," All taxes and service charges"}	{"Personal expenses "," Gratuities (optional) "," Drinks during meals"}	[{"day": 1, "title": "Day 1 | Cairo - Pyramids of Giza, Sphinx, Saqqara & Memphis", "activities": ["Cairo - Pyramids of Giza, Sphinx, Saqqara & Memphis"], "description": "Your Cairo adventure begins with early morning transfer to Luxor Airport for your flight to Cairo. Upon arrival, meet your Egyptologist guide and drive to the Giza Plateau. Explore the Great Pyramid of Khufu, the last surviving ancient wonder standing 146 meters high, alongside the pyramids of Khafre and Menkaure. Learn about construction theories, burial chambers, astronomical significance, and the pyramids' role in pharaonic afterlife beliefs. Visit the Great Sphinx and Valley Temple, understanding ancient mummification processes and funeral rituals. Enjoy lunch with pyramid views before continuing to Saqqara, Egypt's largest archaeological site covering 7 kilometers. Explore the Step Pyramid of Djoser, the world's oldest stone structure and first pyramid, designed by the legendary architect Imhotep. Enter nearby mastaba tombs featuring beautifully preserved colorful reliefs depicting daily life scenes from 4,500 years ago. Visit Memphis, ancient Egypt's first capital for over 3,000 years, viewing the colossal lying statue of Ramses II carved from limestone and the alabaster sphinx. Check into your Cairo hotel for overnight stay, enjoying dinner and rest before tomorrow's explorations."}, {"day": 2, "title": "Day 2 | Cairo - Egyptian Museum, Citadel, Mohamed Ali Mosque & Khan El Khalili", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, depart for the Egyptian Museum in Tahrir Square, home to over 120,000 artifacts spanning Egypt's pharaonic history from prehistoric times through the Greco-Roman period. Spend extensive time exploring King Tutankhamun's complete golden treasures, including his iconic death mask weighing 11 kilograms of solid gold, golden throne, jewelry, chariots, and personal items. Visit the Royal Mummy Room to see preserved pharaohs including Ramses II, Seti I, and Hatshepsut. Your guide will highlight significant artifacts while explaining their historical context and significance. Enjoy lunch at a local restaurant before visiting the Citadel of Salah El Din, a medieval fortress offering panoramic Cairo views across the sprawling city. Explore the magnificent Mohamed Ali Mosque with its Ottoman-style architecture, alabaster walls, stunning domes, and elegant minarets. Continue to the Khan El Khalili bazaar, Cairo's historic marketplace dating to the 14th century. Wander through narrow alleyways filled with shops selling spices, perfumes, jewelry, textiles, copperware, and souvenirs. Experience authentic Egyptian market culture and enjoy traditional mint tea at the historic El Fishawi café. Return to your hotel for dinner and overnight stay."}, {"day": 3, "title": "Day 3 | Cairo - Coptic Cairo, Old Cairo & Optional Activities", "activities": ["Cairo - Egyptian Museum, Citadel, Mohamed Ali Mosque & Khan El Khalili"], "description": "After breakfast and hotel checkout, explore Coptic Cairo, the city's historic Christian quarter with churches dating back to the early Christian era. Visit the Hanging Church (Al-Mu'allaqa), suspended over the ancient Roman fortress of Babylon, featuring beautiful icons, woodwork, and a unique location. Explore the Church of St. Sergius, built over the crypt where the Holy Family reportedly sheltered during their flight to Egypt. Visit the Ben Ezra Synagogue, one of Egypt's oldest Jewish temples with connections to Moses and the Prophet Jeremiah. Continue to the Coptic Museum, housing the world's largest collection of Coptic Christian artifacts including textiles, manuscripts, and religious icons. Enjoy lunch at a local restaurant before choosing optional afternoon activities: visit the Cairo Tower for 360-degree panoramic city views, explore the Al-Azhar Mosque and Park showcasing Islamic architecture and gardens, or enjoy shopping at City Stars Mall. Alternatively, take a relaxing Nile felucca ride or visit additional Islamic monuments. Transfer to Cairo Airport for your evening flight to Luxor. Upon arrival, transfer to your hotel, concluding your comprehensive three-day Cairo immersion."}]	{"Luxor "," Cairo "," Giza "," Saqqara "," Memphis "," Egyptian Museum"}	LUXOR	f	t	2026-02-13 23:05:58.297701	2026-02-14 00:24:19.34	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	\N
df3041dd-48c3-42f2-98d9-7dd78460b39c	Private Hot Air Balloon Over Aswan at Sunrise	private-abu-simbel-day-trip-aswan 	Experience the ultimate adventure with this private hot air balloon over Aswan at sunrise, offering exclusive aerial perspectives of the Nile Valley. Watch the sun illuminate ancient monuments, Nubian villages, and desert landscapes from your private basket. This hot air balloon ride provides unparalleled photography opportunities, champagne celebration, and magical memories floating above Aswan's beauty.	Soar over Aswan in a private hot air balloon at sunrise. Experience breathtaking aerial views of the Nile, temples, and desert landscapes.	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/4ffb90ed-abfe-4cb3-a5e7-95922105273c.avif	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/78c9b26e-3028-48e7-88e5-12fd8517466f.jpg}	2-3 hours	1-6 people	Easy	0	USD	{"Private hot air balloon flight (exclusive basket) "," Professional pilot and ground crew "," Hotel pickup and drop-off in Aswan "," Pre-flight light refreshments "," Champagne celebration after landing "," Flight certificate "," All safety equipment "," Insurance "," All taxes and service charges"}	{"International airfare "," Personal expenses "," Gratuities (optional) "," Any extras not mentioned"}	[{"day": 1, "title": "Day 1 | Aswan - Private Sunrise Hot Air Balloon Flight & Aerial Exploration", "activities": ["Aswan - Private Sunrise Hot Air Balloon Flight & Aerial Exploration"], "description": "Your extraordinary morning begins with pre-dawn pickup from your Aswan hotel around 4:30 AM. Transfer to the launch site on the West Bank where your private hot air balloon awaits. Meet your experienced pilot and ground crew while enjoying light refreshments. Watch the balloon inflation process as the sky begins to lighten. Board your private basket exclusively for your group, then gently lift off as the sun rises over the Nile Valley. Ascend to heights of 1,000-1,500 feet, enjoying breathtaking 360-degree panoramic views. Soar peacefully above the Nile River, watching feluccas and boats appear miniature below. Drift over ancient temples, the Aga Khan Mausoleum, Elephantine Island, and colorful Nubian villages with their distinctive painted houses. Witness the desert landscape meeting the fertile Nile valley in stunning contrast. Capture spectacular sunrise photographs as golden light illuminates the monuments and mountains. After approximately 45-60 minutes of magical flight, gently descend for a smooth landing. Celebrate with a champagne toast and receive your flight certificate before returning to your hotel for breakfast."}]	{Aswan}	ASWAN	f	t	2026-02-14 00:38:45.922858	2026-02-21 15:00:47.568	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	\N
11436d8c-3e40-4ddc-98cb-039f3a2ed844	7-Day VIP Egypt Tour | Private Pyramid Access & Nile Cruise	7-day-vip-egypt-pyramids-nile-cruise	Experience VIP Egypt in 10 days with exclusive access and premium service throughout. Limited to 8-12 guests, enjoy private pyramid chamber access before public opening hours explore the Great Pyramid's interior without crowds. Your VIP treatment includes skip-the-line entry at all major sites and stays at Cairo's legendary Marriott Mena House with stunning pyramid views. Board your deluxe Nile cruise vessel featuring premium suites with private balconies and butler service. Enjoy gourmet dining and spa treatments as you sail from Luxor to Aswan with priority excursions at Valley of the Kings, Karnak Temple, and all stops. Visit Abu Simbel's colossal temples and enjoy private felucca sailing. Includes five-star hotels, luxury cruise, all meals, expert Egyptologist guide, and internal flights.	10 DAYS / 9 NIGHTS\nExclusive VIP Egypt experience with private pyramid chamber access before opening, luxury Nile cruise with butler service, and skip-the-line privileges at all sites. Small groups 8-12. Five-star hotels including Marriott Mena House.	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/5bca76ca-51cc-4132-96fe-42bb1e11fd94.jpg	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f0a79553-1b3d-41a5-9873-348de97952ed.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/4d2a5013-0c58-48ad-88da-9fbcf4d8c1f2.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/cbdea3d1-d90d-48f2-8950-962e0d0f05c2.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/e72d9f89-29cd-49f0-9e0e-0769a380afcd.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/158985bb-c51a-4244-9b3a-2fce434048ed.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/865b2af8-bb35-40a5-a378-0ecaf7c06f28.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/be1bb2e1-4ac3-4f9e-8d28-9b638960fdde.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/68c2ab21-4331-43a6-b9ee-1ff4e38d3ef7.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/fd5c8dc1-c0b9-43ec-a2b7-f8d3b5a1420a.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/fdf33ca9-5c06-4bae-846f-d100adc9c87d.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/09aae57e-14c1-4fd4-acc3-4c7a82bcf877.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/866376ce-ddf7-4bc3-9f1c-e839d5172b36.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/4ebae6a2-08fc-4bd8-adaf-c9b23db085c0.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/daf3363d-6ca5-4635-9bc4-600f6c41f239.jpg}	 7 Days / 6 Nights	4 - 8	Easy	0	USD	{}	{}	[{"day": 1, "title": "Day 1 | Cairo - VIP Arrival & Welcome", "activities": [], "description": "Your private concierge welcomes you airside at Cairo International Airport, bypassing queues entirely before a comfortable Toyota Hiace transfer escorts you to the legendary Marriott Mena House. Settle into your Pyramid View Room with floor-to-ceiling windows framing Khufu's eternal monument.\\n\\nSavor a candlelit welcome dinner beneath starlit pyramids glowing golden across jasmine-scented gardens. Meet your small group of eight to twelve fellow travelers and expert Egyptologist guide who will provide personalized attention throughout this VIP journey combining exclusive access with intimate group camaraderie.\\n\\nOvernight: Marriott Mena House, Cairo\\n\\nMeals: Welcome dinner included"}, {"day": 2, "title": "Day 2 | Grand Egyptian Museum & Private Giza", "activities": [], "description": "Following breakfast with pyramid vistas, your private Egyptologist guides you through the Grand Egyptian Museum's treasures including Tutankhamun's complete golden collection spanning 5,000 artifacts displayed together for the first time. After exploring the Giza Plateau's Valley Temple and ancient stone quarries.\\n\\nExperience exclusive after-hours access standing between the Sphinx's paws before entering the Great Pyramid's King's Chamber in complete solitude where Queen Khufu's sarcophagus rests eternally. This rare privilege reserved for dignitaries and VIP guests ensures an unforgettable pyramid experience in profound silence.\\n\\nOvernight: Marriott Mena House, Cairo\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 3, "title": "Day 3 | Abu Simbel & Board Nile Cruise", "activities": [], "description": "Board your pre-dawn flight over Lake Nasser to witness Ramses II's four colossal statues guarding Abu Simbel's Great Temple and Queen Nefertari's adjacent sanctuary illuminated by sunrise's first golden rays. Stand before four twenty-meter monuments carved entirely into solid mountainside.\\n\\nContinue to Aswan where you embark MS Le Fayan, your boutique floating palace with only fifty suites. After settling into your Luxury Suite with private balcony and marble bathroom, motorboat carries you to Philae's island temple before evening champagne toasts during the Captain's Reception.\\n\\nOvernight: MS Le Fayan Nile Cruise\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 4, "title": "Day 4 | Kom Ombo & Edfu Temples", "activities": [], "description": "Awaken aboard your floating palace gliding peacefully toward Kom Ombo as breakfast arrives on your private balcony overlooking timeless Nile life. Explore Egypt's unique twin sanctuary dedicated to both Horus and Sobek gods featuring perfect architectural symmetry.\\n\\nAfternoon serenity with sun deck swimming or spa indulgence before visiting Edfu's magnificently preserved temple with towering entrance pylons. Late afternoon brings an Egyptian gala dinner under desert stars with traditional entertainment celebrating your VIP journey through ancient wonders.\\n\\nOvernight: MS Le Fayan Nile Cruise\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 5, "title": "Day 5 | Valley of the Kings & West Bank", "activities": [], "description": "Cross the Nile by private motorboat to Luxor's legendary West Bank, entering the Valley of the Kings where Tutankhamun's mummy rests eternally in his golden sarcophagus surrounded by spectacularly decorated royal tombs with vivid astronomical ceilings depicting the pharaoh's journey to the afterlife.\\n\\nContinue to Queen Hatshepsut's breathtaking three-tiered mortuary temple carved into limestone cliffs, then return shipboard for spa relaxation before evening belly dancing and vibrant Luxor Market exploration bringing you closer to modern Egyptian culture.\\n\\nOvernight: MS Le Fayan Nile Cruise\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 6, "title": "Day 6 | Karnak Temple & Return to Cairo", "activities": [], "description": "Disembark for your final Luxor morning at monumental Karnak Temple Complex, the world's largest ancient religious site spanning two hundred acres. Walk the Avenue of Sphinxes and stand awestruck beneath the Great Hypostyle Hall's one hundred thirty-four towering papyrus columns creating an awe-inspiring stone forest.\\n\\nVisit Luxor Temple bathed in morning light before your domestic flight returns you to Cairo's Four Seasons First Residence with spectacular high-rise Nile views. Evening features farewell dinner with panoramic cityscape views celebrating your extraordinary VIP journey.\\n\\nOvernight: Four Seasons Hotel Cairo\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and farewell dinner included"}, {"day": 7, "title": "Day 7 | Cairo - Departure", "activities": [], "description": "After leisurely breakfast overlooking the Nile's shimmering expanse, enjoy final hours strolling the Corniche promenade, relaxing poolside with panoramic city views, or reflecting on your extraordinary journey through five millennia of civilization and royal treatment.\\n\\nYour private chauffeur provides seamless transfer to Cairo International Airport where you depart carrying golden memories of the Nile, whispers of pharaohs, and the promise of return to Egypt's timeless wonders that have captured hearts for thousands of years.\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast included"}]	{Cairo,Giza,Aswan,Luxor}	Small Group Journeys 	t	t	2026-01-22 17:34:37.160831	2026-03-05 19:44:52.631	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/44510eac-a854-49ec-aeb3-5fe008cbbaaa.pdf
611cd689-acaf-4070-ae2d-778ea3fede88	Private Spiritual Tours Egypt | 14-Day Sacred Journey	private-spiritual-tours-egypt-14-days-sacred-journey	Embark on extraordinary private spiritual tours Egypt designed for profound connection with ancient energies and ancestral wisdom. This 14-day ultra-luxury journey blends sacred temple meditations, sunrise rituals at mystical sites, and transformative storytelling across Luxor's tombs, Abydos mysteries, and Siwa's desert tranquility. Experience spiritual awakening with private Egyptologist guidance, Nile cruising, and exclusive 5-star accommodations creating transformative memories throughout Egypt's most sacred destinations.\n	 Transformative private spiritual tours Egypt with temple meditations, ancestral rituals, and luxury accommodations. 14 days exploring Luxor, Abydos, Siwa.\n	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/6c38620e-eb5a-4df8-ae4a-d07d6590366d.avif	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/42db60b9-cf68-4037-9629-0e7fa17a6adc.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/9d92e9b4-f1d7-4aa0-9bf3-d830a6774d91.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/103521a6-8063-4a73-81aa-196a8a027b33.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/907a0f24-30fe-4759-ba86-7725ed41a9cd.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/1f0a09cb-011f-4e86-9564-84f3ba8f99f1.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/917f0764-ed15-44e1-918a-232610b77f8d.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/9160a75f-4a32-4d79-b83d-de69e638ba96.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/8d1636b6-23b8-4aa3-864b-1a21af9ccc47.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/9340605c-ee02-4b49-aac7-ed572493c9b7.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/1819c312-e87f-4b1c-94f5-36f1a2bfe79c.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b8441a83-08c8-46d7-b981-cb908fb4b391.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/04081617-e64e-4de9-b489-23baa17bd551.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f916f5d3-3a6f-4b5b-bcea-bdb7e8d374cd.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/e9814d19-f533-449c-8abd-59aa5fc37015.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/34a48f3a-b423-47b1-8dcd-a10e50e33b9f.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/5bbe4a8f-e6b5-4fdc-9d32-fc73f1a2d38d.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/64cef260-a43a-4b16-8fcb-fedfe8632ee7.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/8401b469-078b-4ded-9558-1f44e054513f.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/4c4464a3-7856-45e7-aa23-15c4a4b5d656.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b92f60ff-c34f-4096-af49-a0ec74239722.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/25a3caf2-aa12-40ca-bded-518b340418fc.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b5035386-d226-47d2-8203-446d269ca082.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/7d292ecd-d20a-4dc4-bf5b-f14a3741abe0.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/de456ddb-9471-43d3-949f-13553f938c00.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/11278d21-0239-4278-a3be-4d4d12ef8e12.jpg}	14 Days / 13 Nights	2 - 8 	Moderate	0	USD	{"Meet-and-assist service by our representatives at airports","All transfers by private air-conditioned vehicles","2 nights accommodation at Sofitel Winter Palace Luxor","5 nights accommodation on a luxury Nile cruise","2 nights accommodation at The Oberoi Sahl Hasheesh","1 night accommodation at Desert Camp","1 night accommodation at Siwa Eco-Lodge","Domestic flights: Luxor to Aswan, Abu Simbel excursion, Hurghada to Siwa, Siwa to Cairo","All entry fees to temples, tombs, and monuments mentioned in the itinerary","Services of an Egyptologist guide on a private tour throughout your trip","All meals stated in the itinerary – (B) for breakfast, (L) for lunch, (D) for dinner","Private motorboat transfers at temples","Private yacht excursion with snorkeling in the Red Sea","Traditional felucca sailboat rides","4x4 desert safari","Cultural workshops and village visits","Bottled water during all tours and meals","24/7 on-call support","All applicable taxes and VAT"}	{"International flights to and from Cairo","Gratuities for guides, drivers, cruise staff, and lodge staff","Alcoholic beverages","Travel insurance"}	[{"day": 1, "title": "Day 1 | Luxor – Gateway to Ancient Mysteries", "activities": [], "description": "Arrive at Luxor Airport. Our meet-and-assist service will take you through the passport control area, assist with your luggage and customs, and transport you to your hotel overlooking the Nile. Evening welcome dinner at the hotel.\\nOvernight: Sofitel Winter Palace Luxor (D)"}, {"day": 2, "title": "Day 2 | Luxor East Bank – Sunrise Meditation", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, visit Karnak Temple, the largest religious complex ever built. Your Egyptologist guide will explain the symbolism and hieroglyphics carved on the temple walls. Continue to Luxor Temple to explore the Avenue of Sphinxes and the divine birth reliefs. Evening felucca sailboat ride on the Nile at sunset.\\nOvernight: Sofitel Winter Palace Luxor (B, L, D)"}, {"day": 3, "title": "Day 3 | West Bank – Valley of Kings & Ancestral Rituals", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, cross the Nile by motorboat to the West Bank. Visit the Valley of the Kings and enter the tomb of King Tutankhamun. Explore other royal tombs known for their detailed astronomical ceilings. Continue to the Temple of Hatshepsut, carved into the cliffs. Afternoon check-in to your Nile cruise vessel and begin sailing.\\nOvernight: Nile Cruise (B, L, D)"}, {"day": 4, "title": "Day 4 | Edfu & Kom Ombo – Dual Temples Meditation", "activities": [], "description": "Breakfast onboard as the cruise continues to Edfu. Visit the Temple of Horus, one of the best-preserved temples in Egypt. Continue sailing to Kom Ombo to visit the unique dual temple dedicated to Horus and Sobek. Return to the cruise for dinner.\\nOvernight: Nile Cruise (B, L, D)"}, {"day": 5, "title": "Day 5 | Aswan – Philae Temple & Divine Feminine", "activities": [], "description": "Arrive in Aswan after breakfast. Take a motorboat to the island of Philae to visit the Temple of Isis. After lunch, visit a Nubian village to experience local culture, music, and crafts. Evening felucca sailboat ride on the Nile.\\nOvernight: Nile Cruise (B, L, D)"}, {"day": 6, "title": "Day 6 | Abu Simbel – Sunrise Ritual Ceremony", "activities": [], "description": "Early morning flight to Abu Simbel to visit the temples of Ramses II and Nefertari, carved into the mountainside. Witness the sunrise illuminating the temple facade. Explore the interior chambers and reliefs before returning to Aswan.\\nOvernight: Nile Cruise (B, L, D)"}, {"day": 7, "title": "Day 7 | Saqqara – Step Pyramid Initiation", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, disembark and transfer to Saqqara to visit the Step Pyramid of Djoser, the oldest stone pyramid in Egypt dating to 2650 BCE. Your guide will explain the history and significance of this ancient monument. Afternoon free for reflection before returning to the cruise.\\nOvernight: Nile Cruise (B, L, D)"}, {"day": 8, "title": "Day 8 | Abydos – Osirian Sacred Chambers", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, drive to Abydos, one of Egypt's most ancient religious sites. Visit the Temple of Seti I, known for its detailed carvings including the King List and the Flower of Life symbols. Your guide will explain the Osirian rituals performed in these chambers. Return to the cruise for dinner.\\nOvernight: Nile Cruise (B, L, D)"}, {"day": 9, "title": "Day 9 | Dendera Temple – Cosmic Alignment", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, visit the Temple of Hathor at Dendera, known for its well-preserved astronomical ceiling depicting the zodiac and celestial deities. Your guide will explain the sacred geometry and solar alignments of the temple. Afternoon at leisure onboard the cruise.\\nOvernight: Nile Cruise (B, L, D)"}, {"day": 10, "title": "Day 10 | Red Sea Arrival & Coastal Wellness", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, disembark and fly to Hurghada on the Red Sea coast. Transfer to your beachfront resort and check into your sea-view room. Afternoon free for beach walks or pool relaxation. Evening yoga session on the beach.\\nOvernight: The Oberoi Sahl Hasheesh (B, L, D)"}, {"day": 11, "title": "Day 11 | Red Sea – Marine Energy & Snorkeling", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, board a private yacht for a snorkeling excursion to explore the coral reefs. A marine biologist will guide you through the underwater ecosystem. Lunch onboard the yacht. Return to the resort in the afternoon for leisure.\\nOvernight: The Oberoi Sahl Hasheesh (B, L, D)"}, {"day": 12, "title": "Day 12 | Eastern Desert – Safari & Stargazing Rituals", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast and morning at leisure, afternoon departure for a 4x4 desert safari to explore the Eastern Desert. Visit hidden oases and ancient caravan routes. Evening Bedouin-style dinner under the stars followed by a stargazing session.\\nOvernight: Desert Camp (B, L, D)"}, {"day": 13, "title": "Day 13 | Siwa Oasis – Oracle Temple & Hot Springs", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, transfer to Siwa Oasis. Check in at your eco-lodge and visit the ancient Temple of the Oracle where Alexander the Great is said to have sought guidance. Afternoon visit to the hot springs for bathing in the mineral-rich waters. Dinner at the lodge.\\nOvernight: Siwa Eco-Lodge (B, L, D)"}, {"day": 14, "title": "Day 14 | Departure – Gratitude Ceremony & Return", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, visit the Temple of the Oracle for a final reflection session. Transfer to Cairo by flight or luxury vehicle. Depending on your international flight schedule, you may have time for last-minute activities before your transfer to Cairo International Airport for departure.\\n(B)"}]	{Luxor,Abydos,Saqqara,Aswan,Dendera,"Red Sea",Siwa}	Wellne