d3c49010-82ff-448d-9c10-0f33336dc814	Luxury Romantic Getaways | 8-Day Egypt Honeymoon	luxury-romantic-getaways-egypt-8-day-honeymoon	Among the world's most distinguished luxury romantic getaways, this eight-day Egyptian honeymoon unfolds as pure poetry, distilling five thousand years of civilization into intimate moments designed for two. From candlelit Nile dinners beneath Cairo's glittering skyline to sunrise at Abu Simbel's monuments of eternal devotion, every carefully orchestrated day balances discovery with tranquility, adventure with romance, creating an unhurried journey where transformation happens naturally and love deepens against humanity's most magnificent backdrop.\n	Experience luxury romantic getaways in Egypt. 8-day honeymoon with pyramids, Luxor temples, Aswan & Abu Simbel. Private guides, palace hotels & unforgettable romance.\n	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/bc26e349-5051-4bdf-aee0-10ab2b39d79c.avif	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/0816658f-82d2-42cc-a5da-1c6c9b0296cb.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/cc6e3b05-5669-47ef-8742-5321a7781c82.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/39227dfc-372a-4f93-86a6-34058a5318f2.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/2c029573-238a-4e26-b188-b73477e92a6b.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/0d676c3a-5d2e-453f-b752-01ca06a84736.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/894febe9-cfae-4348-882b-3bd4983827b8.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f9f99816-278e-4f6c-ac19-7aadbb28e8ea.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/a79ffdb6-a163-49b2-b279-1d851d00634b.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/286d9cd1-61b7-4063-bb89-063d09c726a8.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/7ef89258-5b86-4d53-b391-1a19780bb2c0.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f3dd5355-a05a-4e67-bf32-96d393dc3dd1.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/3bb26490-a6d6-4345-8734-5e43f977cd60.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/5f9bf122-f4f8-4562-940f-75b5cb558913.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b19a63cb-3ef3-4adf-8d1a-3cd5aa4dd4ea.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b19a63cb-3ef3-4adf-8d1a-3cd5aa4dd4ea.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/63ac0457-1998-4a2f-91eb-e32fee4beb1f.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/3b73cb4e-b1f1-499a-b376-ef421f5e0835.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/8d88b8be-939b-470a-8d9e-0804302a929b.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/46861453-427d-4e2f-a15a-e3b5c8cca2ec.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/cc06a00b-aaa4-4be8-90bb-619836c02200.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/a8b90a7e-0ba1-4665-b6da-cc0277c246ee.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f5c07d10-613e-453b-a4a1-971df7e8bb51.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/a3addb30-d6fb-4662-b55c-8c5c70ecbafa.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/23772e88-b9bc-4062-957d-6321e274886f.jpg}	8 Days / 7 Nights	2 - 4 	Moderate	0	USD	{}	{}	[{"day": 1, "title": "Day 1 | Arrival Cairo – A Grand Welcome", "activities": [], "description": "Arrive in Cairo where VIP meet-and-assist services ensure seamless entry before your private transfer to Four Seasons Cairo at Nile Plaza, where floor-to-ceiling windows frame the eternal river's shimmering expanse. Evening leisure allows you to settle into your romantic sanctuary before candlelit Nile-view dinner as the city glows beneath endless stars, your extraordinary journey beginning with champagne toasts, exquisite cuisine, and the promise of adventures awaiting together in this land where civilization itself was born.\\nOvernight: Four Seasons Cairo at Nile Plaza"}, {"day": 2, "title": "Day 2 | Pyramids of Giza & Saqqara", "activities": [], "description": "Your private Egyptologist guides you to the Great Pyramids and enigmatic Sphinx in the magical early morning light when golden rays illuminate Khufu's eternal monument, then continues to Saqqara's Step Pyramid and Memphis where ancient Egypt's first capital reveals colossal statues and timeless mysteries. Return to your riverside sanctuary for couples' spa treatments with Nile views, rooftop infinity pool lounging, or sunset cocktails on your private balcony as Cairo's dynamic energy unfolds below, creating perfect moments of shared wonder.\\nOvernight: Four Seasons Cairo at Nile Plaza"}, {"day": 3, "title": "Day 3 | Old Cairo & Flight to Luxor", "activities": [], "description": "Morning brings intimate exploration of the Egyptian Museum's treasures including Tutankhamun's golden collection, the Hanging Church and Ben Ezra Synagogue revealing Cairo's rich spiritual tapestry, and curated wandering through Khan El Khalili's labyrinthine alleys discovering spices, perfumes, and handcrafted treasures without rush or pressure. Evening flight delivers you to Luxor where you check into the legendary Sofitel Winter Palace, an elegant Edwardian sanctuary where royalty has celebrated love for over a century, your romantic suite overlooking the timeless Nile.\\nOvernight: Sofitel Winter Palace Luxor"}, {"day": 4, "title": "Day 4 | Karnak & Luxor Temples", "activities": [], "description": "Explore Karnak Temple's breathtaking complex in morning's gentle light, walking hand-in-hand through the awe-inspiring Great Hypostyle Hall where one hundred thirty-four colossal columns create a stone forest reaching toward heaven. Return near sunset to Luxor Temple when honey-golden light transforms ancient stone into cinematic magic, illuminated facades glowing romantically as evening descends. Intimate dinner follows in the palace gardens surrounded by tropical flowers, palm fronds swaying gently overhead, and the Nile's eternal presence creating unforgettable ambiance.\\nOvernight: Sofitel Winter Palace Luxor"}, {"day": 5, "title": "Day 5 | West Bank of Luxor", "activities": [], "description": "Optional sunrise hot air balloon drift above the West Bank offers breathtaking aerial views before private exploration of the Valley of the Kings where pharaohs rest eternally in spectacularly decorated tombs, Temple of Queen Hatshepsut carved dramatically into limestone cliffs celebrating Egypt's most powerful female ruler, and the colossal Colossi of Memnon standing sentinel for millennia. Afternoon brings leisurely tea overlooking the Nile from your hotel's elegant terraces, time for swimming, couples' spa indulgence, or simply being together in this magical setting.\\nOvernight: Sofitel Winter Palace Luxor"}, {"day": 6, "title": "Day 6 | Luxor to Aswan", "activities": [], "description": "Scenic private transfer through Upper Egyptian countryside reveals rural life unchanged for centuries, palm groves, feluccas sailing peacefully, and children waving as you pass. Arrive in Aswan where you check into Sofitel Legend Old Cataract, arguably Egypt's most romantic hotel perched majestically above the Nile where Agatha Christie wrote \\"Death on the Nile\\" and countless love stories have unfolded throughout its storied history. Sunset brings silence, serenity, and the slow Nile flowing below your balcony creating profound peace and intimate connection.\\nOvernight: Sofitel Legend Old Cataract Aswan"}, {"day": 7, "title": "Day 7 | Abu Simbel & Aswan", "activities": [], "description": "Early flight brings you to Abu Simbel, the ultimate monument of eternal devotion built by Ramses II for his beloved Queen Nefertari, four colossal statues guarding temples carved entirely into mountainside representing history's greatest love story immortalized in stone. Return to Aswan for motorboat journey to Philae Temple's island sanctuary followed by private felucca sailing at sunset, champagne in hand as traditional white sails catch breeze, golden light painting the Nile molten amber, and Nubian villages pass peacefully along ancient shores creating transcendent romantic moments.\\nOvernight: Sofitel Legend Old Cataract Aswan"}, {"day": 8, "title": "Day 8 | Departure – Transformed", "activities": [], "description": "After leisurely breakfast on your Nile-view terrace savoring final Egyptian morning, private transfer to Aswan or Cairo Airport depending on international flight routing ensures seamless departure. You leave Egypt not exhausted from overcrowded itineraries but genuinely transformed by profound encounters with ancient civilization, intimate moments shared discovering timeless wonders together, and romance deepened through extraordinary experiences that become the foundation of your marriage story, knowing this journey will forever hold sacred space in your shared history.\\nMeals: Breakfast"}]	{Cairo,Luxor,Aswan,"Abu Simbel"}	Romantic Escapes 	t	t	2026-01-21 18:57:08.768378	2026-02-13 01:47:57.943	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/44510eac-a854-49ec-aeb3-5fe008cbbaaa.pdf
4dea4b9c-1a01-4cf0-9fdc-d1027cc5e1b8	Two Days Cairo and Abu Simbel Tour From Luxor	two-days-cairo-abu-simbel-tour-luxor	Embark on an extraordinary two days Cairo and Abu Simbel tour from Luxor covering Egypt's most magnificent monuments. Discover Cairo's iconic Pyramids, Sphinx, and Egyptian Museum, then fly to witness the colossal temples of Abu Simbel. This comprehensive tour combines expert guidance, domestic flights, comfortable accommodations, and unforgettable encounters with pharaonic masterpieces across two action-packed days.	Experience Egypt's greatest treasures on a 2-day Cairo and Abu Simbel tour from Luxor. Explore pyramids, temples, and Ramses II's masterpiece with expert guides.\n	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f38292b8-10d9-4191-8a52-1bc5cbaba932.jpg	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f38292b8-10d9-4191-8a52-1bc5cbaba932.jpg}	2 Days / 1 Night	2 - 12 people	Moderate	0	USD	{"Air-conditioned vehicles "," Professional Egyptologist guides "," Hotel pickup and drop-off in Luxor "," Domestic flights (Luxor-Cairo-Abu Simbel-Cairo-Luxor) "," 1 night accommodation in Cairo (4-star hotel) "," Meals: 1 breakfast, 2 lunches, 1 dinner "," Entrance fees to all sites "," Bottled water "," All taxes and service charges"}	{"Personal expenses "," Gratuities (optional) "," Drinks during meals"}	[{"day": 1, "title": "Day 1 | Cairo - Pyramids of Giza, Sphinx, Egyptian Museum & Khan El Khalili", "activities": ["Cairo - Pyramids of Giza, Sphinx, Egyptian Museum & Khan El Khalili"], "description": "Your Egyptian odyssey begins with early morning transfer to Luxor Airport for your flight to Cairo. Upon arrival, meet your Egyptologist guide and drive to the Giza Plateau. Stand before the Great Pyramid of Khufu, the last surviving ancient wonder, alongside the pyramids of Khafre and Menkaure. Learn about construction theories, astronomical alignments, and the pyramids' role in pharaonic afterlife beliefs. Visit the Great Sphinx, guardian of the necropolis for over 4,500 years, and the Valley Temple used for mummification rituals. Enjoy lunch at a local restaurant before continuing to the Egyptian Museum. Explore King Tutankhamun's spectacular golden treasures, royal mummies, jewelry, statues, and artifacts from all pharaonic periods. Your guide will highlight the museum's most significant pieces. Visit Khan El Khalili bazaar, wandering through the medieval marketplace's narrow alleys filled with shops selling spices, perfumes, jewelry, textiles, and souvenirs. Experience authentic Egyptian haggling culture and enjoy traditional mint tea. Check into your Cairo hotel for overnight stay, enjoying dinner and rest before tomorrow's Abu Simbel adventure."}, {"day": 2, "title": "Day 2 | Abu Simbel - Great Temple of Ramses II & Nefertari Temple Expedition", "activities": [], "description": "After early breakfast and hotel checkout, transfer to Cairo Airport for your morning flight to Abu Simbel via Aswan. Upon arrival at Abu Simbel, meet your guide and proceed immediately to the temple complex. Explore the Great Temple of Ramses II, featuring four colossal 20-meter-high seated statues of the pharaoh guarding the entrance in powerful poses. Step inside to discover intricate hieroglyphics, vibrant wall paintings depicting Ramses II's military victories including the Battle of Kadesh, and the inner sanctuary where sunlight illuminates the statues of Ra-Horakhty, Amun-Ra, Ptah, and deified Ramses II twice yearly. Visit the adjacent Temple of Hathor, dedicated to Queen Nefertari, Ramses II's beloved wife, adorned with beautiful reliefs showing the queen alongside various deities. Learn how UNESCO orchestrated the temples' remarkable relocation in the 1960s, cutting them into blocks and reassembling them 65 meters higher to save them from Lake Nasser's rising waters. Transfer to Abu Simbel Airport for return flight to Cairo, connecting to evening flight back to Luxor, concluding your memorable adventure."}]	{"Luxor "," Cairo "," 