e512c9d0-affc-424e-b718-061d0c8b205a	14-Day Royal Egypt VIP Tour | Private Pyramid Access & Nile	14-day-royal-egypt-vip-tour	Experience Egypt's ultimate luxury on this exclusive 14-day royal journey featuring VIP access and five-star elegance throughout. Limited to just 4-8 distinguished guests, enjoy private sunrise entry inside the Great Pyramid before public opening a rare privilege reserved for select travelers. Stand within the Sphinx Enclosure for exclusive photos. Explore King Tutankhamun's treasures and journey to Luxor for private Valley of the Kings viewings. Sail seven nights aboard a luxury Nile vessel with butler service. Fly privately to Abu Simbel's colossal temples. Stay at Egypt's finest: Marriott Mena House, Sofitel Legend Old Cataract, and five-star-plus Nile cruise. Includes all meals, private Egyptologist guide, skip-the-line access, and internal flights. Perfect for discerning travelers seeking refined sophistication and exclusive privileges.	14 DAYS / 13 NIGHTS\nUltimate luxury Egypt experience limited to 4-8 guests. Private sunrise entry inside the Great Pyramid, exclusive Sphinx Enclosure access, private Abu Simbel flight, and seven nights on a deluxe Nile cruise. VIP treatment throughout.	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/8994e48c-b7ec-4fed-846f-e2fe7a4bd8ed.webp	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/bba2209e-a2ff-4015-b32d-7f67129774a4.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/04e491bc-6160-463d-905a-b939b51cbbc6.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/32c4a1f7-3fd5-4dc1-a6db-03a0a3a38ede.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/ca731954-4076-47f7-8083-b508348f434e.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f3481614-3712-4c2f-b3af-36c653dc36ba.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/c21f09b2-7450-4bd5-ac05-c1ee5048085a.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/c28c5a8b-2bf0-4ebf-8ea1-4c9c562dd027.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/c28c5a8b-2bf0-4ebf-8ea1-4c9c562dd027.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/85b38b52-b861-4383-a29a-ead6530d2b35.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/16591281-4cfe-44dc-b24e-46bc022ceeff.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b26c65f5-3a40-4edb-a2c2-15eaa754319d.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/48302b0d-3b1a-4d07-b471-d64a4214ef87.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/d63a6f95-7f28-4984-a6d6-dc76241b478d.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/334f59a4-6caa-4642-9a7a-7fa50ec1866a.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/4f8003c4-ae61-48cd-b95b-90bc4b45119c.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/195f65e0-1d9f-4931-b70e-42d7ba195875.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b62250aa-c1da-414b-8f1f-a95572437446.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f22f70d2-f718-46df-b39b-f11e18e4e27d.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f22f70d2-f718-46df-b39b-f11e18e4e27d.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/76361fe7-f2c8-4923-945b-642e2dc920c4.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/aad1f914-d036-460c-8616-f02492db939d.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/0d7907fe-0d79-4135-9b13-f68fa4d048e0.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/0d7907fe-0d79-4135-9b13-f68fa4d048e0.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/0d7907fe-0d79-4135-9b13-f68fa4d048e0.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/14134af8-f4b3-463c-8907-8e64bf73a57b.jpg}	14 Days / 13 Nights	4 - 8 	Easy	0	USD	{}	{}	[{"day": 1, "title": "Day 1 | Cairo - VIP Arrival & Welcome Dinner", "activities": [], "description": "VIP airside greeting ensures seamless fast-track service through Cairo International Airport's private lounge. Your luxury Mercedes transfer escorts you to the Marriott Mena House, the historic palace hotel resting at the Great Pyramids' foot.\\n\\nSettle into your spacious Pyramid View Suite with floor-to-ceiling windows framing the ancient monuments. This evening, savor a welcome dinner in the jasmine-scented gardens beneath floodlit pyramids, accompanied by live oriental music. Meet your expert Egyptologist guide who will introduce your extraordinary 14-day journey through Egypt's most exclusive experiences.\\n\\nOvernight: Marriott Mena House, Giza - Pyramid View Suite\\n\\nMeals: Welcome dinner included"}, {"day": 2, "title": "Day 2 | Saqqara - Step Pyramid Complex", "activities": [], "description": "Explore Saqqara necropolis including King Djoser's revolutionary Step Pyramid, the world's oldest monumental stone building designed by legendary Imhotep. Descend into Mereruka's tomb with thirty-three chambers of vivid scenes depicting ancient daily life.\\n\\nEnter Teti's pyramid to view humanity's oldest religious writings carved into chamber walls. Afternoon leisure offers swimming, spa indulgence, or strolling through historic Mena House gardens with unobstructed pyramid panoramas from every vista. Your small group size of four to eight guests ensures personalized attention impossible in larger tours.\\n\\nOvernight: Marriott Mena House, Giza - Pyramid View Suite\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 3, "title": "Day 3 | Memphis & Dahshur - Ancient Pyramids", "activities": [], "description": "Visit Memphis, Egypt's first capital, to witness Ramses II's colossal statue and the magnificent alabaster sphinx. Continue to Dahshur's unique Bent Pyramid and descending into the Red Pyramid's ancient chambers.\\n\\nAfternoon brings exclusive access to the Pyramid Builders' Tombs at Giza, rarely opened burial sites of the skilled artisans who created Egypt's immortal monuments. This offers profound insights into pyramid construction and ancient Egyptian society beyond royal narratives. Your professional photographer captures these extraordinary moments in magical pre-dawn light as the desert awakens.\\n\\nOvernight: Marriott Mena House, Giza - Pyramid View Suite\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 4, "title": "Day 4 | Giza Plateau - Private Pyramid Access", "activities": [], "description": "Private sunrise access to Giza Plateau before public opening includes exclusive entry inside the Great Pyramid of Khufu's King's Chamber and special permit access within the sacred Sphinx Enclosure, normally restricted to archaeologists and dignitaries.\\n\\nYour professional photographer captures these extraordinary moments in magical pre-dawn light as the desert awakens. Evening features private sunset dinner on a terrace overlooking pyramids with live traditional music as monuments glow golden then transform to illuminated silhouettes. This exclusive experience is reserved for select travelers seeking Egypt's treasures with refined sophistication.\\n\\nOvernight: Marriott Mena House, Giza - Pyramid View Suite\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 5, "title": "Day 5 | Luxor - Board Nile Cruise", "activities": [], "description": "Business class flight delivers you to Luxor where you board MS Le Fayan, your floating five-star palace for seven nights of refined elegance. Check into your spacious Deluxe Suite with private furnished balcony overlooking the eternal river's timeless flow, marble bathroom with soaking tub, and Egyptian cotton linens.\\n\\nAfternoon exploration of Karnak Temple Complex, the world's largest ancient religious site, features the breathtaking Great Hypostyle Hall where one hundred thirty-four massive columns create an awe-inspiring stone forest. Evening features cocktails on your private balcony as sunset paints the Nile golden.\\n\\nOvernight: MS Le Fayan Luxury Nile Cruise - Deluxe Suite\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 6, "title": "Day 6 | Valley of the Kings - Private Tomb Access", "activities": [], "description": "Cross the Nile to the legendary West Bank for Valley of the Kings exploration including Tutankhamun's famous tomb where his mummy rests eternally, spectacular Ramses VI's tomb with vivid astronomical ceilings, and a third carefully selected royal burial chamber.\\n\\nContinue to Queen Hatshepsut's stunning three-tiered temple carved into Deir el-Bahari's limestone cliffs and photograph the colossal Memnon statues. Evening returns you shipboard for the Captain's Gala Dinner featuring multi-course tasting menu with champagne and traditional entertainment under the stars.\\n\\nOvernight: MS Le Fayan Luxury Nile Cruise - Deluxe Suite\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 7, "title": "Day 7 | Edfu & Kom Ombo Temples", "activities": [], "description": "Traditional horse-drawn carriage delivers you to Edfu's Temple of Horus, one of Egypt's best-preserved Ptolemaic masterpieces with towering pylons and intact sanctuaries. The temple's remarkable preservation allows you to experience ancient Egyptian worship spaces as they appeared two thousand years ago.\\n\\nAfternoon sailing brings you to Kom Ombo where you explore the unique dual temple honoring both crocodile god Sobek and falcon god Harpoeris, dramatically perched on a riverside promontory with Nile views. Evening Egyptian Night celebration aboard ship features traditional galabeyas, authentic feast, folkloric performances, and Nubian dancing beneath endless desert stars.\\n\\nOvernight: MS Le Fayan Luxury Nile Cruise - Deluxe Suite\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 8, "title": "Day 8 | Aswan - Philae Temple & Nubian Village", "activities": [], "description": "Motorboat carries you across shimmering waters to Agilkia Island for the enchanting Temple of Philae, UNESCO's triumph rescued and reconstructed stone by stone on higher ground after the dam's construction. The temple's elegant island setting makes it one of Egypt's most romantic ancient sites.\\n\\nVisit ancient granite quarries revealing the massive Unfinished Obelisk still attached to bedrock, then the Aswan High Dam with panoramic Lake Nasser views. Afternoon cultural immersion in a traditional Nubian village brings warm hospitality, vibrant painted houses adorned with crocodile symbols, and aromatic hibiscus tea while learning ancient traditions and customs.\\n\\nOvernight: MS Le Fayan Luxury Nile Cruise - Deluxe Suite\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 9, "title": "Day 9 | Abu Simbel - Private Flight", "activities": [], "description": "Pre-dawn private charter flight delivers you to Abu Simbel for witnessing Ramses II's and Nefertari's colossal temples illuminated by sunrise's first golden rays. Stand before four twenty-meter statues guarding the Great Temple carved entirely into solid mountainside, exploring the inner sanctuary penetrating deep into bedrock where sunlight illuminates the gods twice annually.\\n\\nVisit the Small Temple dedicated to Queen Nefertari with its rare equal-sized colossal statues honoring her extraordinary status. Return via sunset felucca sailing with champagne and canapés, enjoying the timeless tranquility of the Nile as golden light transforms the landscape. This private flight experience eliminates the long desert drive required by standard tours.\\n\\nOvernight: MS Le Fayan Luxury Nile Cruise - Deluxe Suite\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 10, "title": "Day 10 | Nile Cruise - Leisure Day", "activities": [], "description": "Serene full day cruising the Nile with no schedule or tours, simply savoring life along the world's longest river from your private balcony's comfort or sun deck lounging. Watch fishermen casting nets, farmers tending fields, water buffalo bathing, palm groves swaying, and villages where life continues as it has for millennia.\\n\\nEvening features private upper deck dining beneath endless stars followed by ancient Egyptian astronomy stories from your Egyptologist, connecting constellations to pharaonic mythology and timeless navigation techniques. This leisurely day allows you to fully absorb the rhythms of the Nile and reflect on your extraordinary journey through five thousand years of civilization.\\n\\nOvernight: MS Le Fayan Luxury Nile Cruise - Deluxe Suite\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 11, "title": "Day 11 | Lost Golden City - Return to Cairo", "activities": [], "description": "Visit the Lost Golden City discovered in 2020, the largest ancient urban settlement ever found in Egypt with remarkably preserved workshops, bakeries, and residential quarters from thirty-four hundred years ago revealing daily life during Amenhotep III's prosperous reign.\\n\\nExplore Deir el-Medina workers' village with beautifully decorated tombs revealing middle-class ancient Egyptian life before your domestic flight to Cairo and transfer to Four Seasons Hotel Cairo at The First Residence with panoramic high-rise views and contemporary sophistication. Evening features leisure time to enjoy hotel amenities or explore nearby dining and shopping.\\n\\nOvernight: Four Seasons Hotel Cairo - Nile View Room\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 12, "title": "Day 12 | Cairo - Citadel & Khan el-Khalili", "activities": [], "description": "Explore Saladin's magnificent Citadel and the stunning Mohamed Ali Mosque with its Ottoman domes, alabaster-clad walls, and panoramic views across sprawling Cairo to distant pyramids shimmering on the horizon.\\n\\nAfternoon leisure offers boutique shopping at Khan el-Khalili Bazaar's labyrinthine alleys filled with spices, perfumes, and treasures, spa treatments, or rooftop infinity pool relaxation with sweeping Nile views. Optional private Nile dinner cruise features gourmet dining, live entertainment, and illuminated cityscape views gliding past. This free afternoon allows you to explore Cairo at your own pace.\\n\\nOvernight: Four Seasons Hotel Cairo - Nile View Room\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 13, "title": "Day 13 | Grand Egyptian Museum - Private Tour", "activities": [], "description": "Private VIP tour of the Grand Egyptian Museum with exclusive access and expert guidance through over one hundred thousand artifacts spanning five millennia. Spend four to five immersive hours exploring the complete Tutankhamun collection including the iconic golden death mask, golden throne with intricate inlay, ceremonial chariots, and five thousand treasures displayed together for the first time.\\n\\nMarvel at Khufu's reconstructed Solar Boat and royal mummies before evening farewell gala dinner celebrating your unforgettable royal Egypt experience with fine dining, traditional entertainment, and personalized farewell gifts as mementos of your extraordinary journey.\\n\\nOvernight: Four Seasons Hotel Cairo - Nile View Room\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and farewell gala dinner included"}, {"day": 14, "title": "Day 14 | Cairo - Departure", "activities": [], "description": "Leisurely final breakfast overlooking the Nile's shimmering expanse with time for last strolls along the Corniche promenade or balcony reflection on your extraordinary journey through five thousand years of civilization.\\n\\nPrivate transfer to Cairo International Airport with VIP services including fast-track check-in, exclusive lounge access, and assistance through departure formalities. Farewell as your plane rises above the desert, carrying Egypt's timeless magic eternally in your heart with memories of exclusive experiences and royal treatment reserved for the most discerning travelers seeking refined sophistication throughout their journey.\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast included"}]	{Cairo,Giza,Luxor,Aswan,"Abu Simbel"}	Small Group Journeys 	f	t	2026-01-22 18:00:47.19647	2026-02-16 03:52:23.686	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	\N
d0218fbb-f070-4f2f-a578-9810838c3504	Two Days Cairo and Alexandria Tour from Aswan by Plane	two-days-cairo-alexandria-tour-aswan	Experience Egypt's ancient and Mediterranean treasures on this two days Cairo and Alexandria tour from Aswan by plane. Discover Cairo's iconic pyramids and museums, then journey to Alexandria's coastal wonders including the Citadel, Catacombs, and modern Library. This comprehensive tour combines expert guidance, comfortable accommodations, and diverse experiences showcasing Egypt's multifaceted heritage.	Discover Cairo and Alexandria on a 2-day tour from Aswan. Explore pyramids, museums, and Mediterranean coastal treasures.	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/9e46cd18-afd9-48da-a025-08e68ae18294.jpg	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/679bfff0-ea9a-45a3-9aa7-8baf79a60187.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/cbe3325b-6bfd-4f25-bed9-5392744a6b97.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/59ddb2ce-84f3-46b7-8df5-c1553bfd20dc.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/fd7a4db6-f46b-477e-988d-8b5e3eb24002.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b7b85015-34dd-4349-9e10-434aa2d69c33.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/259bfbb7-ad96-4528-95c8-7180cb592211.jpg}	2 Days / 1 Night	2-15 people	Moderate	0	USD	{"Private vehicles with professional drivers "," Professional Egyptologist guides "," Hotel pickup and drop-off in Aswan "," Domestic flights (Aswan-Cairo-Aswan) "," 1 night accommodation in Cairo (4-star hotel) "," Meals: 1 breakfast, 2 lunches, 1 dinner "," Entrance fees to all sites "," Bottled water "," All taxes and service charges"}	{"International airfare "," Personal expenses "," Gratuities (optional) "," Drinks during meals "," Any extras not mentioned"}	[{"day": 1, "title": "Day 1 | Cairo - Pyramids, Sphinx, Egyptian Museum & Islamic Cairo", "activities": ["Cairo - Pyramids, Sphinx, Egyptian Museum & Islamic Cairo"], "description": "Your adventure begins with early morning transfer to Aswan Airport for your flight to Cairo. Upon arrival, meet your Egyptologist guide and drive to Giza Plateau. Explore the Great Pyramid of Khufu, Pyramid of Khafre, and Pyramid of Menkaure, marveling at these 4,500-year-old wonders. Visit the Great Sphinx and Valley Temple. Continue to the Egyptian Museum, exploring King Tutankhamun's golden treasures, royal mummies, and countless artifacts spanning ancient Egyptian civilization. Enjoy lunch at a local restaurant before visiting Old Cairo's highlights including the Hanging Church, Ben Ezra Synagogue, and mosques showcasing Islamic architecture. Alternatively, explore Khan El Khalili bazaar, Cairo's historic marketplace filled with shops selling spices, jewelry, textiles, and souvenirs. Check into your Cairo hotel for overnight stay. Enjoy dinner at the hotel or a traditional Egyptian restaurant. Relax and prepare for tomorrow's Mediterranean adventure."}, {"day": 2, "title": "Day 2 | Alexandria - Citadel, Catacombs, Library & Coastal Exploration", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast and hotel checkout, depart Cairo for Alexandria, Egypt's beautiful Mediterranean port city, approximately 2.5 hours drive. Begin at the Citadel of Qaitbay, a 15th-century fortress built on the site of the ancient Pharos Lighthouse, one of the Seven Wonders of the Ancient World. Enjoy stunning Mediterranean views from the fortress walls. Visit the Catacombs of Kom El Shoqafa, a fascinating underground necropolis blending Egyptian, Greek, and Roman artistic styles. Explore the modern Bibliotheca Alexandrina, a stunning architectural tribute to the ancient Library of Alexandria, housing millions of books and manuscripts. Walk along the Corniche, Alexandria's scenic waterfront promenade. Enjoy fresh seafood lunch at a Mediterranean restaurant overlooking the sea. Visit Pompey's Pillar and the Roman Amphitheatre if time permits. Depart Alexandria for Cairo Airport, catching your evening flight back to Aswan. Upon arrival, transfer to your hotel, concluding your enriching two-day journey through Egypt's diverse heritage."}]	{"Aswan "," Cairo "," Alexandria "," Giza "," Egyptian Museum"}	ASWAN	f	t	2026-02-14 00:38:45.91341	2026-02-21 15:11:12.193	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	\N
2621123e-b26d-43df-a4bd-cdf11953491e	9-Day Egypt Tour | Pyramids, Luxor & Red Sea Beach Resort	9-day-egypt-pyramids-luxor-red-sea	Experience Egypt's highlights in just 9 days on this perfectly balanced small group tour combining iconic ancient sites with Red Sea relaxation. Begin in Cairo exploring the legendary Pyramids of Giza, Sphinx, and King Tutankhamun's treasures at the Grand Egyptian Museum. Visit Saqqara's Step Pyramid—the world's oldest stone structure. Journey to Luxor where you'll explore the Valley of the Kings with its elaborately decorated royal tombs and marvel at Karnak Temple's massive columns. Conclude with three nights at a luxury five-star Red Sea resort—relax on pristine beaches, snorkel vibrant coral reefs, or enjoy resort amenities. Includes five-star hotels, all meals, expert Egyptologist guide, skip-the-line access, and internal flights. Ideal for travelers wanting maximum experiences in a compact timeframe.	9 DAYS / 8 NIGHTS\nPerfect blend of culture and relaxation. Explore Cairo's pyramids and King Tut's treasures, discover Luxor's ancient temples and Valley of the Kings, then unwind at a luxury Red Sea beach resort. Small groups 8-12 guests.	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/501477cf-a214-47ff-8cbe-0e76bfea6a27.avif	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/e7f7d38d-1463-4b02-a748-7b1d936efb5d.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/0b532122-2ddd-4da6-bfca-7862cdf396fb.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/5bca76ca-51cc-4132-96fe-42bb1e11fd94.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f3481614-3712-4c2f-b3af-36c653dc36ba.jpg}	9 Days / 8 Nights	2	Easy	0	USD	{}	{}	[{"day": 1, "title": "Day 1 | Cairo - Arrival & Pyramid Views", "activities": [], "description": "Arrive at Cairo International Airport where your VIP representative meets you at the gate to fast-track visa and customs procedures. Enjoy a private luxury transfer to the historic Marriott Mena House hotel, featuring stunning views of the Pyramids of Giza from its landscaped gardens. This evening, meet your fellow small group travelers (maximum 12 guests) and expert Egyptologist guide for a welcome reception. Learn about the exciting 14-day journey ahead as you begin your Egypt adventure in this iconic setting where you can see the pyramids illuminated at night from your hotel. Overnight: Marriott Mena House, Giza (5-star luxury) Meals: Welcome dinner included"}, {"day": 2, "title": "Day 2 | Giza Plateau - Pyramids & Sphinx", "activities": [], "description": "Experience exclusive pre-opening access to Giza Plateau in magical pre-dawn silence before crowds arrive. Enter the Great Pyramid's King's Chamber in complete solitude ascending the Grand Gallery where Khufu's sarcophagus rests eternally, then stand between the Sphinx's paws with special permit reserved for dignitaries.\\n\\nAfternoon leisure offers pool relaxation or spa indulgence amid forty acres of royal gardens with unobstructed pyramid views. Your small group size of just two guests ensures highly personalized attention throughout your journey.\\n\\nOvernight: Marriott Mena House, Cairo\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 3, "title": "Day 3 | Grand Egyptian Museum & Saqqara", "activities": [], "description": "Marvel at the Grand Egyptian Museum housing the complete Tutankhamun collection including his iconic golden death mask, ceremonial throne, gilded chariots, and five thousand treasures displayed together for the first time. Admire the monumental Khufu Boat, a magnificent 43-meter cedar vessel.\\n\\nContinue to Saqqara exploring King Djoser's revolutionary Step Pyramid from 2650 BC, humanity's first monumental stone structure, plus exquisitely preserved noble tombs revealing ancient daily life through forty-three-hundred-year-old carvings showing farming, hunting, and celebration scenes.\\n\\nOvernight: Marriott Mena House, Cairo\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 4, "title": "Day 4 | Luxor - Karnak Temple", "activities": [], "description": "Domestic flight delivers you to Luxor, ancient capital where one-third of the world's monuments await discovery. Explore Karnak Temple Complex, the largest religious site spanning two hundred acres, where the breathtaking Great Hypostyle Hall's one hundred thirty-four towering columns create an awe-inspiring stone forest.\\n\\nEvening brings twilight-illuminated Luxor Temple before checking into the historic Sofitel Winter Palace, where European aristocrats and Egyptologists gathered during Egypt's golden age of archaeological discovery. Enjoy evening at leisure exploring the hotel's colonial elegance.\\n\\nOvernight: Sofitel Winter Palace, Luxor\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 5, "title": "Day 5 | Valley of the Kings - Red Sea Transfer", "activities": [], "description": "Cross to the legendary West Bank by private motorboat visiting the Valley of the Kings where Tutankhamun's mummy rests eternally in his golden sarcophagus, plus spectacularly decorated royal tombs with vivid astronomical ceilings depicting the pharaoh's journey through the afterlife.\\n\\nExplore Queen Hatshepsut's dramatic mortuary temple carved into limestone cliffs before your scenic afternoon transfer to Hurghada's Oberoi Sahl Hasheesh resort, your exclusive beachfront sanctuary where turquoise waters meet pristine white sand beaches.\\n\\nOvernight: Oberoi Sahl Hasheesh, Hurghada\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 6, "title": "Day 6 | Red Sea - Beach Relaxation", "activities": [], "description": "Awaken to turquoise waters lapping pristine private beaches from your sea-view room's balcony. Surrender to timeless indulgence with beachfront cabana relaxation, snorkeling among vibrant coral reefs steps from shore, paddleboarding across crystal waters, or poolside lounging with Red Sea panoramas.\\n\\nSunset brings cocktails at the beach bar before seafood dinner featuring Mediterranean-Arabic fusion cuisine with fresh catches prepared by award-winning chefs. Enjoy the perfect balance of cultural exploration and beach serenity that defines this unique Egypt experience.\\n\\nOvernight: Oberoi Sahl Hasheesh, Hurghada\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 7, "title": "Day 7 | Giftun Island - Snorkeling Adventure", "activities": [], "description": "Your private luxury yacht delivers you to Giftun Island National Park, a protected marine sanctuary with Egypt's most pristine coral reefs. Snorkel among rainbow tropical fish, sea turtles, and vibrant coral gardens in crystal-clear waters rivaling the Maldives.\\n\\nGourmet lunch aboard your vessel precedes white-sand beach relaxation before returning to resort for spa treatments or sunset swimming in infinity pools overlooking the Red Sea. Evening features dinner under the stars with traditional Egyptian entertainment.\\n\\nOvernight: Oberoi Sahl Hasheesh, Hurghada\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 8, "title": "Day 8 | Red Sea - Spa & Leisure", "activities": [], "description": "Morning leisure flows into complimentary spa sanctuary featuring traditional Egyptian massage, aromatic body scrub, and rejuvenating facial using indigenous Red Sea minerals. The luxurious treatment menu offers ancient wellness rituals passed down through generations.\\n\\nAfternoon offers optional diving excursions to famous wreck sites, desert safari adventures, or continued beach serenity from your private cabana. Farewell beach dinner celebrates your journey with live music beneath endless stars as gentle waves provide nature's soundtrack.\\n\\nOvernight: Oberoi Sahl Hasheesh, Hurghada\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 9, "title": "Day 9 | Hurghada - Departure", "activities": [], "description": "After leisurely breakfast overlooking the Red Sea's shimmering expanse, enjoy final moments capturing sunrise photographs from your balcony or last pool relaxation with coastal panoramas. Reflect on the perfect balance of ancient wonders and modern paradise you've experienced.\\n\\nPrivate transfer to Hurghada Airport with VIP departure assistance for your international flight, carrying golden pyramid memories harmonized with turquoise tranquility. This unique journey delivers Egypt's essential ancient sites without sacrificing the beach relaxation that completes any perfect vacation.\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast included"}]	{Cairo,Giza,Luxor,"Hurghada Red Sea"}	Small Group Journeys 	f	t	2026-01-22 17:55:10.903361	2026-02-16 04:04:01.801	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	\N
37c0b2a1-638b-4051-9527-a8f08ef1de9e	7-Day Solo Travel Egypt | Cairo, Luxor & Red Sea	7-day-solo-travel-egypt	Discover Egypt through our inspiring 7-day luxury solo tour designed exclusively for discerning independent travelers seeking sophistication and discovery. From Cairo's timeless Pyramids through Luxor's ancient wonders to the Red Sea's turquoise shores, every moment reflects elegance and authentic Egyptian hospitality.\n\nYour journey includes private Egyptologist guides, five-star accommodations, seamless logistics, and the freedom to explore at your own pace. Perfect for solo travelers with limited time who want to experience Egypt's essential highlights without compromising on comfort or cultural depth. Travel confidently with expert support throughout your adventure.	7 DAYS / 6 NIGHTS Experience Egypt's highlights designed for independent travelers. Private guides, five-star hotels, and seamless logistics. Explore Cairo's pyramids, Luxor's ancient temples, and Red Sea beaches with complete comfort and flexibility. Perfect for solo travelers with limited time.	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/4861c025-852f-4ee7-91bc-6097df20ede6.jpg	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f2b4b327-4b3a-430b-89a1-2a08a92e16a5.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/cc5880bf-441d-41db-b1fb-71af385ab88a.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/a7f1a2a8-37b9-4094-b730-480648350066.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/99453095-69fe-45db-a4f3-cb208ff84291.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/239efd0e-5ab7-4e23-bbd1-0e81657fd71a.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/8946d6c0-e5e6-49e7-ae46-de5b3bb3af1b.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/20072e0f-23ad-4bfd-a4ea-38962cf6c603.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/4a25e056-0690-43d9-ad78-1b406d29bcf3.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b6ffbbe6-d9a0-408b-b5af-4dd0839097f4.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/99c9edbe-14e6-474b-a4d3-be3428b64843.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/3ac8b444-620d-4547-995a-47a262e9ce77.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/ca1ee8b9-0d93-4bbd-83ff-2209dc9f6074.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b1d0cf6b-ee77-4577-890d-427875cfa1d5.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/08143aba-5dd6-4ecb-9d3f-7f2612816cee.jpg}	 7 Days / 6 Nights	1 - 8	Challenging	0	USD	{"Meet-and-assist service by our representatives at all airports","All transfers by private air-conditioned vehicles","2 nights accommodation at Marriott Mena House, Cairo","1 night accommodation at Sofitel Winter Palace Luxor","3 nights accommodation at The Oberoi Beach Resort, Sahl Hasheesh","Domestic flights: Cairo to Luxor, Hurghada to Cairo","All entry fees to temples, tombs, and monuments mentioned in the itinerary","Services of a private Egyptologist guide during cultural tours","All meals stated in the itinerary – (B) for breakfast, (L) for lunch","Local SIM card with data","Bottled water during all tours and transfers","24/7 on-call support","All applicable taxes and VAT"}	{"International flights to and from Cairo","Gratuities for guides, drivers, and cruise staff","Alcoholic beverages","Personal expenses and souvenirs","Travel insurance"}	[{"day": 1, "title": "Day 1 | Cairo - Arrival & Welcome", "activities": [], "description": "Arrive at Cairo International Airport where your VIP representative provides fast-track passport control and customs assistance. Comfortable Toyota Hiace transfer to Marriott Mena House, a historic hotel set in royal gardens at the foot of the Pyramids. Check into your room with pyramid views and settle in at your own pace. Evening at leisure to explore the hotel's beautiful gardens, enjoy dinner, or simply rest after your journey preparing for tomorrow's adventure.\\n\\nOvernight: Marriott Mena House, Cairo\\n\\nMeals: None (meals on own account)"}, {"day": 2, "title": "Day 2 | Giza & Saqqara - Ancient Pyramids", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, meet your private Egyptologist guide for morning exploration at the Giza Plateau. Visit the Great Pyramids and mysterious Sphinx with plenty of time for photos and questions at your own pace. Continue to Saqqara exploring King Djoser's Step Pyramid, the oldest pyramid in Egypt and world's oldest stone structure. Lunch at a restaurant overlooking the pyramids. Afternoon at leisure to relax at the hotel or explore independently.\\n\\nOvernight: Marriott Mena House, Cairo\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast and lunch included"}, {"day": 3, "title": "Day 3 | Luxor - Karnak & Luxor Temples", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, fly to Luxor, ancient Thebes and capital of the New Kingdom. Visit Karnak Temple, the largest religious complex ever built, walking through the massive Hypostyle Hall with 134 towering columns. Continue to Luxor Temple with your private guide explaining the history and significance of these monuments. Check into Sofitel Winter Palace overlooking the Nile, the legendary hotel where archaeologists once gathered during Egypt's golden age of discovery.\\n\\nOvernight: Sofitel Winter Palace, Luxor\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast and lunch included"}, {"day": 4, "title": "Day 4 | Valley of the Kings - Red Sea Journey", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, visit the Valley of the Kings with your private guide entering selected royal tombs including Tutankhamun's resting place. Continue to Queen Hatshepsut's dramatic mortuary temple carved into limestone cliffs and stop at the colossal Memnon statues. After lunch, enjoy scenic drive to the Red Sea coast (approximately 4 hours). Arrive at The Oberoi Beach Resort at Sahl Hasheesh and check into your suite with private courtyard.\\n\\nOvernight: The Oberoi Beach Resort, Hurghada\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast and lunch included"}, {"day": 5, "title": "Day 5 | Red Sea - Leisure & Relaxation", "activities": [], "description": "Day completely at leisure to enjoy the beach and resort facilities at your own pace. Optional activities include snorkeling among colorful coral reefs, scuba diving with certified instructors, spa treatments and wellness experiences, water sports like kayaking or paddleboarding, or simply relaxing by the infinity pool overlooking the turquoise waters. The day is entirely yours to design based on your interests whether seeking adventure or peaceful beach relaxation.\\n\\nOvernight: The Oberoi Beach Resort, Hurghada\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast included"}, {"day": 6, "title": "Day 6 | Red Sea - Beach Paradise", "activities": [], "description": "Another day completely at leisure to continue enjoying the resort and beach. Explore more of the Red Sea's underwater wonders, indulge in additional spa treatments, try new water activities, or simply relax on the pristine private beach. This flexible day allows you to recover from your cultural explorations and enjoy the tranquil beach atmosphere at your own rhythm creating balance in your solo journey.\\n\\nOvernight: The Oberoi Beach Resort, Hurghada\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast included"}, {"day": 7, "title": "Day 7 | Hurghada - Departure", "activities": [], "description": "After leisurely final breakfast overlooking the Red Sea, enjoy your last moments at the resort before transferring to Hurghada Airport. Flight to Cairo connecting to your international departure. Optional overnight in Cairo if your flight departs the following day, allowing more time to relax or do last-minute shopping. Depart Egypt carrying memories of ancient wonders, cultural discoveries, and peaceful beach moments from your solo adventure.\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast included"}]	{Cairo,Luxor,"Red Sea Coast"}	Solo Travel 	f	t	2026-01-21 14:01:35.129277	2026-02-16 08:21:37.194	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/44510eac-a854-49ec-aeb3-5fe008cbbaaa.pdf
23bb49a5-80ef-4464-b601-32172fc7df4d	Memphis, Saqqara & Dahshur Ultra-Luxury Private Archaeological Tour	 exclusive-memphis-saqqara-dahshur	Embark on an extraordinary ultra-luxury private tour beyond the crowds to Egypt's lesser-known yet equally magnificent ancient capitals. This exclusive bespoke experience unveils the Step Pyramid of Saqqara, the engineering marvels of Dahshur, and the open-air museum of Memphis designed specifically for discerning travelers seeking premium archaeological adventures.\n\nYour private luxury tour begins with VIP access to the Step Pyramid of Djoser at Saqqara, the world's oldest monumental stone structure dating back 4,700 years. Your distinguished Egyptologist reveals its revolutionary architectural significance while you enter exclusive mastaba tombs adorned with vibrant hieroglyphs and daily life scenes preserved for millennia. Witness the Pyramid of Unas with its ancient Pyramid Texts privileged access few luxury travelers experience.\n\nContinue in your climate-controlled Mercedes vehicle to Dahshur's royal pyramid complex, home to the distinctive Bent Pyramid and magnificent Red Pyramid. Enter the Red Pyramid's mysterious chambers with VIP interior access descending into pharaonic burial halls, a privilege reserved for exclusive tours. Explore Memphis, ancient Egypt's legendary capital for over 3,000 years.\n\nThis high-end Cairo experience includes luxury chauffeur service, expert Egyptologist, five-star lunch at a distinguished restaurant, and white-glove service throughout.\n	Ultra-luxury private tour: Step Pyramid of Saqqara, Bent Pyramid of Dahshur & ancient Memphis. VIP access, expert Egyptologist, Mercedes transport & gourmet lunch.\n\n	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/cc6e3b05-5669-47ef-8742-5321a7781c82.jpg	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/95fe747a-3731-40eb-bf52-ac8e8edebb14.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/5c384d45-cb20-4895-9849-705e4f55a331.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/as