hoods where locals go about their daily routines, providing authentic glimpses of Egyptian life. Admire architectural details of traditional buildings and modern structures side by side. Photograph the vibrant street scenes and friendly locals. Your carriage ride concludes with return to your hotel, having experienced Aswan's authentic character from a unique, traditional perspective."}]	{Aswan}	ASWAN	f	t	2026-02-14 00:38:45.899735	2026-02-14 00:46:51.787	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	\N
517323ed-bca4-43c5-ab02-848f5cb034ce	16-Day Egypt Archaeological Tour | In-Depth Temples & Tombs	16-day-egypt-archaeological-expedition	Explore Egypt in extraordinary depth on this comprehensive 16-day archaeological expedition designed for serious history enthusiasts. Limited to 8-12 travelers, venture beyond typical tourist routes to discover lesser-known treasures alongside iconic sites. Enjoy extended time in Cairo exploring multiple pyramid complexes and private chamber access. Journey through Middle Egypt visiting Beni Hassan's rock-cut tombs and Amarna's fascinating ruins. Spend extensive time in Luxor exploring Valley of the Kings, Valley of the Queens, and nobles' tombs with your PhD-level Egyptologist guide. Sail the Nile visiting major temples plus smaller sites most tours bypass, including beautifully preserved Dendera and Abydos. Continue to Aswan for Abu Simbel and Philae, concluding in Alexandria exploring Greco-Roman sites. Includes five-star hotels, deluxe cruise, all meals, and internal flights.	16 DAYS / 15 NIGHTS\nComprehensive archaeological journey for serious history enthusiasts. Visit 40+ ancient sites including lesser-known temples, private tomb viewings, and extended time with PhD Egyptologist guides. Small groups 8-12. Most in-depth Egypt tour available.	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/5dca5152-8e01-487f-baff-ce3f5f8a3d1d.avif	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/803a98d8-a742-437b-9567-f7d5055a0394.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/4f7a550b-4cbc-424b-b9c6-ec8d77b22241.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/695a8d6e-c479-47af-85e6-e3ef76158240.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/bcd715b2-33df-4a71-b3db-9fff9a39c2b4.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/0bcce80a-7df9-433e-8d40-9f86a15903b5.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/858b9d22-3d32-4ff7-a328-3f2b18890311.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/48772198-3556-4e6f-83a2-c56539001535.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/4c8c930f-8f7c-47a6-9157-047fe968f6e7.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/c44e84b9-229e-4896-b655-03bc0daee1b8.jpg}	16 Days / 15 Nights	4 - 8 	Easy	0	USD	{}	{}	[{"day": 1, "title": "Day 1 | Cairo - Arrival & Welcome", "activities": [], "description": "VIP concierge welcomes you airside at Cairo International Airport with seamless fast-track immigration service before your comfortable Toyota Hiace transfer escorts you to the legendary Marriott Mena House, a nineteenth-century palace transformed into Egypt's most atmospheric sanctuary.\\n\\nYour Pyramid View Room frames Khufu's eternal monument through floor-to-ceiling windows. Evening brings candlelit welcome dinner on the jasmine-scented terrace as pyramids glow golden beneath desert stars. Meet your fellow archaeology enthusiasts and PhD-level Egyptologist guide who will lead this extraordinary 16-day deep dive into ancient Egyptian civilization.\\n\\nOvernight: Marriott Mena House, Cairo\\n\\nMeals: Welcome dinner included"}, {"day": 2, "title": "Day 2 | Saqqara - Step Pyramid Complex", "activities": [], "description": "Journey to Saqqara, Egypt's oldest royal necropolis where monumental architecture was born. Explore King Djoser's revolutionary Step Pyramid from 2650 BC and Mereruka's exquisitely preserved tomb carvings depicting ancient daily life scenes.\\n\\nEnter Teti's interior pyramid chambers with hieroglyphic texts covering the walls. Midday brings traditional Egyptian feast in a rural farmhouse surrounded by palm groves, offering authentic glimpses of village life unchanged for centuries. Return to your pyramid-view sanctuary for afternoon leisure exploring the historic gardens.\\n\\nOvernight: Marriott Mena House, Cairo\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 3, "title": "Day 3 | Giza Plateau - Great Pyramids", "activities": [], "description": "Experience the Giza Plateau before crowds arrive, watching sunrise cast golden light across the last surviving Ancient Wonder. Exclusive morning access grants private entry inside the Great Pyramid's rarely opened chambers with special permission to stand between the Sphinx's paws for extraordinary photographs.\\n\\nExplore Khafre's Valley Temple and ancient stone quarries. Sunset finds you at a private viewpoint overlooking all three pyramids as the Sahara burns amber, golden, then purple. Evening features traditional music performance under the stars celebrating your first days exploring humanity's most enduring monuments.\\n\\nOvernight: Marriott Mena House, Cairo\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 4, "title": "Day 4 | Abu Rawash & Abu Sir - Forgotten Pyramids", "activities": [], "description": "Venture beyond tourist trails to restricted archaeological sites requiring special permissions. Explore Djedefre's Lost Pyramid at Abu Rawash set on dramatic plateaus with sweeping desert panoramas, then discover Abu Sir's fifth-dynasty pyramids and sun temples in peaceful solitude.\\n\\nThese lesser-restored sites provide authentic archaeological experiences evoking early explorers' discoveries, mysterious and free from crowds. Extended conversations with your PhD guide explain ancient construction techniques impossible to witness elsewhere, offering insights into pyramid evolution across dynasties.\\n\\nOvernight: Marriott Mena House, Cairo\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 5, "title": "Day 5 | Minya - Middle Kingdom Monuments", "activities": [], "description": "Travel south through rural Egypt exploring three remarkable yet rarely visited treasures. Meidum Pyramid's collapsed outer casing dramatically reveals architectural evolution between step pyramids and true pyramids.\\n\\nHawara's legendary Labyrinth Temple site described by ancient Greeks as surpassing the pyramids themselves. Beni Hassan's cliff-carved tombs display vivid four-thousand-year-old paintings depicting Middle Kingdom daily life, sports, and military campaigns. Arrive at your elegant Nile-view boutique sanctuary for evening relaxation.\\n\\nOvernight: Grand Aton Hotel, Minya\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 6, "title": "Day 6 | Amarna & Tuna el-Gebel", "activities": [], "description": "Explore underground catacombs at Tuna el-Gebel filled with mummified ibises and baboons plus Greco-Roman tombs blending Egyptian and classical artistry. Walk through Tell el-Amarna, revolutionary capital where Pharaoh Akhenaten abandoned traditional gods for single sun deity worship.\\n\\nView rock-cut tombs with unique Amarna art showing intimate royal family scenes and naturalistic human forms. This controversial religious revolution was so radical that successors erased Akhenaten's name from history, making these sites extraordinarily significant for understanding ancient Egyptian religious and political evolution.\\n\\nOvernight: House of Life, Abydos\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 7, "title": "Day 7 | Abydos & Dendera - Sacred Temples", "activities": [], "description": "Discover the Temple of Seti I at Abydos, one of Egypt's most sacred sites featuring the famous Abydos King List chronologically recording seventy-six pharaohs alongside Egypt's finest intricate reliefs with traces of original colors still visible after millennia.\\n\\nContinue to Dendera's Temple of Hathor, goddess of love and joy. Marvel at the famous Zodiac ceiling with vibrant colors visible after two thousand years, mysterious crypts with rare ritual scenes, and rooftop chapels with Nile panoramas. Arrive at historic Sofitel Winter Palace where archaeologists gathered during Egypt's golden age of discovery.\\n\\nOvernight: Sofitel Winter Palace, Luxor\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 8, "title": "Day 8 | Hidden Luxor - Beyond Tourist Sites", "activities": [], "description": "Explore the Lost Golden City, Egypt's most significant archaeological discovery since Tutankhamun. This virtually intact thirty-four-hundred-year-old city with streets, houses, and workshops uncovered in 2020 reveals unprecedented details about ancient urban life.\\n\\nVisit the Ramesseum inspiring Shelley's Ozymandias poem, and the Valley of the Queens including Nefertari's breathtaking tomb called the Sistine Chapel of Ancient Egypt with limited daily access protecting fragile masterpieces. Evening brings Luxor Museum and beautifully floodlit Luxor Temple connected by sphinx-lined avenue.\\n\\nOvernight: Sofitel Winter Palace, Luxor\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 9, "title": "Day 9 | West Bank & Flight to Alexandria", "activities": [], "description": "Enter the Valley of the Kings' royal necropolis containing sixty-three tombs, visiting Tutankhamun's eternal resting place and Ramses VI's tomb featuring famous astronomical ceilings depicting the pharaoh's afterlife journey. Explore Queen Hatshepsut's dramatic mortuary temple carved into limestone cliffs.\\n\\nWalk through Karnak's Great Hypostyle Hall where one hundred thirty-four columns soar twenty-three meters creating humanity's most impressive architectural achievement from antiquity. Evening flight brings you to Mediterranean Alexandria and luxurious Four Seasons San Stefano with panoramic sea views.\\n\\nOvernight: Four Seasons Alexandria\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 10, "title": "Day 10 | Alexandria - Greco-Roman Heritage", "activities": [], "description": "Founded by Alexander the Great in 331 BC, Alexandria was once the intellectual capital of the ancient world. Explore the Catacombs of Kom ash-Shuqqafa blending Egyptian, Greek, and Roman art in underground burial chambers.\\n\\nVisit Bibliotheca Alexandrina honoring the ancient Library, and the Citadel of Qaitbay built upon ancient Lighthouse ruins where archaeologists believe Cleopatra's tomb may lie beneath the waves. Explore El-Alamein War Cemetery before transferring to Jaz Almaza Beach Resort's Mediterranean elegance for coastal relaxation.\\n\\nOvernight: Jaz Almaza Beach Resort\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 11, "title": "Day 11 | Siwa Oasis - Journey to the Sahara", "activities": [], "description": "Travel through the Western Desert to remote Siwa Oasis, one of Egypt's most isolated settlements sitting eighteen meters below sea level, surrounded by the Great Sand Sea. This fertile depression remained virtually cut off from the world until the 1980s, preserving unique Berber culture, language, and traditions distinct from mainstream Egypt.\\n\\nCheck into your Siwa Luxury Eco-Lodge, an architectural masterpiece built from traditional kershef blending seamlessly with desert landscapes. Evening features candlelit dinner beneath endless Saharan stars with visibility unmatched anywhere on Earth.\\n\\nOvernight: Siwa Luxury Eco-Lodge\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 12, "title": "Day 12 | Siwa - Ancient Heritage", "activities": [], "description": "Visit the Temple of the Oracle of Amun where Alexander the Great journeyed in 331 BC to be declared son of Zeus-Amun, legitimizing his Egyptian rule. Explore Shali Fortress, the crumbling medieval town built entirely from salt blocks with panoramic oasis views.\\n\\nDiscover the Mountain of the Dead's Roman-era tombs carved into hillsides. Afternoon brings Bir Wahed's natural hot spring surrounded by sand dunes where you swim in warm waters before watching sunset paint the Sahara molten gold from towering dunes.\\n\\nOvernight: Siwa Luxury Eco-Lodge\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 13, "title": "Day 13 | Siwa - Natural Wonders", "activities": [], "description": "Sail across Siwa Salt Lake's hypersaline waters more buoyant than the Dead Sea to Taghaghien Island. Explore the Siwa House Museum revealing traditional Siwan culture, crafts, and jewelry displayed in authentic architecture.\\n\\nJourney to Crystal Mountain and Zeitoun Lakes where calcite crystals sparkle brilliantly in desert sun and surreal salt formations create otherworldly scenery. This remote oasis offers Egypt's most authentic Berber cultural experience and pristine desert solitude impossible to find elsewhere, a profound encounter with timeless Saharan beauty.\\n\\nOvernight: Siwa Luxury Eco-Lodge\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 14, "title": "Day 14 | Return to Cairo & Egyptology Lecture", "activities": [], "description": "Return to Cairo via scenic desert drive, your journey retracing ancient caravan routes across Western Desert landscapes. Evening brings exclusive private lecture with a renowned Egyptologist offering deeper insights into Egypt's archaeological mysteries, recent groundbreaking discoveries, and ongoing research projects at sites you've explored.\\n\\nThis intimate scholarly exchange illuminates connections between monuments visited throughout your expedition, enriching your understanding of five millennia of civilization beneath the familiar pyramid glow visible from your historic hotel terrace.\\n\\nOvernight: Marriott Mena House, Cairo\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 15, "title": "Day 15 | Grand Egyptian Museum & Farewell", "activities": [], "description": "Dedicate your full day to the Grand Egyptian Museum, the world's largest archaeological museum devoted to a single civilization. Explore the complete Tutankhamun Collection with five thousand objects displayed together for the first time.\\n\\nMarvel at Khufu's reconstructed Solar Boat comprising 1,224 pieces, colossal Ramses II statues, and interactive exhibits using cutting-edge technology revealing treasures never before publicly displayed. Evening brings elegant farewell dinner with live Egyptian music overlooking the Nile, celebrating your profound journey through ancient wonders.\\n\\nOvernight: Marriott Mena House, Cairo\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and farewell dinner included"}, {"day": 16, "title": "Day 16 | Cairo - Departure", "activities": [], "description": "After leisurely breakfast overlooking the pyramids' timeless majesty, enjoy final hours reflecting on your extraordinary odyssey through five thousand years of human achievement and civilization spanning forty ancient sites from Mediterranean shores to Saharan depths.\\n\\nPrivate transfer with VIP departure assistance ensures seamless airport experience as you carry not merely photographs, but profound connections to humanity's earliest civilizations and memories of places few travelers ever witness. Egypt's mysteries await your inevitable return.\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast included"}]	{Cairo,Saqqara,Giza,Minya,Abydos,Luxor,Alexandria,"Siwa Oasis"}	Small Group Journeys 	f	t	2026-01-22 17:42:40.780503	2026-02-16 04:19:37.59	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	\N
5aed0469-9132-4f81-b11a-dda4d965e007	10-Day Egypt Family Tour | Nile, Abu Simbel & Red Sea	10-day-egypt-family-tour	Discover exceptional all-inclusive luxury family vacations journeying through six iconic Egyptian destinations in complete comfort. Explore ancient Nile temples, Abu Simbel's colossal monuments, snorkel pristine Red Sea reefs, and discover mystical Siwa Oasis. \n\nYour 10-day journey combines hands-on cultural workshops, desert safaris, private yacht excursions, and treasure hunts creating unforgettable family memories. Travel with just 2-6 guests ensuring personalized attention from expert Egyptologist guides. Enjoy five-star accommodations, all meals, internal flights, and age-appropriate activities throughout Egypt's greatest treasures from Luxor to the Red Sea coast.	10 DAYS / 9 NIGHTS Experience Egypt's ultimate family adventure with small group comfort (max 6 guests). Explore Luxor's temples, Nile cruise, Abu Simbel's monuments, Siwa Oasis desert, and Red Sea beaches. Perfect for families seeking culture and relaxation.	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/79e00e30-ad06-4ca8-8ca4-86c523de1bc6.jpg	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/07c0b45d-61cb-41ee-ae58-7d4f3331cf5d.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/3b8e759c-34ef-448e-97d5-352d34924dde.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/4de32b86-029b-4791-8507-80fe05140ae6.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f2f47cb4-d588-4ef6-8711-1631ed8a46e6.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/82188ddc-da9c-4876-beb4-87dba45aaf3e.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/cb56304b-db7e-4d03-8694-a40dec613eb2.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/cff898da-c82d-4950-932c-18fb70056911.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/2396c0bc-acd5-449f-993f-340fa88578d2.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/53ee0640-ece3-4ade-b014-0456f98bf409.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b2dac0a7-2974-4f3a-b11b-ce54569150d5.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/3a00f39e-9b2e-44d5-bdd8-0fa9ab3be2d3.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/d7c538b1-7885-405b-a092-2a7a53f31bd2.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/ed1e392e-f44b-403c-ae57-cae0b1a1e6b4.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/308c5b2d-ce90-438d-86a5-77bbc1c17d54.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/17a8afae-b412-44e2-b79e-851bd1ede332.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/e8de3e55-1f16-414b-b703-bebb0114aa42.jpg}	10 Days / 9 Nights	2 - 6 	Moderate	0	USD	{"meet-and-assist service by our representatives at airports","All transfers by private luxury vehicles","2 nights accommodation in 5-star hotel in Luxor (Family Room)","4 nights accommodation on 5-star luxury Nile cruise (Family Suite)","2 nights accommodation at The Oberoi Sahl Hasheesh (Family Suite)","1 night accommodation at eco-lodge in Siwa","All domestic flights during your tour","All entry fees to archaeological sites mentioned in the itinerary","Services of an Egyptologist guide on a private tour throughout your trip","Felucca sailboat ride with live music","Horse-drawn carriage at Edfu Temple","Private motorboat to Philae Temple","Nubian village visit with painting and drumming workshops","Private yacht to Giftun Islands Marine Reserve","4x4 desert exploration and sandboarding in Siwa","All meals stated in the itinerary – (B) for breakfast, (L) for lunch, (D) for dinner","Bottled water during all tours and meals","24/7 on-call support","All applicable taxes and VAT"}	{"International flights to and from Cairo","Gratuities for guides, drivers, cruise staff, and lodge staff","Alcoholic beverages","Travel insurance"}	[{"day": 1, "title": "Day 1 | Luxor - Arrival & Nile Views", "activities": [], "description": "Arrive at Luxor International Airport where your VIP representative meets you and provides fast-track visa and customs service. Comfortable Toyota Hiace transfer to your luxury hotel overlooking the Nile. Check into your spacious family suite with river views. Afternoon at leisure to settle in after your journey. Evening welcome dinner at your hotel where your expert Egyptologist guide introduces the exciting adventure ahead and answers questions about Egypt's ancient sites.\\n\\nOvernight: Luxury Hotel, Luxor\\n\\nMeals: Welcome dinner included"}, {"day": 2, "title": "Day 2 | Luxor East Bank - Karnak & Sunset", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, meet your private Egyptologist guide for morning exploration of Luxor's East Bank. Visit Luxor Temple built predominantly by Ramses II and connected to Karnak by the ancient Avenue of Sphinxes. Continue to Karnak Temple, the world's largest religious complex spanning over 200 acres. Walk through the Great Hypostyle Hall with 134 towering columns. Children enjoy Temple Exploration Challenge decoding ancient symbols. Evening felucca sailboat ride on the Nile with traditional music as the sun sets creating magical family moments.\\n\\nOvernight: Luxury Hotel, Luxor\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 3, "title": "Day 3 | West Bank - Valley of Kings & Tombs", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, cross the Nile to Luxor's West Bank exploring the royal necropolis. Visit the Valley of the Kings entering Tutankhamun's tomb discovered intact in 1922, along with other spectacularly decorated royal tombs preserving vivid colors for over 3,000 years. Continue to Queen Hatshepsut's dramatic mortuary temple carved into limestone cliffs. Children participate in Discover Ancient Symbols treasure hunt. Afternoon check-in to your luxury Nile cruise vessel with spacious family suite and private balcony.\\n\\nOvernight: Luxury Nile Cruise\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 4, "title": "Day 4 | Edfu & Kom Ombo - Temple Discovery", "activities": [], "description": "Breakfast onboard as the cruise sails to Edfu. Visit the Temple of Horus, one of Egypt's best-preserved temples built between 237-57 BC, arriving by traditional horse-drawn carriage through local streets. Continue sailing to Kom Ombo visiting the unique dual temple dedicated to both Horus the falcon god and Sobek the crocodile god. Children join an onboard bread-making workshop learning traditional Egyptian baking methods. Evening features pharaonic dress-up party with costumes provided.\\n\\nOvernight: Luxury Nile Cruise\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 5, "title": "Day 5 | Aswan - Philae & Nubian Culture", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, arrive in Aswan with its distinct Nubian character. Take a private motorboat across the reservoir to Agilkia Island visiting Philae Temple, a beautiful sanctuary dedicated to Isis. The temple was relocated stone by stone by UNESCO to save it from flooding. Afternoon visits a traditional Nubian village where children participate in painting workshops with local artists, learn traditional drumming rhythms, and enjoy authentic Nubian sweets. Sunset felucca sailboat ride around Elephantine Island with white sails catching the breeze.\\n\\nOvernight: Luxury Nile Cruise\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 6, "title": "Day 6 | Abu Simbel - Colossal Temples", "activities": [], "description": "Early morning drive to Abu Simbel, one of Egypt's most spectacular archaeological sites on the banks of Lake Nasser. Visit the twin temples of Ramses II and Nefertari carved into the mountainside 3,200 years ago. Marvel at the four colossal statues of Ramses II, each standing 20 meters tall. Venture inside the rock-cut chambers viewing the detailed reliefs depicting the pharaoh's military victories and religious scenes. Visit the smaller Temple of Nefertari honoring the queen. Drive back to Aswan returning to your cruise for the afternoon.\\n\\nOvernight: Luxury Nile Cruise\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 7, "title": "Day 7 | Hurghada - Red Sea Arrival", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, disembark from the cruise and transfer to Aswan Airport for your flight to Hurghada on the Red Sea coast. Transfer to your luxury beachfront resort. Check into your spacious family suite with private balcony overlooking the turquoise waters. Afternoon at leisure to settle in and enjoy the resort's pristine beach, infinity pool with panoramic sea views, or lush tropical gardens. Evening dinner at the resort featuring international cuisine.\\n\\nOvernight: Luxury Red Sea Resort\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 8, "title": "Day 8 | Red Sea - Snorkeling & Marine Life", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, board your private luxury yacht for a full-day excursion to Giftun Islands Marine Reserve. Snorkel among colorful coral reefs teeming with tropical fish, sea turtles, and exotic marine species with professional marine biologists explaining the underwater ecosystem. Adults can enjoy spa treatments on deck while children explore through the yacht's glass-bottom viewing area. Gourmet lunch prepared by your personal chef served onboard featuring freshly grilled seafood and international cuisine. Return to the resort in the afternoon.\\n\\nOvernight: The Oberoi Sahl Hasheesh\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 9, "title": "Day 9 | Siwa Oasis - Desert Adventure", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, drive to Siwa Oasis, a remote desert paradise near the Libyan border. The scenic drive takes approximately 9-10 hours through changing desert landscapes. Check into your eco-lodge surrounded by thousands of date palm groves and natural springs. Evening at leisure to relax after the journey and enjoy dinner at the lodge with traditional Siwan dishes.\\n\\nOvernight: Eco-Lodge, Siwa\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 10, "title": "Day 10 | Siwa & Cairo - Oracle Temple & Departure", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, visit the Temple of the Oracle, the ancient site where Alexander the Great journeyed in 331 BC to seek divine confirmation of his status. Explore the ruins of this historically significant temple with views across the oasis. Children participate in hands-on cultural workshops learning traditional pottery making techniques and palm weaving with local Siwan artisans, taking home handmade souvenirs. After lunch, drive back to Cairo. Transfer to Cairo International Airport for your onward international departure carrying memories of an extraordinary Egyptian family adventure.\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast included"}]	{Luxor,Aswan,"Abu Simbel",Hurghada,Siwa,Cairo}	Family Travel 	f	t	2026-01-21 14:59:59.069533	2026-02-20 14:03:29.691	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/44510eac-a854-49ec-aeb3-5fe008cbbaaa.pdf
f4c48703-eb95-47df-a751-ecd726b6d2d9	Aswan Felucca Tour by Night	aswan-felucca-night-tour	Discover the enchantment of the Nile after dark on this magical Aswan felucca tour by night. Watch the sunset paint the sky in brilliant colors, then sail under sparkling stars with illuminated monuments creating stunning reflections. This nighttime felucca experience offers romantic ambiance, cooler temperatures, and unforgettable evening views of Aswan's landmarks.	Experience magical nighttime sailing on the Nile with an Aswan felucca night tour. Enjoy sunset views, starlit skies, and peaceful evening ambiance.	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/88f67ab3-9e6d-4185-9ac9-7ba11a13b4d5.jpg	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/88f67ab3-9e6d-4185-9ac9-7ba11a13b4d5.jpg}	2-3 hours	2-15 people	Easy	0	USD	{"Private traditional felucca sailboat "," Experienced Nubian captain "," Hotel pickup and drop-off in Aswan "," Comfortable cushioned seating "," Lanterns for evening ambiance "," All taxes and service charges"}	{"International airfare "," Personal expenses "," Gratuities (optional) "," Any extras not mentioned"}	[{"day": 1, "title": "Day 1 | Aswan - Sunset & Nighttime Felucca Sailing Experience", "activities": ["Aswan - Sunset & Nighttime Felucca Sailing Experience"], "description": "Your romantic evening adventure begins with late afternoon pickup from your Aswan hotel as the day's heat subsides. Transfer to the Nile embankment and board your traditional felucca sailboat adorned with colorful cushions and lanterns. Set sail as the sun begins its descent, casting golden light across the water and illuminating the desert hills in warm hues. Watch the spectacular sunset transform the sky into brilliant oranges, pinks, and purples while photographing this magical moment. As twilight deepens, see Aswan's landmarks light up along the shoreline the illuminated Old Cataract Hotel, twinkling city lights, and the glowing Aga Khan Mausoleum creating beautiful reflections on the calm waters. Sail peacefully under emerging stars as the moon rises, enjoying the cool evening breeze and serene atmosphere. Listen to gentle Nubian music if your captain plays traditional instruments. Experience the Nile's timeless tranquility away from daytime crowds. Complete your enchanting journey as city lights twinkle around you, returning to shore and transferring back to your hotel with unforgettable memories."}]	{"Aswan "," Elephantine Island"}	ASWAN	f	t	2026-02-14 00:38:45.906726	2026-02-14 00:39:05.764	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	\N
d033246c-d469-40a4-b515-f8c07eebded3	 Cairo Tour - Private Luxury Felucca Nile Sailing Experience	cairo-tour-private-luxury-felucca-sailing-on-the-nile	Discover the tranquil elegance of a cairo tour aboard your private luxury felucca on the legendary Nile River. This refined sailing experience offers discerning travelers an authentic Egyptian tradition enhanced with contemporary comfort. Glide past Cairo's riverside landmarks as golden sunset light dances on the water, while your attentive crew ensures every moment reflects sophistication, serenity, and the timeless beauty of Egypt's eternal river.\n	Enjoy a serene cairo tour aboard a private luxury felucca on the Nile. Sunset sailing, gourmet refreshments, and authentic Egyptian experience included.\n	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/9198055b-38e5-4877-9796-cadc44e51639.avif	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/c26c8458-9735-4e3b-ae0d-577a2b85202f.avif,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/52ea5c23-d6a4-4026-b3ab-aba3d407a933.avif}	8 hours	2 - 12 	Easy	0	USD	{"Private vehicle with professional driver","Private traditional felucca with luxury appointments","Experienced captain and crew","Gourmet refreshments, pastries, and beverages","Traditional music and ambient atmosphere","Hotel pickup and drop-off (Cairo/Giza)","All taxes and service charges"}	{"International airfare","Egypt entry visa","Personal expenses","Gratuities (optional)","Extras not mentioned in itinerary"}	[{"day": 1, "title": "Day 1 | Cairo – Private Felucca Sailing", "activities": [], "description": "Your private driver escorts you to an exclusive embarkation point along the Nile where your traditional felucca awaits, appointed with luxury cushions and refined comfort. Your experienced captain and crew welcome you aboard this elegant sailing vessel, explaining the ancient art of wind navigation that has defined Nile travel for millennia.\\nCast off into the gentle current as billowing white sails catch the breeze. Recline on plush seating while Cairo's skyline glides past—modern buildings, historic mosques, and verdant riverside gardens creating an ever-changing panorama. Your crew serves gourmet refreshments including fresh Egyptian pastries, seasonal fruits, premium teas, and refreshing beverages.\\nAs golden hour approaches, witness the Nile transform into a shimmering canvas of amber and rose. The peaceful rhythm of water and wind creates meditative tranquility unavailable in Cairo's bustling streets. Your captain shares stories of the Nile's historical significance, from pharaonic trade routes to modern river life, while traditional music plays softly.\\nCapture stunning photographs of sunset reflecting off the water and silhouetted minarets. Experience the same timeless sailing tradition that has connected Egypt's people for 5,000 years, now enhanced with luxury comfort. After approximately two hours of serene sailing, return to shore where your driver awaits for a comfortable return to your hotel, refreshed by this peaceful Nile interlude."}]	{CAIRO}	CAIRO 	f	t	2026-02-11 17:02:37.989676	2026-02-11 16:04:04.474	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	
ca8ae05e-a282-4217-8af0-d94dbf84707f	9-Day Solo Travel Egypt | Cairo, Luxor, Aswan & Red Sea	9-day-solo-travel-egypt	Discover Egypt through our empowering 9-day solo travel experience designed exclusively for independent explorers. Travel alone but never feel lonely with expert private Egyptologist guides, seamless five-star service, and authentic cultural connections. \n\nJourney from Cairo's legendary Pyramids through Luxor and Aswan's ancient wonders to the Red Sea's turquoise shores. Every moment balances cultural immersion with personal reflection. Enjoy private transportation, skip-the-line access, five-star accommodations, and the freedom to explore at your own pace. Perfect for solo travelers seeking meaningful discovery, personal growth, and authentic Egyptian experiences in complete safety and comfort.	9 DAYS / 8 NIGHTS Experience Egypt's ultimate solo adventure designed for independent travelers. Private guides, five-star hotels, seamless logistics, and meaningful connections. Explore pyramids, ancient temples, Nile sailing, and Red Sea beaches with complete safety and sophistication.	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/99f64350-17a7-4be4-b2f7-ca5c6b424493.avif	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/2e489529-2565-4d5a-86fb-c9fa66088354.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/ef3da304-8272-4bdf-aa4e-ee65a6162401.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/c9585b42-9277-47e5-a666-36ad37477870.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/5e64ac95-b379-4c49-a583-7cd1ab39d37f.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/da9e75e1-d43d-459d-8266-0a31ce2c3090.jpg}	 9 Days / 8 Nights	1 - 8	Challenging	0	USD	{"Meet-and-assist service by our representatives at all airports","All transfers by private air-conditioned vehicles","2 nights accommodation at Marriott Mena House, Cairo","2 nights accommodation at Sofitel Winter Palace Luxor","2 nights accommodation at Sofitel Legend Old Cataract Aswan","2 nights accommodation at The Oberoi Beach Resort, Sahl Hasheesh","Domestic flights: Cairo to Luxor, Aswan to Hurghada, Hurghada to Cairo","All entry fees to temples, tombs, and monuments mentioned in the itinerary","Services of a private Egyptologist guide during cultural tours","All meals stated in the itinerary – (B) for breakfast, (L) for lunch","Traditional felucca sailboat ride in Aswan","Private motorboat transfer to Philae Temple","Local SIM card with data","Bottled water during all tours and transfers","24/7 on-call support","All applicable taxes and VAT"}	{"International flights to and from Cairo","Gratuities for guides, drivers, and cruise staff","Alcoholic beverages","Personal expenses and souvenirs","Travel insurance"}	[{"day": 1, "title": "Day 1 | Cairo - Arrival & Welcome", "activities": [], "description": "Arrive at Cairo International Airport where your VIP representative provides fast-track passport control and customs assistance. Comfortable Toyota Hiace transfer to Marriott Mena House, a historic hotel set in royal gardens at the foot of the Pyramids. Check into your room with pyramid views and settle in at your own pace. Evening at leisure to explore the hotel's beautiful gardens, enjoy dinner at one of the restaurants, or simply rest after your journey preparing for the adventure ahead.\\n\\nOvernight: Marriott Mena House, Cairo\\n\\nMeals: None (meals on own account)"}, {"day": 2, "title": "Day 2 | Giza & Saqqara - Ancient Wonders", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, meet your private Egyptologist guide for morning exploration at the Giza Plateau. Visit the Great Pyramids and mysterious Sphinx with plenty of time for photos and questions. Continue to Saqqara exploring King Djoser's Step Pyramid, the world's oldest stone structure, and the Open-Air Museum of Memphis. Lunch at a restaurant overlooking the pyramids. Afternoon at leisure to relax at the hotel, enjoy the pool, or explore the gardens at your own pace.\\n\\nOvernight: Marriott Mena House, Cairo\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast and lunch included"}, {"day": 3, "title": "Day 3 | Cairo Museums & Flight to Luxor", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, visit the Egyptian Museum seeing Tutankhamun's treasures and thousands of pharaonic artifacts with your private guide. Continue to Old Cairo exploring the Hanging Church, Ben Ezra Synagogue, and Church of St. Sergius. After lunch, visit Khan El Khalili Bazaar where you can browse shops and practice your bargaining skills independently. Late afternoon flight to Luxor. Check into Sofitel Winter Palace overlooking the Nile, a legendary hotel where archaeologists once gathered.\\n\\nOvernight: Sofitel Winter Palace, Luxor\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast and lunch included"}, {"day": 4, "title": "Day 4 | Valley of the Kings - Royal Tombs", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, cross the Nile with your private guide to the Valley of the Kings entering selected royal tombs including Tutankhamun's resting place. Continue to Queen Hatshepsut's dramatic mortuary temple carved into limestone cliffs and photograph the colossal Memnon statues. Return to your hotel for lunch and afternoon at leisure. Optional hot-air balloon ride at sunrise available (additional cost) offering spectacular aerial views of ancient temples and the Nile Valley.\\n\\nOvernight: Sofitel Winter Palace, Luxor\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast included"}, {"day": 5, "title": "Day 5 | Luxor Temples - Journey to Aswan", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, visit Karnak Temple exploring the massive complex with your private guide before continuing to Luxor Temple. After lunch, enjoy a scenic drive to Aswan (approximately 3-3.5 hours) watching rural Egyptian life unfold along the Nile Valley. Arrive at Sofitel Legend Old Cataract Aswan, the legendary hotel where Agatha Christie wrote Death on the Nile. Check into your room with Nile views and settle in for the evening.\\n\\nOvernight: Sofitel Legend Old Cataract, Aswan\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast and lunch included"}, {"day": 6, "title": "Day 6 | Philae Temple & Felucca Sailing", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, take a motorboat with your private guide to Philae Temple dedicated to goddess Isis. The temple was relocated stone by stone by UNESCO, a remarkable feat. Continue to the High Dam and the Unfinished Obelisk revealing ancient stone-carving techniques. Return to your hotel for lunch and afternoon rest. Late afternoon traditional felucca sailboat ride on the Nile at sunset, a peaceful moment for reflection watching the golden light transform the landscape.\\n\\nOvernight: Sofitel Legend Old Cataract, Aswan\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast included"}, {"day": 7, "title": "Day 7 | Red Sea Coast - Beach Paradise", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, optional visit to Aswan Souk exploring the colorful market independently. Midday flight to Hurghada on the Red Sea coast where turquoise waters meet endless beaches. Transfer to The Oberoi Beach Resort at Sahl Hasheesh. Check into your suite with private courtyard and ocean views. Afternoon at leisure to settle in, enjoy the pristine beach, or explore the resort's luxurious facilities preparing for two days of beach relaxation.\\n\\nOvernight: The Oberoi Beach Resort, Hurghada\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast included"}, {"day": 8, "title": "Day 8 | Red Sea - Complete Freedom Day", "activities": [], "description": "Day completely at leisure to enjoy the beach and resort facilities at your own pace. Optional activities include snorkeling among colorful coral reefs, scuba diving with certified instructors, spa treatments, water sports like kayaking or paddleboarding, or simply relaxing by the infinity pool overlooking the sea. The day is entirely yours to design based on your interests whether seeking adventure, wellness, or peaceful relaxation by the turquoise waters.\\n\\nOvernight: The Oberoi Beach Resort, Hurghada\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast included"}, {"day": 9, "title": "Day 9 | Hurghada - Departure", "activities": [], "description": "After leisurely final breakfast overlooking the Red Sea, enjoy your last moments at the resort before transferring to Hurghada Airport. Flight to Cairo connecting to your international departure. Optional overnight in Cairo if your flight departs the following day, allowing more time to relax or do last-minute shopping. Depart Egypt carrying memories of ancient wonders, cultural discoveries, and personal growth from your solo adventure through five thousand years of civilization.\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast included"}]	{Cairo,Luxor,Aswan,"Red Sea Coast"}	Solo Travel 	f	t	2026-01-21 14:13:24.920356	2026-02-16 08:16:53.172	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/44510eac-a854-49ec-aeb3-5fe008cbbaaa.pdf
255bbe26-ceb0-4c73-9a43-521baa247bd4	Two Days Trip to Cairo from Aswan by Plane	two-days-cairo-trip-aswan-flight	Immerse yourself in Cairo's wonders on this comprehensive two days trip to Cairo from Aswan by plane. Explore the Pyramids, Egyptian Museum, Islamic monuments, and bustling markets across two enriching days. This extended Cairo tour provides deeper exploration, comfortable accommodations, and expert guidance, revealing the capital's ancient treasures and vibrant modern culture.	Maximize your Cairo experience on a comprehensive 2-day tour from Aswan. Explore pyramids, museums, Islamic Cairo, and more.	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/6cf06e1c-308f-434f-a325-2fe5e51a8bae.avif	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/501477cf-a214-47ff-8cbe-0e76bfea6a27.avif,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/5dca5152-8e01-487f-baff-ce3f5f8a3d1d.avif,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/544e9bfb-07fc-491f-ab05-fc096ceb89c2.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/9340605c-ee02-4b49-aac7-ed572493c9b7.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/5f9bf122-f4f8-4562-940f-75b5cb558913.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/6525dd71-e0c2-4231-871e-7879b6adced7.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/e09aa5a4-1409-4832-b3d3-ca3395015296.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/e7633f76-baa8-4074-a4b4-d3d23ff538a0.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/14134af8-f4b3-463c-8907-8e64bf73a57b.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f67f393b-80fc-443a-b9a8-47bc119b20c9.jpg}	2 Days / 1 Night	2-15 people	Moderate	0	USD	{"Private vehicles with professional drivers "," Professional Egyptologist guides "," Hotel pickup and drop-off in Aswan "," Domestic flights (Aswan-Cairo-Aswan) "," 1 night accommodation in Cairo (4-star hotel) "," Meals: 1 breakfast, 2 lunches, 1 dinner "," Entrance fees to all sites "," Bottled water "," All taxes and service charges"}	{"International airfare "," Personal expenses "," Gratuities (optional) "," Drinks during meals "," Any extras not mentioned"}	[{"day": 1, "title": "Day 1 | Cairo - Pyramids of Giza, Sphinx, Saqqara & Memphis", "activities": ["Cairo - Pyramids of Giza, Sphinx, Saqqara & Memphis"], "description": "Your Cairo adventure begins with early morning transfer to Aswan Airport for your flight to Cairo. Upon arrival, meet your Egyptologist guide and drive to Giza Plateau. Explore the Great Pyramid of Khufu, the last surviving ancient wonder, along with the Pyramids of Khafre and Menkaure. Visit the Great Sphinx and Valley Temple, learning about ancient mummification processes. Enjoy lunch at a restaurant with pyramid views before continuing to Saqqara, site of the Step Pyramid of Djoser, Egypt's oldest stone structure designed by architect Imhotep. Explore nearby mastaba tombs with beautifully preserved reliefs depicting daily life in ancient Egypt. Visit Memphis, ancient Egypt's first capital, viewing the colossal statue of Ramses II and alabaster sphinx. Check into your Cairo hotel for overnight stay. Enjoy dinner at the hotel or a traditional restaurant. Optional evening Sound and Light Show at the Pyramids or Nile dinner cruise available."}, {"day": 2, "title": "Day 2 | Cairo - Egyptian Museum, Citadel, Khan El Khalili & Islamic Cairo", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, depart for the Egyptian Museum in Tahrir Square, housing over 120,000 artifacts including King Tutankhamun's complete golden treasures, royal mummies, jewelry, statues, and everyday objects from all dynastic periods. Your guide will highlight the museum's most significant pieces while explaining their historical context. Visit the Citadel of Salah El Din, a medieval Islamic fortress offering panoramic Cairo views. Explore the magnificent Mohamed Ali Mosque with its Ottoman-style architecture, alabaster walls, and stunning domes. Enjoy lunch at a local restaurant before venturing into Khan El Khalili, Cairo's historic bazaar dating back to the 14th century. Wander through narrow alleyways filled with shops selling spices, perfumes, jewelry, textiles, copperware, and souvenirs. Experience authentic Egyptian haggling culture and enjoy traditional mint tea at a historic café. Transfer to Cairo Airport for your evening flight to Aswan. Upon arrival, transfer to your hotel, concluding your memorable two-day Cairo exploration."}]	{"Aswan "," Cairo "," Giza "," Saqqara "," Memphis "," Egyptian Museum"}	ASWAN	f	t	2026-02-14 00:38:45.919228	2026-02-21 15:06:21.944	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	\N
d24f780e-d6b5-4da0-85a4-fb0df53fa4f9	Best All Inclusive Vacations for Couples | Egypt Honeymoon	best-all-inclusive-vacations-for-couples-egypt-honeymoon	Recognized among the best all inclusive vacations for couples worldwide, this ten-day Egyptian odyssey represents refined elegance where every detail serves romance. Begin among timeless pyramids, sail the legendary Nile aboard five-star Le Fayan cruise exploring ancient temples, and conclude in barefoot luxury at The Oberoi Beach Resort where turquoise Red Sea waters meet pristine beaches. Every moment intentional, every experience private, this journey lets Egypt seduce you slowly—exactly how honeymoons should unfold.\n	Discover the best all inclusive vacations for couples in Egypt. 10-day luxury honeymoon with pyramids, Nile cruise & Red Sea. Private guides, 5-star hotels & romance.\n	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/6c36235b-69c1-4c87-8bd1-977b667b880b.jpg	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f9e61c3f-dddd-4499-8f04-f7474f3bb036.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/ea645787-2d2a-47ed-9920-6a2bc79633bd.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/afced899-ebfc-437f-8fa6-6002a3e5a38b.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/94a7a75d-3a39-4a09-925a-69d83d7a26c4.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/0652dbd0-0f73-4e8a-af8a-ded2f63e1f75.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b48bc85a-846f-4cda-9ee2-14abd5eae64d.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b48bc85a-846f-4cda-9ee2-14abd5eae64d.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/7afc1ec5-864e-4fb4-8d34-dfbd6dcffc67.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/7afc1ec5-864e-4fb4-8d34-dfbd6dcffc67.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/a91db27e-4703-4a01-8af3-78bba7423ddd.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/7960e44a-fd3e-4ebc-a041-24ef63ad781c.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/65cb6fe3-9828-4367-a9a3-f193f26b1fb9.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/64d7dd05-6651-417b-8e93-b8689476720a.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/fddffbbf-ebae-4846-b67d-02763ce24331.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/e69132c8-5410-4a7d-85d6-9d7d50d7c028.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f2e93c96-bcae-41c1-836d-53760780d93f.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/7fb9d61b-4f7b-4ee5-86c2-fb1fc7d320da.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/0072e08f-36a9-4f75-aa69-d4490d8005c1.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/349f7dab-031f-4f5a-a007-caf6cf578b5d.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/5fa11775-bec1-495a-bd24-3d3f7557d014.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/ff66337d-dc49-4ee3-9c56-982a7458862f.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f5819350-ee61-47d7-8ec0-6d2ca9837ac5.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/fff4b996-44c7-4805-852e-980d2ee1c45e.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/4b45f3db-7fda-48cf-8a46-7a60496ec9f1.jpg}	 10 Days / 9 Nights	2 - 4	Moderate	0	USD	{}	{}	[{"day": 1, "title": "Day 1 | Arrival Cairo – Romance Begins", "activities": [], "description": "VIP meet-and-assist services at Cairo Airport ensure seamless entry before your private transfer to Marriott Mena House Cairo, a historic palace hotel offering breathtaking pyramid views from your romantic suite's private balcony. Evening brings candlelit dinner overlooking the illuminated Giza Plateau as ancient monuments glow golden beneath desert stars, fine Egyptian cuisine paired with wines, and live traditional music setting the perfect tone for your extraordinary honeymoon journey together celebrating your love against civilization's most magnificent backdrop.\\nOvernight: Marriott Mena House Cairo"}, {"day": 2, "title": "Day 2 | Pyramids of Giza & Saqqara", "activities": [], "description": "Your private Egyptologist guides you through the Great Pyramids and enigmatic Sphinx in morning's gentle light, then continues to Saqqara's revolutionary Step Pyramid where monumental architecture was born and Memphis where colossal Ramses II statues stand sentinel. Afternoon leisure at your pyramid-view sanctuary offers couples' spa treatments with ancient-inspired rituals, swimming in gardens with pyramid backdrop, or sunset cocktails on your private balcony watching Khufu's masterpiece transform from golden amber to illuminated silhouette against endless desert sky.\\nOvernight: Marriott Mena House Cairo"}, {"day": 3, "title": "Day 3 | Cairo Cultural Treasures", "activities": [], "description": "Explore Cairo's cultural soul with your private guide beginning at the Egyptian Museum or Grand Egyptian Museum if opened, discovering Tutankhamun's golden treasures and thousands of ancient artifacts. Continue to the Hanging Church and Ben Ezra Synagogue revealing Cairo's rich spiritual tapestry, then enjoy curated exploration of Khan El Khalili Bazaar's labyrinthine alleys filled with spices, perfumes, handcrafted silver, and traditional treasures without rush or pressure, selecting meaningful souvenirs commemorating your honeymoon before evening leisure at your hotel.\\nOvernight: Marriott Mena House Cairo"}, {"day": 4, "title": "Day 4 | Fly to Aswan – Board Le Fayan Nile Cruise", "activities": [], "description": "Morning flight delivers you to Aswan where you board Le Fayan Luxury Nile Cruise, your floating five-star palace with only fifty suites ensuring intimate personalized service. After settling into your spacious Luxury Suite with private furnished balcony, explore Philae Temple dedicated to Isis, goddess of love herself, reached by motorboat across shimmering waters, then visit the High Dam and Unfinished Obelisk revealing ancient stone-cutting techniques. Evening brings sunset cocktails and gourmet dining aboard as your romantic Nile journey begins.\\nOvernight: Le Fayan Luxury Nile Cruise"}, {"day": 5, "title": "Day 5 | Abu Simbel & Kom Ombo", "activities": [], "description": "Early excursion brings you to Abu Simbel, the most powerful love monument in ancient Egypt where Ramses II built colossal temples for his beloved Queen Nefertari, four twenty-meter statues guarding entrances carved entirely into mountainside representing history's greatest architectural love letter. Return to your floating palace and sail north toward Kom Ombo, visiting the unique dual temple dedicated to both Sobek and Haroeris at sunset when golden light transforms ancient stone, creating romantic moments photographed against the Nile's timeless flow.\\nOvernight: Le Fayan Luxury Nile Cruise"}, {"day": 6, "title": "Day 6 | Edfu Temple & Scenic Sailing", "activities": [], "description": "Visit Edfu Temple, one of Egypt's best-preserved sanctuaries dedicated to Horus with towering pylons and intact chambers revealing vivid reliefs still showing original colors after two millennia. Afternoon brings serene relaxation on your private balcony or sun deck as the Nile flows past timeless villages, farmers tending fields, children waving, water buffalo bathing, and palm groves swaying—life continuing as it has for centuries while you drift peacefully through this eternal landscape hand-in-hand, disconnected from modern world.\\nOvernight: Le Fayan Luxury Nile Cruise"}, {"day": 7, "title": "Day 7 | Luxor Temples", "activities": [], "description": "Explore Luxor's magnificent East Bank beginning with Karnak Temple Complex, the largest ancient religious site in the world where the breathtaking Great Hypostyle Hall's one hundred thirty-four towering columns create an awe-inspiring stone forest. Continue to Luxor Temple at golden hour when honey-colored light transforms facades into cinematic beauty, then return shipboard for your final romantic dinner aboard the cruise featuring gourmet tasting menu, champagne toasts, traditional entertainment, and Nile views creating unforgettable conclusion to your floating palace experience.\\nOvernight: Le Fayan Luxury Nile Cruise"}, {"day": 8, "title": "Day 8 | Luxor West Bank & Transfer to Red Sea", "activities": [], "description": "Optional sunrise hot air balloon drift above the West Bank offers breathtaking aerial perspectives before exploring the Valley of the Kings where pharaohs rest eternally in spectacularly decorated tombs, Temple of Queen Hatshepsut carved dramatically into limestone cliffs, and colossal Colossi of Memnon. After profound morning discoveries, private transfer through scenic Egyptian countryside delivers you to The Oberoi Beach Resort, Sahl Hasheesh, Egypt's most exclusive seaside sanctuary where pristine beaches, turquoise waters, and barefoot luxury await your arrival for ultimate relaxation.\\nOvernight: The Oberoi Beach Resort, Sahl Hasheesh"}, {"day": 9, "title": "Day 9 | Red Sea Romance", "activities": [], "description": "A full day dedicated entirely to pure indulgence, relaxation, and celebrating each other in paradise. Unwind on the resort's private beach with powdery white sand and crystal-clear turquoise waters exclusively for resort guests, snorkel vibrant coral reefs teeming with tropical marine life, indulge in luxurious couples' spa treatments with seaside views, or arrange optional private yacht charter for intimate Red Sea exploration. As sun sets painting the sky in brilliant hues, enjoy romantic dinner beneath endless stars with waves lapping gently.\\nOvernight: The Oberoi Beach Resort, Sahl Hasheesh"}, {"day": 10, "title": "Day 10 | Departure", "activities": [], "description": "Savor your final Egyptian breakfast overlooking the Red Sea's shimmering turquoise expanse, perhaps taking last morning swim in pristine waters or strolling hand-in-hand along the private beach reflecting on your extraordinary journey together. Private transfer to Hurghada Airport for international departure or Cairo via domestic flight if required ensures seamless conclusion. You leave Egypt not just with photographs and souvenirs, but genuinely transformed by profound shared experiences, deepened love, and treasured memories becoming your marriage's foundation story forever.\\nMeals: Breakfast"}]	{Cairo,Aswan,Luxor,"Red Sea (Sahl Hasheesh)"}	Romantic Escapes 	f	t	2026-01-21 19:12:17.655114	2026-02-13 01:48:08.113	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/44510eac-a854-49ec-aeb3-5fe008cbbaaa.pdf
7da195ff-ec32-4776-a78b-dbaf17311710	10-Day Egypt Family Escape | Pyramids, Red Sea & Desert	10-day-egypt-family-escape	Discover an exclusive 10-day Egypt family escape blending ancient wonders with modern luxury. Begin in Cairo exploring the iconic pyramids and King Tutankhamun's treasures before flying to the Red Sea for private yacht adventures and pristine beaches. Venture into the Eastern Desert for authentic Bedouin experiences, camel rides, and professional stargazing under endless desert skies.\n\nYour family journey includes ultra-luxury accommodations, all meals, private Egyptologist guides, internal flights, and unique experiences like Junior Archaeologist programs, sunset photography sessions, and traditional cooking classes. Perfect for families seeking authentic cultural immersion combined with beach relaxation and desert adventures in intimate comfort.	10 DAYS / 9 NIGHTS Experience luxury family vacation combining Cairo's ancient pyramids with Red Sea beaches and Eastern Desert adventure. Private yacht excursions, desert safaris, stargazing, and ultra-luxury accommodations. Perfect for families seeking exclusive experiences.	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/29d99cbd-4078-425c-8333-fa38635eb785.jpg	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/8a6795a5-6529-48ab-8a4f-c46b17ba6d33.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/c0bff7d0-b686-4dc9-aaea-97bd9b3ac957.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/0739f0de-2614-4427-aa8a-22e4ecf622dd.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/d1a6392c-5ce8-4abd-b6b2-7cce34e513e7.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/808fb6dd-c518-4ab9-b002-e29b438bc7a4.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b48c1272-43a9-4b86-9cce-d4118d04a7c4.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/4a168f6e-4595-4d3d-8e1c-4c0ff78f4876.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/29d99cbd-4078-425c-8333-fa38635eb785.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/a03503c9-b1cf-4d2a-9c21-bf939efc8c5b.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/deeafe2d-9e64-4c20-b214-7a4bb6d180c3.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/06882537-f75a-4605-93ee-a690c2d019f2.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/ebae5e5b-3961-4f72-aa61-7b3d936b0993.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/544e9bfb-07fc-491f-ab05-fc096ceb89c2.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/dec9bcd7-559c-41b1-b0ff-06c4ae45bf68.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/9811fbcf-7337-4c52-8050-d52f3c456981.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/a6502399-9973-4c76-9d7c-2c8bcefd77c4.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/799d1bd5-1e6c-4cd6-b1c1-c5ec07cb7856.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/58806b53-bbb6-4ab7-a6a2-41f1a71cc3e2.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/253a9ae2-eb71-427a-bc6b-c7eedda8eafd.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f0523c51-4d1b-4b77-971e-23fa432d3328.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/0a0cffef-3fa0-416e-9386-4a7256ca2d81.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/7c5274ea-8d78-4700-9e86-23d9376af783.jpg}	10 Days / 9 Nights	2 - 6 	Challenging	0	USD	{"Meet-and-assist service by our representatives at airports","All transfers by private air-conditioned vehicles","4 nights accommodation at Four Seasons Cairo at Nile Plaza (Family Room)","3 nights accommodation at The Oberoi Sahl Hasheesh (Family Suite)","2 nights accommodation at Luxury Desert Camp (Family Tent)","All domestic flights during your tour","All entry fees to museums and archaeological sites mentioned in the itinerary","Services of an Egyptologist guide on a private tour throughout your trip","Private sunset Nile cruise with dinner","Private yacht charter with snorkeling equipment","Water sports activities (kayaking, parasailing, jet-skiing)","Private 4x4 desert safari in Eastern Desert","Bedouin village visit with camel rides","Desert wildlife walk with naturalist guide","Stargazing session with professional astronomer","Farewell dinner overlooking the Nile","All meals stated in the itinerary – (B) for breakfast, (L) for lunch, (D) for dinner","Bottled water during all tours and meals","24/7 on-call support","All applicable taxes and VAT"}	{"International flights to and from Cairo","Gratuities for guides, drivers, cruise staff, and lodge staff","Alcoholic beverages","Travel insurance"}	[{"day": 1, "title": "Day 1 | Cairo - VIP Arrival & Nile Cruise", "activities": [], "description": "Arrive at Cairo International Airport where your VIP representative provides fast-track passport control and customs assistance. Comfortable Toyota Hiace transfer to Four Seasons Cairo at Nile Plaza. After settling into your spacious family suite, enjoy a private sunset Nile cruise with dinner onboard. Watch the city lights reflect on the water as traditional feluccas sail past while your guide shares stories of Cairo's rich history creating magical first impressions of Egypt.\\n\\nOvernight: Four Seasons Cairo at Nile Plaza\\n\\nMeals: Welcome dinner included"}, {"day": 2, "title": "Day 2 | Giza - Great Pyramids & Sphinx", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, meet your private Egyptologist guide for morning exploration at the Giza Plateau. Visit the Great Pyramid of Khufu, the only surviving Ancient Wonder. Ride camels across the desert for panoramic views of all three pyramids rising from golden sands. Stand before the imposing Sphinx, the guardian with a lion's body and pharaoh's face. Children participate in Junior Archaeologist program crafting miniature statues and learning to write their names in hieroglyphs on papyrus creating hands-on memories.\\n\\nOvernight: Four Seasons Cairo at Nile Plaza\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 3, "title": "Day 3 | Cairo - Grand Egyptian Museum & Islamic Quarter", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, visit the Grand Egyptian Museum, the world's largest museum dedicated to a single civilization. Stand face-to-face with Tutankhamun's Golden Mask exploring thousands of artifacts spanning 7,000 years. After lunch, walk through historic Islamic Cairo streets. Explore El Muizz Street, an open-air museum filled with medieval architectural treasures, and wander through Khan El Khalili market. End the day with private family cooking class preparing traditional Egyptian dishes together.\\n\\nOvernight: Four Seasons Cairo at Nile Plaza\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 4, "title": "Day 4 | Hurghada - Red Sea Arrival", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, take morning flight to Hurghada on the Red Sea coast. Transfer to The Oberoi Sahl Hasheesh, your ultra-luxury beachfront resort. Check into spacious family suite with private balcony overlooking turquoise waters. Afternoon at leisure relaxing on your private beach, swimming in pools, or exploring resort facilities. Late afternoon professional sunset photography session on the beach capturing your family against colorful sky and Red Sea creating treasured portraits.\\n\\nOvernight: The Oberoi Sahl Hasheesh\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast and dinner included"}, {"day": 5, "title": "Day 5 | Red Sea - Private Yacht Adventure", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, board your private luxury yacht for full-day Red Sea adventure. Cruise to protected marine areas snorkeling among vibrant coral gardens teeming with tropical fish, sea turtles, and colorful marine life. Optional beginner diving courses available for older children and adults with certified instructors. Gourmet lunch served onboard featuring freshly grilled seafood and Mediterranean specialties. Parents enjoy spa treatments on deck while children explore underwater world through glass-bottom viewing area.\\n\\nOvernight: The Oberoi Sahl Hasheesh\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 6, "title": "Day 6 | Red Sea - Water Sports & Beach Leisure", "activities": [], "description": "Day at leisure with variety of activities available. Optional water sports include kayaking through crystal-clear waters, parasailing high above the Red Sea for aerial coastline views, or jet-skiing along the shore. Afternoon spa sessions with treatments for the whole family including massage therapies and wellness experiences. Evening private beach dinner illuminated by lanterns with live traditional music as gentle waves lap the shore while stars emerge over the water.\\n\\nOvernight: The Oberoi Sahl Hasheesh\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 7, "title": "Day 7 | Eastern Desert - Safari Adventure", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, depart for the Eastern Desert in your private 4x4 vehicle. Navigate through golden dunes and rocky wadis experiencing the dramatic desert landscape stretching between the Nile and Red Sea. Stop for sandboarding down high dune slopes. Visit a traditional Bedouin village enjoying camel rides and sweet mint tea with local families learning about desert life and culture. Evening Bedouin-style BBQ dinner prepared over open fire followed by campfire storytelling under the desert sky.\\n\\nOvernight: Luxury Desert Camp\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 8, "title": "Day 8 | Eastern Desert - Wildlife & Stargazing", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, join a naturalist guide for morning desert wildlife walk discovering how plants and animals have adapted to survive in this harsh environment. Return to camp for lunch and afternoon activities including traditional craft workshops where children learn Bedouin weaving and sand art techniques. Listen to traditional stories and legends passed down through generations. As darkness falls, gather for professional astronomer-guided stargazing session learning about celestial navigation and constellations ancient travelers used.\\n\\nOvernight: Luxury Desert Camp\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 9, "title": "Day 9 | Cairo - Return & Leisure", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast and final morning in the desert, drive back to the Red Sea coast and fly to Cairo. Transfer to Four Seasons and check into your family suite overlooking the Nile. Afternoon at leisure to relax at the hotel, enjoy the rooftop pool, or do last-minute shopping. Evening farewell dinner at a restaurant overlooking the Nile celebrating the incredible journey your family has shared across Egypt's diverse landscapes from ancient monuments to desert wilderness and Red Sea paradise.\\n\\nOvernight: Four Seasons Cairo at Nile Plaza\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast and dinner included"}, {"day": 10, "title": "Day 10 | Cairo - Departure", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, enjoy your final morning in Cairo with time to pack and prepare for your journey home. Depending on your flight schedule, you may have time for a last stroll through the hotel gardens or a final view of the Nile from your balcony. Private transfer to Cairo International Airport where your representative assists with check-in procedures. Depart Egypt with hearts filled with memories of ancient wonders, desert adventures, Red Sea beauty, and precious family moments to treasure forever.\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast included"}]	{Cairo,Giza,Hurghada,"Eastern Desert"}	Family Travel 	t	t	2026-01-21 14:35:47.966712	2026-02-16 07:59:11.261	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/44510eac-a854-49ec-aeb3-5fe008cbbaaa.pdf
4444d2e8-ed6a-4626-bc3c-bd0608856603	Private Abu Simbel Day Trip from Aswan by Vehicle	private-abu-simbel-day-trip-aswan	Embark on an exclusive day trip to Abu Simbel from Aswan by private vehicle and witness Egypt's most awe-inspiring temples. Marvel at the colossal statues of Ramses II and Queen Nefertari's beautifully decorated sanctuary. This private Abu Simbel excursion offers personalized attention, flexible scheduling, and comfortable transportation across the stunning Nubian Desert landscape.	Experience the magnificent Abu Simbel temples on a private day trip from Aswan. Explore Ramses II's colossal monuments with expert guides and comfortable transportation.	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/88f67ab3-9e6d-4185-9ac9-7ba11a13b4d5.jpg	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/88f67ab3-9e6d-4185-9ac9-7ba11a13b4d5.jpg}	1 Day	2-15 people	Moderate	0	USD	{"Private vehicle with professional driver "," Professional Egyptologist guide "," Hotel pickup and drop-off in Aswan "," Entrance fees to Abu Simbel temples "," Bottled water during transfer "," All taxes and service charges"}	{"International airfare "," Personal expenses "," Gratuities (optional) "," Any extras not mentioned"}	[{"day": 1, "title": "Day 1 | Abu Simbel - Ramses II Great Temple & Nefertari Temple Exploration", "activities": ["Abu Simbel - Ramses II Great Temple & Nefertari Temple Exploration"], "description": "Your private Abu Simbel adventure begins with early morning pickup from your Aswan hotel around 4:00 AM. Relax in your air-conditioned vehicle as you journey through the breathtaking desert landscape for approximately 3 hours, covering 280 kilometers southwest of Aswan. Upon arrival, explore the Great Temple of Ramses II, featuring four massive 20-meter-high seated statues guarding the entrance. Step inside to discover intricate hieroglyphics and vibrant wall paintings depicting the pharaoh's military triumphs. Your expert Egyptologist guide will reveal fascinating details about the temple's construction and astronomical alignment. Next, visit the Temple of Hathor, dedicated to Queen Nefertari, adorned with stunning reliefs and colorful decorations. Learn how UNESCO heroically relocated these ancient monuments in the 1960s to save them from Lake Nasser's rising waters. Enjoy ample time for photography and personal exploration before departing for Aswan. Arrive back at your hotel by early afternoon, enriched with unforgettable memories of these magnificent ancient wonders."}]	{"Aswan "," Abu Simbel"}	ASWAN	f	t	2026-02-14 00:38:45.864183	2026-02-14 00:21:05.98	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	\N
