aonic significance of these eternal monuments. Approach the enigmatic Great Sphinx for intimate viewing and exceptional photography without tourist congestion. Your guide reveals ancient Egyptian cosmology, construction techniques, and royal burial traditions. Climate-controlled luxury transportation ensures your comfort, with refreshing beverages provided throughout. This privileged morning access creates an unparalleled encounter with humanity's most enduring architectural achievements.\\nJourney to the imposing Citadel of Saladin, exploring the stunning Muhammad Ali Mosque with its soaring domes and alabaster walls. Your guide reveals the fortress's military significance and Ottoman architectural grandeur while you enjoy panoramic Cairo views. Continue to the atmospheric Khan El Khalili bazaar, established in the 14th century, where master craftsmen practice traditional arts in historic alleyways. Discover hidden workshops, architectural gems, and authentic Egyptian culture. Savor a refined lunch at a distinguished restaurant serving contemporary Egyptian cuisine. Throughout your afternoon, experience personalized attention and cultural immersion in Cairo's living medieval heritage."}]	{CAIRO,GIZA}	CAIRO 	f	t	2026-02-11 16:26:44.912551	2026-02-11 17:46:15.562	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	
75bb70c3-6da1-4d5f-bfd7-69b77552b668	14-Day Egypt Small Group Tour | Pyramids & Nile	14-day-egypt-small-group-tour	Discover ancient Egypt on our exclusive 14-day small group tour limited to just 12 travelers. Experience personalized attention while exploring iconic sites with like-minded culture enthusiasts. Visit Cairo's legendary Pyramids and King Tut's treasures at the Grand Egyptian Museum. Explore the Valley of the Kings and marvel at Karnak Temple's massive columns. Sail the Nile aboard a deluxe five-star cruise with private balconies, stopping at Edfu and Kom Ombo temples. Witness the colossal Abu Simbel temples carved into solid rock. Your journey includes five-star hotels, all meals, expert Egyptologist guides, skip-the-line access, and internal flights. Travel with 8-10 fellow adventurers aged 45-75 who share your passion for history and authentic experiences. Unlike 40-person bus tours, our intimate group ensures flexible pacing, meaningful conversations with guides, and genuine friendships that last beyond the journey.	14 DAYS / 13 NIGHTS\nExperience Egypt through our intimate small group tour (max 12 guests). Visit Cairo's pyramids, King Tut's tomb, cruise the Nile aboard a 5-star vessel, and explore ancient temples with expert Egyptologist guides. All-inclusive luxury package.	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/1f92bc2d-458c-4cb4-8f02-cf833d6950f8.webp	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/5ad5da32-41d6-4fdf-a727-c0350bf9d918.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/79e00e30-ad06-4ca8-8ca4-86c523de1bc6.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/7822eb58-7861-40bb-9a16-e83d47be515a.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b78859b0-51bd-4558-b832-ef270ba213de.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/daf453a3-3d31-47d5-8e02-eb102b7f453b.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/d6657773-b5bf-472d-a469-bb44eeb67037.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/e9961960-63b4-45ba-911b-039d3bace10b.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/dfab7fb2-ccf4-4d4e-9cf9-07356eabcc4c.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/bacaf15e-a900-4eed-9ae5-b4d810c72a1f.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/4df11e4b-b452-440a-aa12-00a765778918.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b536283a-e70c-42ca-b811-85d4878e39f1.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/c8033b31-edad-40ee-94e8-979762c1f387.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b668e5a3-e9d9-4526-9852-3de8acdb3f45.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f6ac14fc-13a7-4348-9451-25e7b02d5e28.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f6ac14fc-13a7-4348-9451-25e7b02d5e28.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/e077fbe6-fb59-4f7c-b8d0-0d5478c563a1.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/608bc200-edcd-4fa5-bc0f-97b4113e04e2.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/6280fd1f-ff04-4f52-8703-23719e3f1817.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/2321186f-40e2-41d2-ba59-d9831aac0d5e.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/2321186f-40e2-41d2-ba59-d9831aac0d5e.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/75cf83b4-54f3-4e96-9cd0-566b3f5f2e32.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/c420326e-0dee-41dd-b42f-c1a9c8449ad4.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/b664afca-7e7e-4c4e-b509-89252a03c598.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/887cc5eb-f255-4c8e-86ad-f00d9c8ad823.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/26db5adc-8355-4513-952a-6ac5522dba18.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/856a09d6-4fd8-4d4b-9e40-228e1d8f318e.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/e2a89d16-7064-4f67-aea4-deb3e5e38a37.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/9a37f1b9-afb7-46ba-811f-e11975e6482e.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/8e1def19-a5d7-4c1f-8ca6-1a2844dec94f.jpg}	 14 Days / 13 Nights	8 - 12 	Easy	0	USD	{}	{}	[{"day": 1, "title": "Day 1 | Cairo - Arrival & Welcome Reception", "activities": [], "description": "Arrive at Cairo International Airport where your VIP representative meets you at the gate to fast-track visa and customs procedures. Enjoy a private luxury transfer to the historic Marriott Mena House hotel, featuring stunning views of the Pyramids of Giza from its landscaped gardens.\\n\\nThis evening, meet your fellow small group travelers (maximum 12 guests) and expert Egyptologist guide for a welcome reception. Learn about the exciting 14-day journey ahead as you begin your Egypt adventure in this iconic setting where you can see the pyramids illuminated at night from your hotel.\\n\\nOvernight: Marriott Mena House, Giza (5-star luxury)\\n\\nMeals: Welcome dinner included"}, {"day": 2, "title": "Day 2 | Saqqara & Giza - Pyramids & Sphinx", "activities": [], "description": "Begin at Saqqara, Egypt's oldest necropolis and home to the Step Pyramid of King Djoser, the world's first pyramid. Explore ancient tombs and burial chambers with remarkably preserved hieroglyphics and colorful reliefs.\\n\\nAfter lunch, experience exclusive VIP access at Giza Plateau including private entry to Great Pyramid chambers closed to regular visitors, special access between the paws of the Great Sphinx, and visits to Khafre's Valley Temple. Conclude with sunset viewing from a private panoramic spot as golden light bathes the ancient monuments.\\n\\nOvernight: Marriott Mena House, Giza\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 3, "title": "Day 3 | Cairo - Grand Egyptian Museum", "activities": [], "description": "Step into the Grand Egyptian Museum, a masterpiece of modern architecture housing over 50,000 artifacts spanning 7,000 years of history. Stand before the complete Tutankhamun collection displayed together for the first time, including his golden death mask, ornate throne, gilded chariots, and precious burial treasures.\\n\\nAdmire the monumental Khufu Boat, a magnificent 43-meter cedar vessel that carried the pharaoh to the afterlife. Evening features a private Egyptology lecture introducing the mysteries of ancient kings and queens whose footsteps you will follow throughout your journey.\\n\\nOvernight: Marriott Mena House, Giza\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 4, "title": "Day 4 | Beni Hassan - Ancient Rock Tombs", "activities": [], "description": "Travel south into Middle Egypt, a seldom-visited region rich in untouched historical treasures. At Beni Hassan, explore rock-cut tombs from the Middle Kingdom featuring vibrant scenes of daily life including sports competitions, musical performances, agricultural activities, and celebratory feasts.\\n\\nThese remarkably preserved paintings reveal the sophistication of provincial Egyptian life beyond the royal courts. Enjoy scenic drives through rural Egyptian countryside, seeing traditional village life that has remained largely unchanged for centuries.\\n\\nOvernight: House of Life Abydos\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 5, "title": "Day 5 | Tell el-Amarna - Akhenaten's Lost City", "activities": [], "description": "Begin at Tuna el-Gebel, a vast archaeological site featuring temples and extensive catacombs devoted to Thoth, the god of wisdom. Continue to Tell el-Amarna, the visionary city founded by revolutionary Pharaoh Akhenaten and Queen Nefertiti.\\n\\nWalk among ancient tombs decorated with vivid reliefs celebrating the worship of Aten, the sun god. These unique artworks showcase the artistic revolution that broke from traditional Egyptian conventions, depicting the royal family in intimate, naturalistic scenes never before seen in Egyptian art.\\n\\nOvernight: House of Life Abydos\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 6, "title": "Day 6 | Abydos & Dendera - Sacred Temples", "activities": [], "description": "Visit the magnificent Temple of Seti I in Abydos, where delicate carvings still shimmer with traces of original color. This temple is considered among Egypt's finest artistic achievements, with incredibly detailed hieroglyphics covering its walls and columns.\\n\\nContinue to Dendera Temple, dedicated to the goddess Hathor. Marvel at the famous astronomical ceiling featuring zodiac constellations and celestial deities, ranking among Egypt's most exquisite treasures. Transfer to Luxor and check in at the historic Sofitel Winter Palace, where European aristocrats and distinguished Egyptologists once stayed during Egypt's golden age of discovery.\\n\\nOvernight: Sofitel Winter Palace, Luxor\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 7, "title": "Day 7 | Luxor - Valley of the Kings (Private Access)", "activities": [], "description": "Explore the awe-inspiring Karnak Temple Complex with its forest of colossal papyrus columns, sacred lake, and long avenue of sphinxes. Continue to Luxor Temple, an elegant monument featuring massive statues of Ramses II that glows golden as evening falls.\\n\\nLater, experience extraordinary private after-hours access to the Valley of the Kings when the site closes to tourists. Explore the elaborately decorated royal tombs where Egypt's greatest pharaohs including Tutankhamun rest, enjoying the profound atmosphere without crowds for an unforgettable experience.\\n\\nOvernight: Sofitel Winter Palace, Luxor\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 8, "title": "Day 8 | Valley of Queens - Board Nile Cruise", "activities": [], "description": "Visit the Valley of the Queens to step inside the breathtaking Tomb of Queen Nefertari, often called Egypt's Sistine Chapel for its stunning artwork featuring vivid scenes with brilliantly preserved colors. Explore the Temple of Hatshepsut, a remarkable monument carved into limestone cliffs honoring Egypt's most successful female pharaoh.\\n\\nBoard your deluxe Nile cruise vessel, the MS Le Fayan, featuring spacious cabins with private balconies, gourmet dining, and elegant public spaces. Enjoy the captain's cocktail reception and dinner under the stars with traditional Egyptian entertainment as you begin sailing south toward Aswan.\\n\\nOvernight: MS Le Fayan Nile Cruise\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 9, "title": "Day 9 | Edfu & Kom Ombo Temples", "activities": [], "description": "Morning visit to the majestic Temple of Edfu, dedicated to the falcon god Horus. This is one of Egypt's best-preserved temples, offering a perfect example of ancient Egyptian architecture with its towering entrance pylons and massive columns.\\n\\nAfter lunch onboard, relax on the sun deck as you cruise past timeless landscapes of palm groves and rural villages. Afternoon stop at Kom Ombo Temple, a unique sanctuary dedicated to both Horus and Sobek the crocodile god, featuring perfect symmetrical design with duplicate halls and sanctuaries. Enjoy an elegant Egyptian-themed dinner with live music onboard.\\n\\nOvernight: MS Le Fayan Nile Cruise\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 10, "title": "Day 10 | Abu Simbel & Aswan", "activities": [], "description": "At dawn, take a short flight to Abu Simbel where four colossal 20-meter statues of Ramses II rise from the cliffs in one of ancient Egypt's most breathtaking monuments. Visit the adjacent temple honoring Queen Nefertari, celebrating the pharaoh's great love for his queen.\\n\\nReturn to Aswan to visit the High Dam, a modern engineering marvel that tamed the Nile's floods. Take a private boat to an authentic Nubian village where local culture thrives with vibrant colors, traditional architecture, and warm hospitality. Enjoy aromatic hibiscus tea with village families and learn about Nubian customs and daily life.\\n\\nOvernight: MS Le Fayan Nile Cruise\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 11, "title": "Day 11 | Philae Temple - Fly to Alexandria", "activities": [], "description": "Sail to Philae Island, home of the graceful Temple of Isis, goddess of magic and motherhood. This beautiful temple was rescued stone by stone by UNESCO and relocated to higher ground when the Aswan Dam was built. Walk through elegant colonnades featuring reliefs depicting ancient myths in one of Egypt's most romantic temple settings.\\n\\nVisit the Unfinished Obelisk in ancient granite quarries, revealing the secrets of how ancient Egyptians carved these massive monuments. Fly to Alexandria and check in at the elegant Four Seasons Hotel Alexandria at San Stefano, a seaside sanctuary overlooking the Mediterranean Sea.\\n\\nOvernight: Four Seasons Hotel Alexandria at San Stefano\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 12, "title": "Day 12 | Alexandria - Greek & Roman Sites", "activities": [], "description": "Explore Alexandria where Greek, Roman, and Egyptian civilizations once converged in magnificent fusion. Visit the Catacombs of Kom ash-Shuqqafa, remarkable underground burial chambers blending Egyptian and Greco-Roman architectural styles with intricate carvings and chambers on multiple levels.\\n\\nExplore the Roman Amphitheater revealing glimpses of daily life during Roman rule. See the magnificent Bibliotheca Alexandrina, a stunning modern rebirth of the ancient Library of Alexandria. End at the Citadel of Qaitbay, built on the site of the ancient Lighthouse of Alexandria, one of the Seven Wonders of the Ancient World.\\n\\nOvernight: Four Seasons Hotel Alexandria at San Stefano\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 13, "title": "Day 13 | Taposiris Magna - Return to Cairo", "activities": [], "description": "Enjoy exclusive access to Taposiris Magna, a sacred temple site where ongoing archaeological excavations continue to reveal mysteries. Some researchers believe this may be connected to Cleopatra's final resting place, making it one of Egypt's most intriguing active dig sites.\\n\\nReturn to Cairo for your final night at the Four Seasons Hotel Cairo at The First Residence, overlooking the Nile with panoramic city views. Celebrate with a farewell gala dinner featuring live Egyptian music, traditional dancers, and a gourmet feast, providing a fitting finale to your extraordinary journey through ancient and modern Egypt.\\n\\nOvernight: Four Seasons Hotel Cairo at The First Residence\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and farewell dinner included"}, {"day": 14, "title": "Day 14 | Cairo - Departure", "activities": [], "description": "After a leisurely breakfast with final views of the Nile River, enjoy some free time for last-minute shopping or relaxation at the hotel. Your private chauffeur escorts you to Cairo International Airport with plenty of time for your international departure, providing seamless VIP assistance through check-in and security.\\n\\nDepart with unforgettable memories of Egypt's timeless treasures, from Tutankhamun's golden artifacts to the colossal temples of Abu Simbel, from intimate Nubian villages to the grandeur of pharaonic monuments, carrying the spirit of ancient Egypt with you always.\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast included"}]	{Cairo,Giza,Minya,Abydos,Luxor,Aswan,"Abu Simbel",Alexandria}	Small Group Journeys 	f	t	2026-01-22 18:24:13.414711	2026-02-16 03:38:42.932	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/accb2108-f31b-4ce6-9f72-9d72c3cdddee.pdf
a9f9400d-955b-4778-8eee-07e533af1f01	10-Day Egypt Nile Cruise | Pyramids, Luxor & Aswan Experience	10-day-egypt-nile-cruise-experience	Sail the Nile in style on this classic 10-day Egypt tour combining iconic pyramids with a luxurious river cruise. Begin in Cairo exploring the Great Pyramids of Giza, mysterious Sphinx, and Saqqara necropolis. Discover King Tutankhamun's treasures at the Grand Egyptian Museum. Fly to Luxor to board your deluxe five-star Nile cruise featuring spacious cabins with private balconies and gourmet dining. Explore the Valley of the Kings with its royal tombs and marvel at Karnak Temple's massive columns. Sail south stopping at Edfu's Temple of Horus and Kom Ombo's unique double temple. In Aswan, visit the colossal Abu Simbel temples carved into solid rock and the beautiful island Temple of Philae. Includes five-star hotels, full-board cruise, all meals, expert guides, and internal flights.	10 DAYS / 9 NIGHTS\nClassic Egypt journey featuring Cairo's pyramids and a luxurious Nile cruise from Luxor to Aswan. Explore Valley of the Kings, Karnak Temple, and Abu Simbel. Sail aboard a deluxe five-star vessel. Small groups 8-12.	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/6917f991-c1be-470c-9474-075e026cebfb.webp	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/e7633f76-baa8-4074-a4b4-d3d23ff538a0.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/2c2e92cf-6c64-45e4-b874-b35b0a101451.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/6b421250-a123-4b77-9064-5745ee232bf3.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/40eee11e-e8fb-478a-a47a-124eacc4b32e.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/098587f1-3cfd-403d-b3d2-7b6f16036d27.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/7d04e9db-f611-41ac-8cc6-653bd7d5ca0f.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/1de3585a-bdbc-4c4f-8def-3c358e3e7eec.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/e80ea677-94f2-4d23-ba79-0c22ff97983d.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/e80ea677-94f2-4d23-ba79-0c22ff97983d.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/5c384d45-cb20-4895-9849-705e4f55a331.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/00af2958-35dc-45fe-b2f8-9291145f0057.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/95fe747a-3731-40eb-bf52-ac8e8edebb14.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/a310acbd-8462-4071-9c16-3c444657e9c1.jpg}	10 Days / 9 Nights	4 - 8 	Easy	0	USD	{}	{}	[{"day": 1, "title": "Day 1 | Cairo - Arrival & Pyramid Views", "activities": [], "description": "VIP concierge greets you airside at Cairo International Airport, providing seamless fast-track service through the private lounge before your comfortable Toyota Hiace transfer escorts you to Marriott Mena House. Your Pyramid View Room frames the ancient wonder through expansive floor-to-ceiling windows.\\n\\nEvening brings welcome dinner beneath stars in jasmine-scented gardens with illuminated pyramids as backdrop, featuring Egyptian mezze, succulent grilled meats, Mediterranean delicacies, and live oriental music setting the tone for your extraordinary journey ahead through Egypt's most iconic ancient sites.\\n\\nOvernight: Marriott Mena House, Cairo\\n\\nMeals: Welcome dinner included"}, {"day": 2, "title": "Day 2 | Saqqara & Memphis - Pyramid Evolution", "activities": [], "description": "Journey through Egypt's architectural evolution at Saqqara's Step Pyramid of Djoser, the world's first monumental stone structure designed by legendary Imhotep. Explore noble tombs with exquisite forty-three-hundred-year-old carvings depicting ancient daily life scenes.\\n\\nContinue to Memphis to stand before Ramses II's colossal statue and Egypt's ancient capital ruins. Conclude at Dahshur's Bent and Red Pyramids in serene desert solitude, descending into ancient chambers where priests walked forty-six centuries ago through dimly lit passages into the heart of these monuments.\\n\\nOvernight: Marriott Mena House, Cairo\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 3, "title": "Day 3 | Giza Plateau - Private Pyramid Access", "activities": [], "description": "Experience exclusive pre-opening access to the Giza Plateau in magical pre-dawn silence before crowds arrive. Enter the Great Pyramid's inner chambers in complete solitude, ascending the Grand Gallery to the King's Chamber where Khufu's empty sarcophagus rests eternally.\\n\\nStand between the Sphinx's paws with special permit reserved for dignitaries and archaeologists. Visit Valley Temple and capture panoramic photographs from the desert viewpoint. Afternoon leisure at Mena House offers pool relaxation or spa indulgence amid royal gardens with pyramid views.\\n\\nOvernight: Marriott Mena House, Cairo\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 4, "title": "Day 4 | Luxor - Board Nile Cruise", "activities": [], "description": "Domestic flight delivers you to Luxor, ancient capital of the New Kingdom where one-third of the world's monuments await discovery. Board MS Le Fayan, your floating five-star palace with only fifty suites ensuring intimate personalized service.\\n\\nCheck into your spacious Luxury Suite featuring private furnished balcony and marble bathroom before exploring Karnak Temple Complex with its breathtaking Hypostyle Hall. Gain private access to Khonsu Temple closed to regular visitors. Evening brings twilight-illuminated Luxor Temple followed by riverside dinner aboard your elegant vessel.\\n\\nOvernight: MS Le Fayan Luxury Nile Cruise\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 5, "title": "Day 5 | Valley of the Kings - Royal Tombs", "activities": [], "description": "Cross to the legendary West Bank by private motorboat to the Valley of the Kings where you visit Tutankhamun's tomb containing his mummy in its golden sarcophagus, plus spectacularly decorated royal tombs with vivid astronomical ceilings depicting the afterlife journey.\\n\\nExplore Queen Hatshepsut's Temple carved dramatically into limestone cliffs and photograph the massive Colossi of Memnon standing sentinel. Return for lunch as your ship sails toward Edfu, then enjoy afternoon spa treatments or sun deck relaxation before the Captain's Cocktail Reception under the stars.\\n\\nOvernight: MS Le Fayan Luxury Nile Cruise\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 6, "title": "Day 6 | Edfu & Kom Ombo Temples", "activities": [], "description": "Traditional horse-drawn carriage delivers you through Edfu's authentic streets to the Temple of Horus, Egypt's best-preserved ancient temple built between 237-57 BC with massive entrance gates and pristine hypostyle halls featuring detailed hieroglyphics.\\n\\nLunch aboard as you sail toward Kom Ombo watching timeless rural Egyptian life along the riverbanks. Late afternoon exploration of the unique dual temple honoring both crocodile god Sobek and falcon god Harpoeris features ancient surgical instruments before evening Egyptian Night celebration with traditional feast and folkloric performances.\\n\\nOvernight: MS Le Fayan Luxury Nile Cruise\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 7, "title": "Day 7 | Abu Simbel & Aswan", "activities": [], "description": "Pre-dawn departure brings you to Abu Simbel for witnessing Ramses II's four colossal sixty-five-foot statues illuminated by sunrise's first golden rays. Enter the temple penetrating sixty-three meters into solid mountainside to the inner sanctuary where sunlight illuminates the gods twice annually.\\n\\nVisit adjacent Temple of Nefertari featuring six equal-sized colossal statues honoring her extraordinary status. Return to Aswan for High Dam visit, authentic Nubian village with aromatic hibiscus tea, and sunset felucca sailing with champagne as golden light transforms the landscape into pure magic.\\n\\nOvernight: MS Le Fayan Luxury Nile Cruise\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 8, "title": "Day 8 | Philae Temple - Return to Cairo", "activities": [], "description": "Motorboat carries you across shimmering waters to Agilkia Island visiting the enchanting Temple of Philae, island sanctuary of goddess Isis rescued by UNESCO and reconstructed stone by stone on higher ground after the dam's construction. Walk through elegant colonnades covered in reliefs showing the Osiris myth resurrection story.\\n\\nVisit ancient granite quarries revealing the massive Unfinished Obelisk providing insights into ancient stone-carving techniques. Domestic flight returns you to Cairo and transfer to Four Seasons Hotel with spectacular high-floor Nile views and contemporary sophistication for your final nights.\\n\\nOvernight: Four Seasons Hotel Cairo at The First Residence\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 9, "title": "Day 9 | Grand Egyptian Museum & Farewell", "activities": [], "description": "Explore the Grand Egyptian Museum housing over one hundred thousand artifacts spanning five millennia of civilization. Ascend the monumental Grand Staircase and discover the complete Tutankhamun collection featuring the iconic golden death mask, golden throne with intricate inlay, ceremonial chariots, and exquisite jewelry displayed together for the first time.\\n\\nMarvel at Khufu's Solar Boat displayed in climate-controlled magnificence. Afternoon spa treatments or rooftop infinity pool relaxation followed by farewell gala dinner with fine Egyptian gastronomy, live traditional music, and personalized farewell gifts commemorating your unforgettable journey.\\n\\nOvernight: Four Seasons Hotel Cairo at The First Residence\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and farewell dinner included"}, {"day": 10, "title": "Day 10 | Cairo - Departure", "activities": [], "description": "After leisurely breakfast overlooking the Nile's shimmering expanse, enjoy final moments capturing photographs from your private balcony or reflecting on your extraordinary journey through five thousand years of human achievement and civilization.\\n\\nPrivate transfer to Cairo International Airport for your international flight with VIP departure assistance. Carry with you the timeless majesty of ancient Egypt, profound wisdom of the pharaohs, and treasured memories of exclusive experiences and exceptional service throughout this unforgettable odyssey.\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast included"}]	{Cairo,Giza,Luxor,Aswan,"Abu Simbel"}	Small Group Journeys 	f	t	2026-01-22 17:47:29.82155	2026-02-16 04:08:04.604	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	\N
f784fbcd-2747-4f7f-9c1d-4a53b8ab91af	All Inclusive Romantic Vacations | Egypt Honeymoon	all-inclusive-romantic-vacations-egypt-honeymoon	Among the world's most enchanting all inclusive romantic vacations, this seven-day Egyptian honeymoon weaves ancient wonders with contemporary luxury and intimate moments designed exclusively for couples. From candlelit Nile dinners beneath Cairo's starlit skyline to private beach serenades at the Red Sea, every carefully orchestrated experience celebrates your love story with five-star elegance, personalized surprises, and unforgettable encounters with civilization's greatest treasures in settings reserved for romance.\n	Discover all inclusive romantic vacations in Egypt. 7-day luxury honeymoon with pyramids, Luxor temples & Red Sea beaches. Private guides, 5-star hotels & romance.\n	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/be9c66c9-b71e-426d-b872-ebf8d372bf8a.jpg	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/4df731d6-55de-41a9-ba63-eb801044b74a.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/de3f39e9-4b79-4f29-ae75-5f42ef7e65e9.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/e9fbf4d6-0b99-4c78-bf5a-df75ec22ce47.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/3714f2de-56a6-4d8b-80ef-6e3ed819c255.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f393d0fd-8674-4dc5-9af2-547951f26dd2.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/43b0968d-641e-4e83-a578-ff327e4794dc.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/aea4948e-a930-4ad4-bd0c-b9b14ba24e24.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/aea4948e-a930-4ad4-bd0c-b9b14ba24e24.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/29f8e65b-2147-4686-bf00-cf5e45496cd4.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/2d4bb52c-e6ef-45ab-9f21-561886429ab8.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/349cba57-6600-44a5-9e5d-d978c4a7b019.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/e3002f44-a405-435b-8bc6-7c7b78156d5a.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/6c36235b-69c1-4c87-8bd1-977b667b880b.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f380d75a-b2cc-4062-a578-15b262075b41.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f4295cb4-fcc4-4ad2-84ea-2d39da6f46b9.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/1e241d3c-1adf-4a04-bac5-fba3659bea05.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/806cb922-5c5f-4c2d-a1ed-083ca51003e1.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/a5695399-1c3a-40a9-829a-888c4a48d4a5.jpg}	7 Days / 6 Nights	2 - 4	Moderate	0	USD	{}	{}	[{"day": 1, "title": "Day 1 | Welcome to Cairo – Romantic Nile Dinner Cruise", "activities": [], "description": "Begin your luxury Egyptian honeymoon with VIP meet-and-assist services at Cairo International before your private transfer to the iconic Marriott Mena House, a historic palace hotel offering breathtaking pyramid views from your romantic suite. Evening brings an enchanting dinner cruise on the Nile River complete with live traditional music, mesmerizing belly dancing performances, and delicious international buffet as you toast to your new life together while Cairo's glittering skyline passes beneath endless stars.\\nOvernight: Marriott Mena House, Cairo"}, {"day": 2, "title": "Day 2 | Great Pyramids of Giza & Egyptian Museum", "activities": [], "description": "Wake to unforgettable breakfast with panoramic pyramid views before your private Egyptologist guides you through the Great Pyramids of Giza, one of the Seven Wonders of the Ancient World, the enigmatic Great Sphinx, and Valley Temple. Continue to the Egyptian Museum or Grand Egyptian Museum to marvel at King Tutankhamun's golden treasures and thousands of ancient artifacts telling Egypt's golden age story. Evening leisure offers sunset cocktails overlooking illuminated pyramids creating perfect honeymoon moments captured forever.\\nOvernight: Marriott Mena House, Cairo"}, {"day": 3, "title": "Day 3 | Fly to Luxor – Karnak & Luxor Temples", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast overlooking eternal pyramids, your short domestic flight delivers you to Luxor, the world's greatest open-air museum and dream destination for romantic travelers. Check into the legendary Sofitel Winter Palace Luxor, an elegant Edwardian-era landmark where royalty and celebrities have celebrated love for over a century. Afternoon exploration of Karnak Temple, the largest ancient religious site in the world, and sunset-illuminated Luxor Temple offers hand-in-hand walks through the Avenue of Sphinxes immersed in ancient Thebes' magic.\\nOvernight: Sofitel Winter Palace Luxor"}, {"day": 4, "title": "Day 4 | West Bank Wonders & Transfer to Red Sea", "activities": [], "description": "Cross the Nile to Luxor's legendary West Bank for morning exploration of the Valley of the Kings where pharaohs including Tutankhamun rest eternally, Temple of Queen Hatshepsut carved into dramatic limestone cliffs, and the colossal Colossi of Memnon guarding the Theban Necropolis. After your profound morning discoveries, enjoy scenic private transfer through Egyptian countryside to Hurghada where crystal-clear Red Sea waters await at The Oberoi Beach Resort, Sahl Hasheesh, Egypt's most exclusive seaside sanctuary with private villas and unparalleled tranquility.\\nOvernight: The Oberoi Beach Resort, Sahl Hasheesh"}, {"day": 5, "title": "Day 5 | Red Sea Romance & Leisure", "activities": [], "description": "This day dedicates itself entirely to relaxation, romance, and celebrating each other in paradise. Unwind on the resort's pristine private beach, lounge in your luxurious villa's intimate spaces, or indulge in rejuvenating couples' spa treatments with Red Sea views. Optional adventures include snorkeling vibrant coral reefs teeming with tropical fish, private yacht charter along the breathtaking coastline, or water sports and marine exploration. As sun sets over turquoise waters, enjoy private candlelit dinner by the sea surrounded by gentle wave sounds.\\nOvernight: The Oberoi Beach Resort, Sahl Hasheesh"}, {"day": 6, "title": "Day 6 | Return to Cairo – Grand Finale", "activities": [], "description": "After leisurely beachfront breakfast savoring final Red Sea moments, fly back to Cairo for your final night in Egypt's vibrant capital. Check into a luxury five-star hotel with optional upgrade to Four Seasons Hotel Cairo at Nile Plaza for a grand honeymoon finale with panoramic river views. Spend evening exploring Cairo's modern sophistication, shopping for treasured souvenirs in boutique galleries, or simply enjoying romantic Nile views from your elegant suite while reflecting on extraordinary experiences shared together throughout this magical journey.\\nOvernight: Four Seasons Hotel Cairo at Nile Plaza"}, {"day": 7, "title": "Day 7 | Farewell Egypt – Hearts Full of Forever", "activities": [], "description": "Savor your final Egyptian breakfast with lingering Nile views before private transfer to Cairo International Airport for departure with VIP assistance. Leave with hearts overflowing with cherished memories and cameras filled with moments from your dream luxury Egyptian honeymoon, a perfect harmony of timeless history discovered hand-in-hand, world-class indulgence, and unforgettable romance celebrating your love story against civilization's most magnificent backdrop, knowing Egypt will forever hold special meaning in your hearts.\\nMeals: Breakfast"}]	{Cairo,Luxor,"Hurghada (Sahl Hasheesh)"}	Romantic Escapes 	f	t	2026-01-21 18:34:31.105678	2026-02-13 01:47:48.377	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/44510eac-a854-49ec-aeb3-5fe008cbbaaa.pdf
7bbb79ba-e5a5-4aec-af32-de6a020516d3	Day Trip from Aswan to Edfu & Kom Ombo Temples	aswan-edfu-kom-ombo-temples-day-trip	Journey through ancient Egypt on this captivating day trip from Aswan to Edfu and Kom Ombo temples. Visit the remarkably preserved Temple of Horus at Edfu and the unique double temple at Kom Ombo. This Edfu and Kom Ombo tour offers intimate encounters with Egypt's Ptolemaic treasures, stunning Nile views, and expert historical commentary.	Explore the stunning Edfu and Kom Ombo temples on a day trip from Aswan. Discover ancient Egyptian architecture and fascinating mythology with expert guides.	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/88f67ab3-9e6d-4185-9ac9-7ba11a13b4d5.jpg	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/88f67ab3-9e6d-4185-9ac9-7ba11a13b4d5.jpg}	1 Day	2-15 people	Moderate	0	USD	{"Private vehicle with professional driver "," Professional Egyptologist guide "," Hotel pickup and drop-off in Aswan "," Entrance fees to Edfu and Kom Ombo temples "," Entrance to Crocodile Museum "," Bottled water "," All taxes and service charges"}	{"International airfare "," Personal expenses "," Gratuities (optional) "," Any extras not mentioned"}	[{"day": 1, "title": "Day 1 | Edfu & Kom Ombo - Temple of Horus & Dual Deity Temple Exploration", "activities": ["Edfu & Kom Ombo - Temple of Horus & Dual Deity Temple Exploration"], "description": "Your temple discovery begins with morning pickup from your Aswan hotel for a scenic drive north along the Nile to Edfu. Arrive at the Temple of Horus, the best-preserved ancient temple in Egypt, built during the Ptolemaic period. Explore its massive pylons, spacious courtyard, and hypostyle hall featuring towering columns with intricate capitals. Your Egyptologist guide will explain the legendary battle between Horus and Seth depicted throughout the temple. Continue to Kom Ombo, uniquely positioned on a bend in the Nile. Discover this unusual double temple dedicated to both Sobek, the crocodile god, and Horus the Elder. Marvel at the symmetrical design with duplicate halls, sanctuaries, and courts. Examine fascinating reliefs including ancient surgical instruments and the Nilometer used to measure flood levels. Visit the Crocodile Museum displaying mummified crocodiles. Enjoy panoramic Nile views before returning to Aswan, arriving at your hotel by evening with deeper appreciation for Egypt's temple architecture."}]	{"Aswan "," Edfu "," Kom Ombo"}	ASWAN	f	t	2026-02-14 00:38:45.879184	2026-02-14 00:19:46.523	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	\N
8fc7b466-6994-4222-a12c-e67c1f0bc652	Two Days Trip to Luxor and Cairo from Aswan	two-days-luxor-cairo-tour-aswan	Embark on an extraordinary two days trip to Luxor and Cairo from Aswan covering Egypt's most iconic destinations. Explore Luxor's magnificent temples and royal tombs, then fly to Cairo to witness the Pyramids, Sphinx, and Egyptian Museum treasures. This comprehensive tour combines expert guidance, comfortable accommodations, and seamless logistics for an unforgettable Egyptian adventure.	Experience Egypt's greatest treasures on a 2-day tour from Aswan to Luxor and Cairo. Explore ancient temples, pyramids, and museums.	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/88f67ab3-9e6d-4185-9ac9-7ba11a13b4d5.jpg	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/88f67ab3-9e6d-4185-9ac9-7ba11a13b4d5.jpg}	2 Days / 1 Night	2-15 people	Moderate	0	USD	{"Private vehicles with professional drivers "," Professional Egyptologist guides "," Hotel pickup and drop-off in Aswan "," Domestic flights (Luxor-Cairo-Aswan) "," 1 night accommodation in Luxor (4-star hotel) "," Meals: 1 breakfast, 2 lunches, 1 dinner "," Entrance fees to all sites "," Bottled water "," All taxes and service charges"}	{"International airfare "," Personal expenses "," Gratuities (optional) "," Drinks during meals "," Any extras not mentioned"}	[{"day": 1, "title": "Day 1 | Luxor - Valley of the Kings, Karnak & Hatshepsut Temple Exploration", "activities": ["Luxor - Valley of the Kings, Karnak & Hatshepsut Temple Exploration"], "description": "Your two-day adventure begins with early morning pickup from your Aswan hotel and drive to Luxor. Cross to the West Bank to explore the Valley of the Kings, entering three spectacularly decorated royal tombs including vibrant wall paintings and hieroglyphic texts. Visit the magnificent Temple of Hatshepsut, carved into towering limestone cliffs, and photograph the Colossi of Memnon. Enjoy lunch at a local restaurant before crossing to the East Bank. Explore the vast Karnak Temple complex, wandering through the Great Hypostyle Hall with 134 massive columns, sacred lake, and numerous sanctuaries dedicated to Theban gods. Visit Luxor Temple, beautifully illuminated if time permits, connected to Karnak by the Avenue of Sphinxes. Check into your Luxor hotel for overnight stay, with dinner at the hotel or local restaurant. Relax and reflect on the day's discoveries while enjoying Nile views from your accommodation."}, {"day": 2, "title": "Day 2 | Cairo - Pyramids of Giza, Sphinx & Egyptian Museum Journey", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast and hotel checkout, transfer to Luxor Airport for your flight to Cairo. Upon arrival, meet your Egyptologist guide and drive to the Giza Plateau. Stand before the Great Pyramid of Khufu, Pyramid of Khafre, and Pyramid of Menkaure, learning about their construction mysteries and historical significance. Visit the Great Sphinx, the enigmatic limestone guardian watching over the pyramids for millennia. Continue to the Egyptian Museum in Tahrir Square, housing over 120,000 ancient artifacts including King Tutankhamun's golden treasures, royal mummies, jewelry, statues, and everyday objects spanning Egypt's pharaonic history. Your guide highlights the museum's most significant pieces while sharing captivating stories. Enjoy lunch at a quality Cairo restaurant before transferring to Cairo Airport for your flight back to Aswan. Upon arrival, transfer to your Aswan hotel, concluding your comprehensive two-day Egyptian odyssey with memories of Egypt's greatest monuments."}]	{"Aswan "," Luxor "," Cairo "," Valley of the Kings "," Karnak Temple "," Giza "," Egyptian Museum"}	ASWAN	f	t	2026-02-14 00:38:45.909753	2026-02-14 00:03:27.746	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	\N
2318aacf-ecc7-45c1-8cf6-475b2b0d7bee	14-Day Egypt Family Tour | Nile, Abu Simbel & Red Sea	14-day-egypt-family-tour	Discover Egypt's wonders on our exclusive 14-day family small group tour limited to just 12 travelers. Experience personalized attention while exploring iconic sites with like-minded families. Visit Cairo's legendary Pyramids and King Tut's treasures at the Grand Egyptian Museum. Journey to Alexandria's Mediterranean coast and Siwa Oasis desert paradise. Sail the Nile aboard a deluxe five-star cruise with private balconies. Conclude with Red Sea beach relaxation, snorkeling, and water activities.\n\nYour journey includes five-star family-friendly hotels, all meals, expert Egyptologist guides, skip-the-line access, internal flights, and age-appropriate activities including Junior Pharaoh programs, treasure hunts, camel rides, and hands-on cultural workshops. Travel with 8-12 fellow families who share your passion for adventure and authentic experiences. Unlike 40-person bus tours, our intimate group ensures flexible pacing, meaningful conversations with guides, and genuine friendships that last beyond the journey.	14 DAYS / 13 NIGHTS Experience Egypt through our family-friendly small group tour (max 12 guests). Explore pyramids, Alexandria, Siwa Oasis, luxury Nile cruise, and Red Sea beaches. Perfect for families with children of all ages.	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/695a8d6e-c479-47af-85e6-e3ef76158240.jpg	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/43355952-ab3c-41cf-87a3-27197170b5c3.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/39e9e95e-06c8-4df9-b53a-189664eba376.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/0f1c6211-d015-4808-9647-e5a90643a049.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/9dd277f5-4eaa-4356-b675-783e45bbea12.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/ed32747f-9e7f-4c6a-9ebe-b2a463a40a23.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f411b305-a5e7-4685-97ff-59efeca82676.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/a07b323b-3b5e-4029-b00e-a50ae4de7f88.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/82b4e3ef-5776-4c37-a8fb-3ffe98d5859e.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/89070e2a-c7c2-4033-8ad6-e4ad2734e169.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/d42ed466-97cd-408f-ad2b-b8be6b3e4479.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/de8ae4c3-357f-4333-8d5b-e8ea49dbefc5.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/afa0e621-09ba-4d07-babf-88725531f0b5.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/672bbfe5-3791-49b9-858a-fb95939e5d78.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/f2d13abc-0b42-4051-947b-baaf441ac2cc.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/583ea0c1-6dee-45b2-9a53-33c159f358c2.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/66436da4-dac0-4c70-aec4-dab4c9b7f569.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/d585c358-8aad-4405-8e0a-52963d752905.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/ffd27fae-72bf-42f0-b6b2-97684f976269.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/9e46cd18-afd9-48da-a025-08e68ae18294.jpg,https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/79fbfa8a-0c19-4121-beb9-e749910c5a0e.jpg}	14 Days / 13 Nights	4 - 8 	Moderate	0	USD	{"Meet-and-assist service by our representatives at all airports","All transfers by private air-conditioned vehicles","2 nights accommodation at Marriott Mena House, Giza (Family Suite)","1 night accommodation at Four Seasons Hotel Alexandria (Family Room)","2 nights accommodation at Eco-Lodge, Siwa (Family Room)","1 night accommodation at Desert Camp, Great Sand Sea","4 nights accommodation on Nile Cruise (Family Suite)","3 nights accommodation at Red Sea Resort (Family Suite)","Domestic flights: Siwa to Luxor, Aswan to Red Sea","All entry fees to temples, tombs, and museums mentioned in the itinerary","Services of a private Egyptologist guide throughout cultural tours","4x4 desert safari and sandboarding","Snorkeling excursion to Giftun Islands with marine biologist","Camel ride at Giza","Traditional felucca sailboat rides","Horse-drawn carriage at Edfu Temple","Private motorboat to Philae Temple","All meals stated in the itinerary – (B) for breakfast, (L) for lunch, (D) for dinner","Bottled water during all tours and meals","Welcome gifts for children","24/7 on-call support","All applicable taxes and VAT"}	{"International flights to and from Cairo","Gratuities for guides, drivers, cruise staff, and lodge staff","Alcoholic beverages","Travel insurance"}	[{"day": 1, "title": "Day 1 | Cairo - Arrival & Pyramid Views", "activities": [], "description": "Arrive at Cairo International Airport where your VIP representative meets you at the gate to fast-track visa and customs procedures. Comfortable Toyota Hiace transfer to Marriott Mena House, a historic hotel set in royal gardens at the foot of the Pyramids. Check into your spacious family suite with private terrace framing direct pyramid views. Evening welcome reception with your fellow small group families (maximum 12 guests) and expert Egyptologist guide who introduces the exciting 14-day journey ahead.\\n\\nOvernight: Marriott Mena House, Cairo\\n\\nMeals: Welcome dinner included"}, {"day": 2, "title": "Day 2 | Giza & Saqqara - Ancient Pyramids", "activities": [], "description": "Begin at the Giza Plateau exploring the Great Pyramids and mysterious Sphinx. Your small group size ensures everyone can hear your guide clearly. Visit the Solar Boat Museum before continuing to Saqqara where King Djoser's Step Pyramid stands as the world's oldest stone structure. Children participate in Junior Pharaoh Adventure with hands-on hieroglyphics activities on papyrus. Afternoon camel rides across golden sands create unforgettable family memories together.\\n\\nOvernight: Marriott Mena House, Cairo\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 3, "title": "Day 3 | Grand Egyptian Museum & Alexandria", "activities": [], "description": "Marvel at the Grand Egyptian Museum housing Tutankhamun's complete golden collection including his death mask and five thousand treasures. Your intimate group explores at comfortable pace. Drive north to Alexandria visiting ancient Catacombs and Qaitbay Citadel where the legendary Lighthouse once stood. Children enjoy scavenger hunt discovering architectural treasures. Evening check-in at Four Seasons Alexandria overlooking the Mediterranean.\\n\\nOvernight: Four Seasons Hotel Alexandria\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 4, "title": "Day 4 | Alexandria & Siwa - Desert Journey", "activities": [], "description": "Morning at Bibliotheca Alexandrina, the stunning modern library. After lunch, begin the scenic drive to Siwa Oasis deep in the Western Desert. The approximately 9-hour journey allows your small group families to bond together. Arrive at your eco-lodge surrounded by thousands of date palm groves. Evening 4x4 desert safari explores surrounding dunes where families try sandboarding before watching sunset transform the Sahara into shades of amber and gold.\\n\\nOvernight: Eco-Lodge, Siwa\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 5, "title": "Day 5 | Siwa Oasis - Cultural Discovery", "activities": [], "description": "Visit the Temple of the Oracle where Alexander the Great sought divine guidance. Explore Shali Fortress with panoramic oasis views. Float in sparkling salt lakes more buoyant than the Dead Sea. Children participate in cultural workshops learning traditional Siwan pottery, basket weaving, and desert crafts from local artisans. Your small group size allows personalized instruction and meaningful cultural exchange with village families.\\n\\nOvernight: Eco-Lodge, Siwa\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 6, "title": "Day 6 | Great Sand Sea - Desert Safari", "activities": [], "description": "Full-day 4x4 desert safari across the Great Sand Sea where massive dunes create dramatic golden landscapes. Your small group navigates hidden valleys discovering adapted desert wildlife. Arrive at your desert camp among towering dunes. As darkness falls, billions of stars appear overhead. Gather around the campfire listening to ancient Bedouin legends while your chef prepares traditional dinner under endless Saharan skies.\\n\\nOvernight: Desert Camp, Great Sand Sea\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 7, "title": "Day 7 | Luxor - Board Nile Cruise", "activities": [], "description": "After morning farewell to Siwa, fly to Luxor and board your deluxe Nile cruise vessel. Check into spacious family suites with private balconies and panoramic river views. Your intimate cruise group of 8-12 families ensures personalized service. Afternoon welcome reception as the vessel begins sailing through timeless landscapes. Children enjoy treasure hunt activities while parents relax on sun decks watching rural Egyptian life unfold along ancient shores.\\n\\nOvernight: Nile Cruise\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 8, "title": "Day 8 | Valley of the Kings - Royal Tombs", "activities": [], "description": "Cross the Nile to Luxor's West Bank exploring the Valley of the Kings where pharaohs rested for over 500 years. Visit Tutankhamun's tomb and spectacularly decorated royal tombs with vivid colors preserved for over 3,000 years. Continue to Queen Hatshepsut's dramatic mortuary temple and the colossal Memnon statues. Children participate in Discover Ancient Symbols treasure hunt while your small group explores together without rushing.\\n\\nOvernight: Nile Cruise\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 9, "title": "Day 9 | Edfu Temple - Sacred to Horus", "activities": [], "description": "Arrive at Edfu visiting the Temple of Horus by traditional horse-drawn carriage through authentic local streets. Explore one of Egypt's best-preserved ancient temples built between 237-57 BC with massive entrance pylons. Your intimate group size means plenty of time for questions and photos. Afternoon sailing continues as you relax on sun decks while children enjoy onboard activities and parents unwind together.\\n\\nOvernight: Nile Cruise\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 10, "title": "Day 10 | Kom Ombo & Aswan - Nile Journey", "activities": [], "description": "Visit Kom Ombo's unique dual temple dedicated to both Horus and Sobek, dramatically positioned on a riverside promontory. View the crocodile mummy collection. Continue sailing to Aswan where your small group enjoys onboard Egyptian cooking class. Families prepare traditional dishes together learning authentic recipes. Evening features entertainment with belly dancing and music as the Nile carries you toward Egypt's southern frontier.\\n\\nOvernight: Nile Cruise\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 11, "title": "Day 11 | Philae Temple & Nubian Village", "activities": [], "description": "Take a motorboat to Agilkia Island visiting beautiful Philae Temple dedicated to goddess Isis. The temple was relocated stone by stone by UNESCO. Afternoon visits a traditional Nubian village where children participate in painting workshops and learn traditional drumming rhythms. Experience warm Nubian hospitality with aromatic hibiscus tea while discovering unique colorful architecture and culture. Optional evening felucca sailboat ride among the islands.\\n\\nOvernight: Nile Cruise\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 12, "title": "Day 12 | Red Sea Coast - Beach Paradise", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, disembark and transfer to Aswan Airport for your flight to the Red Sea coast. Transfer to your luxury beachfront resort. Check into spacious family suites with private balconies overlooking turquoise waters. Afternoon at leisure enjoying pristine beaches and multiple swimming pools. Evening welcome dinner at one of the resort's specialty restaurants while your small group families reunite after the flight.\\n\\nOvernight: Red Sea Resort, Hurghada\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 13, "title": "Day 13 | Red Sea - Snorkeling Adventure", "activities": [], "description": "Board a private boat for your small group's full-day excursion to Giftun Islands Marine Reserve. Snorkel among colorful coral reefs teeming with tropical fish and sea turtles guided by a marine biologist. Younger children view underwater wonders through glass-bottom sections. Lunch onboard features fresh grilled seafood. Your intimate group size ensures flexible timing and personalized attention throughout this memorable aquatic adventure.\\n\\nOvernight: Red Sea Resort, Hurghada\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast, lunch, and dinner included"}, {"day": 14, "title": "Day 14 | Red Sea - Departure", "activities": [], "description": "After leisurely final breakfast overlooking turquoise waters, enjoy last moments with your travel group families who've become friends. Time for final swims or pool relaxation while reminiscing about pyramids, desert safaris, Nile cruising, and snorkeling discoveries. Private transfer to the airport with VIP departure assistance. Depart Egypt carrying memories of ancient wonders and precious family moments created with like-minded travelers.\\n\\nMeals: Breakfast included"}]	{Cairo,Giza,Alexandria,Siwa,"Great Sand Sea",Luxor,Edfu,"Kom Ombo",Aswan,"Red Sea"}	Family Travel 	f	t	2026-01-21 17:18:02.621751	2026-02-16 08:09:32.719	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/44510eac-a854-49ec-aeb3-5fe008cbbaaa.pdf
