xtraordinary day at the Giza Plateau, where your expert guide escorts you through the magnificent Pyramids of Khufu, Khafre, and Menkaure. Stand before these architectural marvels while learning their construction mysteries, astronomical alignments, and royal significance. Approach the enigmatic Great Sphinx, the colossal limestone guardian with its lion body and pharaoh's face, for intimate viewing and stunning photography. Your private access ensures exploration without crowds, while your Egyptologist shares insights into ancient Egyptian religion, engineering prowess, and burial traditions. Refreshing beverages and comfort maintained throughout your morning exploration.\\nJourney to Memphis, Egypt's magnificent capital for over 3,000 years and the heart of Old Kingdom power. Your guide escorts you through this open-air museum where the colossal statue of Ramses II reclines in limestone grandeur. Marvel at the exquisite Alabaster Sphinx and discover artifacts from Memphis's golden age. Learn about the city's religious significance, administrative importance, and eventual decline. Savor a gourmet lunch at a distinguished restaurant featuring authentic Egyptian specialties with contemporary refinement. Your personalized journey concludes with a relaxed return to Cairo, enriched by ancient Egyptian majesty."}]	{CAIRO,GIZA}	CAIRO 	f	t	2026-02-11 16:33:06.870652	2026-02-11 17:50:08.841	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	
fa09982d-034b-474a-9598-0a4a83881a69	Felucca Ride on the Nile in Aswan	felucca-ride-nile-aswan	Experience the timeless beauty of the Nile on this relaxing felucca ride on the Nile in Aswan aboard a traditional sailboat. Glide peacefully past Elephantine Island, botanical gardens, and desert landscapes while enjoying gentle breezes and stunning views. This felucca sailing tour offers authentic Egyptian river culture and serene Nile moments.	Sail the Nile on a traditional felucca in Aswan. Enjoy peaceful sailing, stunning river views, and authentic Egyptian boat experience.	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/88f67ab3-9e6d-4185-9ac9-7ba11a13b4d5.jpg	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/88f67ab3-9e6d-4185-9ac9-7ba11a13b4d5.jpg}	2-3 hours	2-15 people	Easy	0	USD	{"Private traditional felucca sailboat "," Experienced Nubian captain "," Hotel pickup and drop-off in Aswan "," Comfortable cushioned seating "," All taxes and service charges"}	{"International airfare "," Personal expenses "," Gratuities (optional) "," Any extras not mentioned"}	[{"day": 1, "title": "Day 1 | Aswan - Traditional Felucca Sailing & Nile Island Views", "activities": ["Aswan - Traditional Felucca Sailing & Nile Island Views"], "description": "Your peaceful Nile adventure begins with pickup from your Aswan hotel and transfer to the river's edge. Board your traditional wooden felucca sailboat, used for centuries on the Nile, and settle onto comfortable cushions. Your skilled Nubian captain hoists the large white sail, catching the wind as you glide gracefully across the sparkling blue waters. Sail past Elephantine Island, observing the Nubian villages, ancient ruins, and lush vegetation along its shores. Drift by the Aswan Botanical Garden on Kitchener's Island, a verdant oasis showcasing exotic plants and palm trees. Enjoy panoramic views of the Aga Khan Mausoleum perched on the western hills and the Old Cataract Hotel's Victorian grandeur. Listen to the gentle lapping of water against the boat and watch traditional feluccas with colorful sails crossing your path. Observe local fishermen, children playing along the banks, and birds soaring overhead. Return to the embarkment point and transfer back to your hotel, refreshed by your tranquil Nile experience."}]	{"Aswan "," Elephantine Island"}	ASWAN	f	t	2026-02-14 00:38:45.902852	2026-02-14 00:05:27.342	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	\N
