er royal mummies, intricate papyri, and monumental statues while your guide reveals the stories behind these priceless artifacts. Climate-controlled halls and personalized pacing ensure comfortable exploration. Your morning concludes with privileged insights into ancient Egyptian art, religion, and daily life.\\nStroll through elegant downtown Cairo, exploring Belle Époque architecture from Egypt's cosmopolitan golden age. Your guide reveals the history behind Talaat Harb Street's European-inspired buildings, the majestic Cairo Opera House area, and distinguished landmarks. Visit the refined Café Riche, a historic gathering place for intellectuals and artists. Explore the atmospheric streets where modern Egyptian culture emerged. Savor an exquisite lunch at a distinguished restaurant serving contemporary Egyptian cuisine with international sophistication. Throughout your afternoon, experience Cairo's sophisticated urban heritage and vibrant cultural scene before your comfortable return to your hotel."}]	{CAIRO,GIZA}	CAIRO 	f	t	2026-02-11 16:41:21.306716	2026-02-11 17:54:12.288	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	
ed741832-1639-4bd2-991a-2bee2c6bbbe4	Full-Day Aswan City Highlights Sightseeing Tour	aswan-city-highlights-sightseeing-tour	Explore the jewels of Nubia on this comprehensive Aswan sightseeing tour that showcases the city's most remarkable attractions. Visit the engineering marvel of the High Dam, the enchanting Philae Temple, and the massive Unfinished Obelisk. This full-day Aswan tour combines ancient history with modern achievements, offering insights into Egypt's rich cultural heritage and stunning Nile scenery.	Discover Aswan's iconic landmarks on a comprehensive sightseeing tour. Visit the High Dam, Philae Temple, and Unfinished Obelisk with expert guides.	https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/88f67ab3-9e6d-4185-9ac9-7ba11a13b4d5.jpg	{https://iluxuryegypt.com/api/assets/uploads/88f67ab3-9e6d-4185-9ac9-7ba11a13b4d5.jpg}	1 Day	2-15 people	Easy	0	USD	{"Private vehicle with professional driver "," Professional Egyptologist guide "," Hotel pickup and drop-off in Aswan "," Motorboat to Philae Temple "," Entrance fees to all sites "," Bottled water "," All taxes and service charges"}	{"International airfare "," Personal expenses "," Gratuities (optional) "," Any extras not mentioned"}	[{"day": 1, "title": "Day 1 | Aswan - High Dam, Unfinished Obelisk & Philae Temple Discovery", "activities": ["Aswan - High Dam, Unfinished Obelisk & Philae Temple Discovery"], "description": "Begin your Aswan exploration with pickup from your hotel and head to the impressive Aswan High Dam, completed in 1970. Learn how this modern engineering feat controls the Nile's flooding and generates hydroelectric power while creating the vast Lake Nasser. Continue to the ancient granite quarries to witness the Unfinished Obelisk, the largest known ancient obelisk that would have stood 42 meters tall if completed. Your guide will explain the ancient stone-cutting techniques used by Egyptian craftsmen. Next, take a scenic motorboat ride to Agilkia Island to explore the magnificent Philae Temple, dedicated to the goddess Isis. Admire the beautifully preserved reliefs, towering columns, and intricate hieroglyphics that adorn this Ptolemaic-era masterpiece, which was relocated stone by stone to save it from flooding. Wander through the temple's courts, sanctuaries, and chapels while your Egyptologist guide shares captivating myths and historical insights. Return to your hotel with comprehensive knowledge of Aswan's treasures."}]	{"Aswan "," High Dam "," Philae Temple "," Unfinished Obelisk"}	ASWAN	f	t	2026-02-14 00:38:45.875358	2026-02-14 00:36:11.57	73480e9b-4af4-4782-9d1d-a7269fc854e2	\N
