de will explain the history and construction of these ancient monuments. Continue to Saqqara to visit the Step Pyramid of Djoser, the oldest pyramid in Egypt. Visit Memphis to see the colossal statue of Ramses II. After lunch, return to your hotel to freshen up before your evening flight to Aswan. Check in at your hotel on an island in the Nile.\\nOvernight: Mövenpick Resort Aswan (B, L)"}, {"day": 3, "title": "Day 3 | Abu Simbel – Monument to Eternal Love", "activities": [], "description": "Early morning drive to Abu Simbel to visit the temples of Ramses II and Nefertari, carved into the mountainside. Your guide will explain the history and significance of these UNESCO World Heritage temples. Return to Aswan in the afternoon. Afternoon free for optional activities such as a felucca sailboat ride, visiting the local markets, or relaxing at the hotel.\\nOvernight: Mövenpick Resort Aswan (B)"}, {"day": 4, "title": "Day 4 | Aswan to Luxor – Temples & Timeless Beauty", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, visit the Temple of Philae, dedicated to the goddess Isis. Take a motorboat across the water to reach the temple on the island. Continue to the High Dam and the Unfinished Obelisk, where you can see ancient stone-cutting techniques. After lunch, drive to Luxor. Visit the Valley of the Kings and enter selected royal tombs. Continue to the Temple of Hatshepsut, carved into the cliffs, and stop at the Colossi of Memnon. Evening visit to Karnak Temple before checking in at your hotel.\\nOvernight: Hilton Luxor Resort & Spa (B, L)"}, {"day": 5, "title": "Day 5 | Farewell Egypt – A Heart Full of Memories", "activities": [], "description": "After breakfast, morning at leisure to enjoy the hotel facilities or visit Luxor Temple. Depending on your flight schedule, you may have time for last-minute shopping before your transfer to Luxor Airport for your flight to Cairo and onward international connection.\\n(B)"}]	{Cairo,Aswan,"Abu Simbel",Luxor}	Solo Travel 	f	t	2